<title>Affinity - Bikeway</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h2 align=center>City of Cleveland Announces Expansion of Bikeway</h2>
<p>After many years of planning and talking, the first phases have begun for a greenbelt and bikeway 
that will eventually connect the east side of Cleveland and its suburbs to the downtown. The plan, 
which includes a bikepath along the Cleveland section of Lake Erie, finally got funding for the 
section that connects the Inner Harbor with University Circle. </p>
<p>Running along Martin Luther King Blvd. and North Marginal Rd., the route will be used both by 
commuters and recreationists alike. Over 2 million people every year are expected to use the path. 
Nearly twenty years in the making, local cyclists point to momentum created by the opening of the 
Rock and Roll Hall of Fame.</p>
