<head>
<title>Affinity - Hempfields</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h3 align=center>Hempfields</h3>
<p>Hemp is the strongest, most versatile and evolved plant on Earth and is organically grown. George 
Washington grew hemp, Betsy Ross crafted the first American flag out of hemp and Ben Franklin 
opened a hemp paper mill so that America would not be dependent upon British sources of paper.<br>
Hemp has been know to humankind for thousands of years. Hemp has been used for food, fuel, 
clothing, medicine and much more. The use of hemp products have many environmentally and 
economic benefits. Hemp even has the potential to replace more than three-quarters of the nation&#185;s 
fiber needs currently served by logging, and could make the petro-chemical industry virtually 
obsolete.</p>
<p>Hemp is known as our planet&#185;s most prolific plant. It grows more in one season and produces 
more biomass than any other plant. It has the potential to make the U.S. energy independent. 
Because it is an annual plant that breaks down naturally, it fits in well with the many environmental 
cycles and contributes greatly to the CO2, the oxygen balance that all species need to survive.</p>
<p>Hemp could replace 70 percent of the wood-pulp-based paper produced in this country. It is one 
of the first crops ever cultivated (grown since about 8,000 B.C.), is the strongest, most rot-resistant 
natural fiber known, and up until the 1880s, provided 80 percent of all paper. The 1850 U.S. 
Census reported that there were 8,237 hemp farms with over 2,000 acres under cultivation. 
Botanists tell us that hemp also is acomplete protein with eight essential amino acids. The seeds can 
be sprouted or made into a tofu-type curd or margarine.</p>
<p>Helping to increase awareness about hemp and the products that can be derived from this plant is 
Cleveland&#185;s first hemp store HEMPFIELDS. Open for a year now (Happy Birthday Hempfields), 
Hempfields sells an array of hemp products including clothes (jeans, dresses, lingerie), Adidas 
shoes, jewelry, cosmetics, baseball caps, backpacks, food, etc. Hempfields is committed to 
promoting hemp products and making a difference in the world.</p>
<p>Hempfields also has excellent information concerning hemp and they are willing to share their 
knowledge of this important plant. Hempfields is currently seeking a Goddess partner/investor to 
expand this fast growing environmentally friendly business with limitless potential.</p>
<p>For more information stop in at Hempfields, 11798 Detroit Ave, Lakewood or call (216) 
226-2229.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
