<html>

<head>
<title>Affinity - Herbal Sage</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h2 align=center>The Herbal Sage</h2>
<p>United Plant Savers (UPS) is dedicated to replanting endangered and threatened medicinal plants. 
UPS is a newly founded, non-profit organization dedicated to saving endangered and threatened 
medicinal plants. An organization for herbalists and people who love plants, their purpose is to 
ensure the future of our rich diversity of medicinal plants.Vast numbers of plants have been and 
continue to be taken and indiscriminate wildharvesting, deforestation and urbanization have 
devastated many areas of former abundance. Perhaps even more disturbing, native North 
American medicinal plants are being exported to meet the demand in other countries where wild 
plants have already been gravely depleted. UPS was formed in a spirit of hope, as a group of 
herbalists committed to protecting and replanting threatened species and to raise public awareness 
of the plight of our wild medicinal plants.</p>
<p>Fortunately,&#160;The Herbal Sage (located in the Cleveland Shop at 11606 Detroit Ave., Lakewood) 
only sells herbs that can be traced back to the grower. They are accountable for how and where 
the herbs are grown, and assure high quality and chemical-free herbs. The Herbal Sage is 
committed to selling herbs that will not endanger the plant.</p>
<p>Many herbs have been so over-picked that they are now endangered. For example, Golden Seal 
has been picked almost to the point of extinction due to over harvesting of the plant in its natural 
habitat. The Herbal Sage will special order herbs in amounts less than 1#. In the spring, The Herbal 
Sage sells organic plants from the Herbal Sage farm near Athens, Ohio. You can buy herbs dried, 
tinctures, extracts and aroma therapy essential oils.</p>
<p>The Herbal Sage will be conducted workshop series throughout Cleveland expressing the medicinal 
values of herbs. For example, slippery elm bark is great for soothing sore throats, red raspberry 
leaf strengthens womens reproductive systems and cat nip tea soothes the stomach and helps 
colicky babies. Handouts are available at The Herbal Sage. Also, ask for their teas at your favorite 
coffee house.</p>
<p>The Herbal Sage is in the Cleveland Shop which sells vintage clothing and era costume rental since 
1979. For more information call (216) 228-9725.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
