<p><font size="2">Letter from the Editor:</font></p>

<p><font size="2">Welcome to the Early Winter issue of Affinity.
The cover story discusses the issue of deforestation in Ohio.
Unfortunately, after many years the Forest Service has decided,
against public opinion, to log in the Wayne National Forest. Now
is the time to voice your opinion on logging in Ohio&#146;s only
national forest. Call the Buckeye Forest Council - (614) 594-6400
- if you want to get involved in the zero-cut campaign. YOUR HELP
IS NEEDED!</font></p>

<p><font size="2">Another issue that needs immediate attention is
air pollution standards. The U.S. EPA recently revised the
National Ambient Air Quality Standards for ozone and particulates
and are ready to set strict standards that should help clean up
our air. The U.S. EPA needs to here from citizens now encouraging
them to go through with setting these standards. Letters need to
be sent to Administrator Carol Browner, Environmental Protection
Agency, 401 M Street, SW, Washington, D.C. 20460.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">The center-spread focuses on the meat industry
and how they pose a threat to public health and the environment.
The articles also discuss a recently released report that
explains the highly consolidated U.S. meat industry, detailing
the links between industry concentration and chronic bacterial
contamination of the meat supply that continues to claim
thousands of lives every year.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">Give an education gift for the holidays.
Receive Affinity right at your home. See the
subscription/donation form on page 15 for more information.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">Affinity thanks the advertisers who make this
publication possible. Also, thanks to the volunteers who help out
in the office and with distribution. I hope everyone has a great
holiday and enjoys the beginning of the winter season.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">The next issue will be will be distributed on
February 1.</font></p>

<p><font size="2">Until next time,</font></p>

<p><font size="2">Stefanie Mugridge</font></p>

