<title>Affinity - Nature's Bin</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h2 align=center>Nature's Bin</h2>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>Concerned about environmental and health risks from foods treated with agricultural chemicals? 
You are not alone. According to a recent survey done by HealthFocus, environmental concerns 
have surpassed health concerns to become the primary reason consumers buy organic foods. Yet, 
in a poll conducted by Louis Harris and Organic Gardening, 64 percent of those surveyed said that 
long term health benefits are the single most important reason for eating organic food, and 84 
percent would prefer organic food if it was readily available. </p>
<p>Organic farming is done without agricultural chemicals that seriously impact the health of wildlife. 
Pesticides and herbicides used in conventional farming enter the food chain and are believed by 
many to be directly responsible for deformation, cancer and premature death among several animal 
species. Additionally, chemicals that enter the food web through vegetation and water have long 
lasting and cumulative environmental effects.At Nature's Bin they make every effort to assure the 
purity and quality of everything they sell. Nature's Bin is a full service natural food store. Their 
emphasis is on quality fresh produce with a complete organic section.</p>
<p>Nature's Bin also carries Eden Foods which is OCIA certified organic. A long-standing leader in 
the Natural Foods industry, Eden Foods has maintained and enhanced the highest standards for 
organically grown foods. Eden standards reflect their growers' commitment to sustainable, 
non-chemical farming. Nature's Bin recently celebrated the grand opening of their second store in 
Cleveland Heights at 2255 Lee Road - (216) 932-2342. The first store they opened is located in 
Lakewood at 18120 Sloane Ave. - (216) 521-4600. Nature's Bin is operated by Cornucopia, 
Inc., a nonprofit organization founded in Lakewood in 1975. </p>
<p>At their new store they have a juice bar which highlights organic juice. Customers can buy organic 
carrot, carrot &amp; celery, V4: carrot, celery, beet and purple cabbage, and apple juice. They also 
serve smoothies, protein drinks, Kombucha tea, herbal tea and coffee.Nature's Bin provides a &quot;real 
work&quot; training environment. People with mental retardation and developmental disabilities learn 
basic vocational and social skills by playing an active role in produce, grocery, deli/bakery, 
maintenance and customer service department activities. Proceeds from retail sales are invested in 
the training program.</p>
<p>Anyone who has not yet visited either of the Nature's Bin stores is encouraged to do so.</p>
<hr>
