<title>affinity - Tinker's Creek</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<h2 align=center>Ohio EPA Favors Parking Lot Over Waterway</h2>
<p>In a devastating decision for the future of waterways in Ohio, the Ohio EPA last week approved a 
proposal for a developer to move 1000 feet of Tinker's Creek in Twinsburg. The developer plans 
to put in a parking lot for a strip mall where this natural stream corridor now exists. Rivers 
Unlimited, the Tinker's Creek Land Conservancy and a host of other organizations all testified in 
opposition to this hair-brained scheme, but Ohio EPA Director Don Schregardus decided that a 
parking lot for a strip mall was more important than the wishes of the overwhelming majority of 
people in the area or the health of the waterway.Theorganizations involved in the fight to stop the 
project are considering an appeal of the decision to the Environmental Board of Review.</p>
<p>The EPA has not resolved issues concerning degradation of water quality, value for enhancement of 
public interest, speculative engineering techniques and cost benefit analysis. This creek relocation 
project is strictly for financial gain. This project will place the entire Tinker's Creek corridor and the 
residents and businesses in and adjacent to the flood plain at risk.</p>
<p>For more information call Susan Ferritto at (216) 425-8793.</p>
<hr>
