<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML 3.0//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Products and technology</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#173973" VLINK="#777777" ALINK="#C8D838" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<map name="products">
<area shape="rect" coords="361,23, 449,53" href="/jobs/jobs.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="268,23, 362,54" href="/doing/doin.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="201,00, 268,67" href="prod.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="114,23, 201,54" href="/media/medi.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="34,23, 115,53" href="/general/gene.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="00,22, 34,54" href="/index.htm">
</map>
<IMG SRC="prod.gif" ALIGN=BOTTOM WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="68" BORDER="0" usemap="#products" border="0">
</center>
<!--header ends here-->

<h2>Products &amp; Technology</h2>
<IMG SRC="/general/people/pics/Normcar.gif" width="446" height="334 border="0"><p>
Norman R. Bodine, president and CEO of UT Automotive, drives the company's high-technology products into the future, in this composite photo. These <A HREF="products.htm"><b>products</b></A>, based on <A HREF="tech.htm"><b>technology</b></A> developed by the company's Wiring Systems, Input Controls, Motor Systems and Interiors business groups, help reduce cost, improve reliability and enhance vehicle performance for customers around the world.
