<!--header ends here-->
<H2>General Information</H2>

<table>
      <tr>
        <th valign="top" align="right">Overview: <td> UT Automotive develops, manufactures and markets a
        wide variety of systems and components for automobile and light truck
        original equipment manufacturers around the world. Electrical components
        and systems make up about 75% of UT Automotive's overall business and interior
        trim about 25%. The company's products are part of nearly every
        passenger vehicle built in North America and Europe. For more detail see our <A HREF="info/closer.htm"><b>Overview presentation</b></A> and a timeline of <A HREF="history/history.htm"><b>UT Automotive's History</b></A>.      <br>
      <tr>
        <th valign="top" align="right">Headquarters: <td>5200 Auto Club Drive,
        Dearborn, Mich., 48126<br> Telephone: (313) 593-9000
      <br>
      <tr>
        <th valign="top" align="right">European Headquarters: <td>72, Rue du Colonel de
        Rochebrune, F92380 Garches, France<br>Telephone: 33-1-4710-8070
      <br>
      <tr>
        <th valign="top" align="right">President: <td><A HREF="/media/releases/greer.htm"><b>C. Scott Greer</b></A> (Links to other <A HREF="people/key_execs.htm"><b>Key Executives</b></A>)
      <br>
      <tr>
        <th valign="top" align="right">Associates: <td>More than 40,000
        worldwide with <A HREF="locations/locations.htm"><B>locations</B></A> in 17 countries
      <br>
      <tr>
        <th valign="top" align="right">Revenues: <td>$3.1 billion in 1995<br>
        By customer type: 95% automotive; 5% non-automotive
    </table>
<p>
If you have other questions about our company please contact <A HREF="mailto:ckelly@uta.com">Chris Kelly</A>.<p>
If you have questions about this website, contact <A HREF="mailto:rkrawczyk@uta.com">Ralph Krawczyk</A> with design related questions, or <A HREF="mailto:njohnson@uta.com">Ned Johnson</A> with content related questions.



