<!--header ends here-->

<h2>General Manager - China Joint Venture</h2>

          [ <em>Opportunity #</em> <strong> 3072-96 </strong> ]
         
        </p>
      </div>
  
      <div align="center">
        <table align="center" border>
          <tr>
            <th colspan=4 valign=center>
            
              <h3 align="center">RESPONSIBILITIES</h3>
            </th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td colspan=4>
              <ol>
  <li> Direct and manage all plant operations relating to production, production
  control methods, accounting.</li>
  <li> Direct the identification and recruitment of key staff management, as well as
  the phase-in of all associated production associates and implementation of skill-based
  training programs.</li>
  <li> Establish and monitor overall plant performance criteria to ensure adherence to
  pre-established start-up, launch and delivery schedules, in accordance with specified
  quality standards.</li>
  <li> Ensure conformance to local laws in all aspects of the operations.</li>
  <li> Identify a high quality supplier base and create strong localized relationships as
  appropriate.</li>
  <li> Develop and control budgets and associated profit plans through the
  implementation of cost effective systems of control relating to capital, material,
  manpower, etc.</li>
  <li> Serve as community liaison with local dignitaries in promoting UTA's citizenship
  image, dealing effectively with political, cultural and ethical systems that may differ
  from Western standards.</li>
  <li> Establish strong customer relations with local OEM's and interface with senior
  local management.</li>
  
              </ol>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th colspan=4>
              <h3 align = "center">QUALIFICATIONS</h3>
            </th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
           
            <td colspan=4>
              <ul>
               <li> Prefer seasoned professional with 10+ years of plant operations
  experience in a high volume production environment, preferably with wiring systems
  background.</li>
  <li> Graduate or undergraduate degree required, preferably in engineering.</li>
  <li> Strong interpersonal skills a must.  Sense of protocol and diplomatic
  relations.</li>
  
              </ul>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
           
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th colspan=4 valign=center>
              <h3 align="center">ADDITIONAL INFORMATION</h3>
            </th>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td colspan=4 align="left">
  UT Automotive is seeking an individual to lead a forthcoming joint venture in
  Mainland China.  As General Manager, this position will direct the overall activities
  associated with the operation of a manufacturing facility dedicated to automotive
  wire harness production.
  
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
      </div>
  


