    <hr>

    <h3><a name="#overview">1. Overview</a></h3>

    <p>
    UT Automotive, based in Dearborn, Mich., designs, manufactures and
    markets a wide variety of systems and components for automobile and light
    truck original equipment manufacturers (OEMs).
    <P>
    Our products are part of nearly every passenger vehicle built in North
    America and Europe. We have been able to form many long-term partnerships
    within the automotive industry by helping OEMs stay competitive in the
    global marketplace, where we excel.
    <P>
    UT Automotive is able to stand out from other automotive suppliers because we are able
    to integrate so many resources to find solutions for our customers. Our
    areas of expertise include:
    <ul>
      <li>Electrical distribution, electronic and electromechanical systems and
      components, including wire assemblies, control modules, switches,
      fractional horsepower DC motors, actuators, relays, terminals and
      connectors, junction boxes and power network boxes.
      <li>Interior and exterior trim, including modular headliners, door panels,
      steering wheels, painted and decorated trim components, exterior mirrors,
      instrument panels, door and sidewall trim, sealants and insulator panels.
    </Ul>
    <P>
    Electrical components and systems make up about 75 percent of UT Automotive's overall
    business and interior trim about 25 percent. About 95 percent of UT Automotive's
    business is automotive related. The company has annual sales of $3 billion.
    <P>
    UT Automotive is a unit of <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corp.
    (UTC)</a>, based in Hartford, Conn., which provides a broad range of high-
    technology products and support services to the aerospace, building systems
    and automotive industries. Among UTC's units are Pratt & Whitney jet
    engines, Sikorsky helicopters,
    <a href="http://www.hamilton-standard.com/">Hamilton Standard</a> aerospace
    controls, <a href="http://www.otis.utc.com/">Otis elevators</a> and
    Carrier heating and air conditioning systems. Transferring technology from
    these divisions provides UT Automotive with another advantage over other automotive
    suppliers.
    <P>
    In addition, we're working with the
    <a href="http://www.utrc.utc.com/">United Technologies Research Center</a>
    and many leading universities to develop new solutions for tomorrow's
    vehicles.
    <P>
    Few automotive suppliers can match our capabilities, our worldwide presence,
    or our history of integrating these resources to develop quality-driven,
    value-added solutions for our customers.
    <P>
    This information package is designed to showcase our many products and
    capabilities, and how a partnership with UT Automotive can play a critical role in
    your company's success.



