<h5>Contact: Peter Murphy 
<a href="mailto:murphyp@utc.com">(murphyp@utc.com</a>) (860) 728-7977
<BR>
Contact: Lin Cummins (<a href="mailto:lcummins@uta.com">lcummins@uta.com</a>) (313) 593-9475<BR>
</h5>

<h3>C. Scott Greer Named President of UT Automotive; Bodine Appointed UTC Senior Vice President</h3>

<p>




	HARTFORD, Conn., January 30, 1997 --  C. Scott Greer, 46, has been appointed president of UT Automotive, a subsidiary of United Technologies Corporation, the company announced today.<p>

	He succeeds Norman Bodine, who has been named a senior vice president of UTC.  Greer and Bodine will report to UTC's President and Chief Executive Officer George David.<p>

	Greer Joins UTC from Echlin, Inc. where he was president, chief operating officer and a member of the company's board of directors.  Echlin, Inc. is a multi-product supplier to the original equipment manufacturer and aftermarket segments of the automotive industry.<p>

	UTC President and Chief Executive George David said,
"Scott brings to our automotive company nearly two decades of skill and experience, which has made Echlin number one among its peer companies."<p>
	Greer began his career with Echlin in 1980 as international group controller.  In 1986 he was named group vice president, international and served in that position until he was named Echlin's president and a member of its board of directors in 1990.  Greer was named the company's chief operating officer in 1994.<p>

	He is a graduate of St. Olaf College and holds a B.B.A. and an M.S. from the University of Wisconsin, and is a licensed CPA.<p>
	UT Automotive is a $3.1 billion tier-one supplier of electrical, electronic and interior trim systems and components to car and light truck manufacturers.  It is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based United Technologies Corporation, which provides a broad range of high-technology products and services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.



