<!--header ends here--><H2>Forward</H2>
<P>
The Partners in Excellence Supplier Management Policy was developed
through the cooperative efforts of all UT Automotive's
business units, in order to standardize and communicate the methods
by which UT Automotive manages its supply base.  The ultimate responsibility
of the Supplier Management Policy rests with UT Automotive's
Purchasing Council and is administered through corporate Quality
and Supplier Development.  Management reviews are conducted periodically
to ensure the effectiveness of the program.e program.<BR>

<P>
UT Automotive has implemented its supply management policy in the spirit
of continuous improvement, and is confident that the requirements
set forth will enhance quality systems, improve process efficiencies,
and ultimately reduce total costs for the design and manufacture
of our automotive products.  UT Automotive encourages suppliers to strive
for advancements in technology, quality, and service beyond the
requirements set forth in this document.<BR>

<P>
The concepts of the Partners in Excellence Supplier Management
Policy were developed around UT Automotive's
Quality Policy, which has been endorsed by UT Automotive's
president and the senior executive of each UT Automotive business unit.
 The policy is as follows:<BR>


<UL>
<LI><I>Make our customer our focus.  Provide continuous improvement of the quality   of
      products and services to our customer.</I><BR>

<LI><I>Design and produce a product that fulfills the needs of our customer.</I><BR>

<LI><I>Eliminate waste and produce our product at the lowest cost.</I><BR>

<LI><I> Every person must fully understand their role on the team in producing a  quality
       product.</I><BR>
</UL>

<P>
The Partners in Excellence Supplier Management Policy, with its
associated documents (see Appendix D), establishes the minimum
requirements for UT Automotive's
supplier quality systems.  The Quality System Requirements QS-9000,
and all documents referenced within it, as well as ISO 9001 and
various customer requirements, form a part of this Partners in
Excellence policy.  This manual is considered incomplete without
the associated documents.<BR>

<P>
The topics covered in this policy establish requirements that
are specific to UT Automotive, and may not be currently covered in QS-9000,
or further emphasize or clarify an existing requirement.  References
to QS-9000 are made throughout this policy =  "Apply
QS-9000 ..." These references are offered to assist in the application of the policy
and are not meant to be exclusive of any part of QS-9000.  There
may be procedures issued from individual UT Automotive facilities, to accompany
this policy in directing the interface between a supplier and
a UT Automotive manufacturing facility.  UT Automotive plant procedures are in accordance
with the requirements of QS-9000, and in line with the concepts
of this policy.<BR>
<P>

<U><B>Revisions<BR>
</B></U>
<P>
This is the October, 1995 edition of the Partners in Excellence
Supplier Management Policy.  All previous editions, including
the system, commercial and technology surveys, are obsolete. 
Updates to this policy, including associated appendices, will
be made and reviewed by management periodically.  Direct comments,
suggestions and requests for additional copies to:<BR>

<P>
<CENTER>
UT Automotive
<BR>
Quality &amp; Supplier Development
<BR>
5200 Auto Club Drive
<BR>
Dearborn, MI 48126
<BR>
Phone (313) 593-9605
<BR>
Fax (313) 240-3606<BR>
</CENTER>
<P>
<U><B>Associated Documents<BR>
</B></U>
<P>
<B>Quality System Requirements QS-9000, and all documents required
by QS-9000, form a part of this policy, and are referenced where
applicable.</B>  Suppliers shall comply to the latest version of these
documents.  These requirements reflects UT Automotive's
minimum expectation for a UT Automotive supplier's
quality system.  Suppliers may substitute their own forms and/or
format, if content requirements are met.<BR>
<br>
