<H2>General Supplier Quality Policy</H2><p>
<b>1.1.1   Mission Statement </b><P>
UT Automotive is committed to the attainment of the highest standards of quality in all purchased products and services.  It is UT Automotive policy to purchase all equipment, supplies and services on the basis of merit.  We emphasize fair competition without discrimination or misrepresentation, in a manner consistent with long term business relationships.<br><p>
<b> 1.1.2  Purpose </b><p>
UT Automotive's Partners in Excellence are intended to communicate the initial and on-going requirements for supplier quality systems and performance.  UT Automotive relies on suppliers to continuously improve performance, engage in joint sharing of information, and develop productive, long-term relationships with UT Automotive.  The importance of the Partners in Excellence program is emphasized by its inclusion as a requirement within the UT Automotive purchase order terms and conditions.<br><p>
<b> 1.1.3  Scope</b><p>
This policy applies to suppliers of products, materials and services who are, or propose to be, in business with UT Automotive.  However, instances where a UT Automotive customer has an approved subcontractor list, UT Automotive shall purchase relevant materials from subcontractors on the list.<br><p>
<b> 1.1.4  Responsibility</b><p>
The Partners in Excellence supplier quality system requirements incorporate the global requirements of the QS-9000.  UT Automotive encourages and recognizes suppliers who have attained ISO 9001, 9002, 9003 registration, as well as suppliers who have met the requirements of QS-9000 and all standards specified within.

<p>
