<H2>Supplier Business Profile</H2>
<BR>
</U></B></CENTER>
<P>
<B>3.1.1  Purpose<BR>
</B>
<P>
The Supplier Business Profile provides relevant business information
to UT Automotive Purchasing, with regard to contract awards and maintenance.
<BR>

<P>
<B>3.1.2 Scope<BR>
</B>
<P>
Supplier Business Profile information is maintained on production,
materials and service suppliers, in a centralized database which
is shared across UT Automotive business units.<BR>

<P>
<B>3.1.3 Procedure<BR>
</B>
<P>
The Supplier Business Profile (Appendix E) is to be completed
and delivered to UT Automotive Purchasing, at a minimum, during the program
Request for Quote phase.  Additionally, the Supplier Business
Profile should be completed and delivered to UT Automotive Purchasing any
time the suppliers'
address, key contacts, UT Automotive manufacturing plants supplied, or minority
business enterprise information changes.  All data fields are
to be completed, unless they are not applicable; in such a case,
"N/A" should be indicated.  Supplier Business Profiles allow purchasing
representatives to investigate the centralized database for potential
sources of new contacts.<BR>

<P>
<B>3.1.4 Minority Business Enterprise Certification<BR>
</B>
<P>
It is the policy of UT Automotive that minority business concerns shall
have equal opportunity to complete for the company's
products and service needs on a competitive quoting basis.  Purchases
of goods and services shall be made from such concerns to the
fullest extent possible, consistent with this policy and prudent
business practice.<BR>

<P>
A minority owned business is one in which at least 51% of the
business is owned and controlled by the minority principal.  The
minority principal shall control the daily business operations
and management decisions.  Each Minority Business Enterprise shall,
on an annual basis, submit a copy of their minority certification
issued by a registered certifying board, along with their completed
Supplier Business Profile to the following UT Automotive office:<BR>

<P>
<CENTER>
UT Automotive
<BR>
Supplier Development Manager
<BR>
5200 Auto Club Drive
<BR>
Dearborn, MI 48126<BR>
</CENTER>

<P>

In concert with U.S. government guidelines, the following definitions
have been adopted for minority group members.<BR>

<UL>
<LI><B>African American</B><br>
A U.S. citizen having origins in any of the black racial groups of Africa.<BR>
<P>
<LI> <B>Hispanic American</B><br>
A. U.S. citizen of true-born Hispanic heritage (true-born meaning
"authentically" or "genuinely," 
as per Webster) from any of the Spanish-speaking areas of Latin
America or  the following regions: Mexico, Puerto Rico, Cuba,
Central America, South America, the  Caribbean basin, and the
Iberian Peninsula.<BR>
<P>
<LI> <B>Native American</B><br>
A U.S. citizen who is an American Indian, Eskimo, Aleut or native
Hawaiian, and  regarded  as such by the community of which the
person claims to be a part.  Native Americans must  be documented
members of a North American tribe, band or otherwise group of
native people  who are indigenous to the continental United States
and proof can be provided through a  Native American Blood Degree
Certificate (i.e., tribal registry letter, tribal roll register
 number).<BR>
<P>
<LI> <B>Asian-Pacific American</B><br>
A U.S. citizen whose origins are from Japan, China, Taiwan, Korea,
Vietnam, Laos,  Cambodia, the Philippines, Samoa, Guam, the U.S.
Trust Territories of the Pacific or the  Northern Marianas, Indonesia,
Micronesia, or Polynesia.<BR>
<P>
<LI> <B>Asian-Indian American</B><br>
A U.S. citizen whose origins are in India, Pakistan, or Bangladesh.
<BR>
</UL>
<P>
<B>3.1.5 Key Supplier Contacts<BR>
</B>
<P>
UT Automotive Purchasing and Quality Assurance shall be notified in writing
with the names of key contacts for program, product, and/or customer
service concerns, as well as inquiries regarding continuous improvement
activities.<BR>
<br>
<br>
