<H2>Capital Equipment</H2>
<P>
<B>8.1.1     Purpose</B>
<P>
To define capital equipment and outline UT Automotives Terms and Conditions (See Appendix C) in the purchase of capital equipment.
<P>
<B>8.1.2     Scope</B>
<P>
Applicable to all suppliers and/or potential suppliers of tooling and/or capital equipment to UT Automotive.
<P>
<B>8.1.3     Definition</B>
<P>
Capital equipment is classified to be the fixed assets or long-lived assets of the company that are not intended for resale in day-to-day business activities.  Capital equipment includes industrial and office machinery and tools, transportation equipment, furniture and fixtures, and others.  Specifications of all capital equipment must be defined and mutually understood prior to the award of the contract.  Closure of the contract constitutes an acceptance that the equipment meets or exceeds specifications.  Acceptance may be at the facility of either the supplier or UT Automotive, and should be defined at the award of a contract.
<p>
