<H2>Early Product Development Launch</H2>
<P>
<B>9.1.1     Purpose</B>
<P>
To integrate supplier involvement into the business decision process throughout the entire product development launch for new, modified carryover, or carryover programs.
<P>
<B>9.1.2     Scope</B>
<P>
In the Product Development Launch process, there are going to be certain suppliers that will be incorporated into the process.  These suppliers can fall into one of several categories as follows:
<OL>
<LI>Selected to support the strategic objective of the business unit by creating, through the relationship, competitive advantages in time, cost, delivery or quality.
<LI>To create or gain access to critical product and/or process technology.
<LI>Support areas of non core-competency.
<LI>UT Automotive is required to deal with them such as customer source or proprietary products or processes.
</OL>
<B>9.1.3     General</B>
<P>
Selected suppliers will be expected to participate at various times throughout the typical phases of UT Automotive product and process design development, manufacturing feasibility review, production launch and post launch performance.  Suppliers should expect to provide cost saving suggestions, target cost estimates, manufacturing feasibility, timing and capacity to support alternate and preferred design concepts.
<P>
During the process design development phase, a full level production proveout may be required that will satisfy the intent and be representative of production capacity.  Occasions may arise which require suppliers to be co-located within UT Automotive during the pre launch and UT Automotive launch phase.<p>
