<H2>Production Scheduling and Releases</H2><P>
<B>13.1.1     Purpose</B><P>
To insure that UT Automotive suppliers plan production and/or delivery in accordance with the requirements of the releasing UT Automotive facility.
<P>
<B>13.1.2     Scope</B><P>
UT Automotive suppliers of production parts and materials are directed by release schedules or purchase orders, as issued by the releasing UT Automotive plant or division after acceptance of the Product Sample Warrant (PSW).
<P>
<B>13.1.3    Responsibility </B><P>
It is the responsibility of the supplier to insure that order quantities stated on the purchase order are manufacturable by the supplier, and that release schedules are obtained from the releasing UT Automotive facility in a manner which allows adequate time for fulfillment of the order.  Suppliers shall notify the releasing UT Automotive plant immediately if the fulfillment of a released order is threatened.
<P>
<B>13.1.4     Release Notification</B><P>
The release schedule frequency and firm order quantities for production and raw material for which UT Automotive will be liable in the event of cancellation, shall be established by the terms of the purchase order.
<P>
It is UT Automotives intention to minimize schedule changes in order to maximize productivity.  However, it is essential that our suppliers understand that the dynamic automobile market demands flexible schedules and reduced leadtimes.  Only with the full cooperation of our supplier base can UT Automotive successfully compete in the marketplace, and responsively satisfy our customers needs.
<P>
<B>13.1.5     Advanced Shipping Notification</B><P>
Suppliers shall notify UT Automotive within a timeframe prior to the shipment of product from the suppliers facility, as designated by the specific business unit, using the notification method identified by the specific business unit.
<P>
<B>13.1.6     Electronic Data Interchange Considerations</B><P>
It is strongly suggested that suppliers employ Electronic Data Interchange (EDI) methods for the communication of releases and accounts receivable information.  Suppliers should contact their UT Automotive purchasing representative to inquire about EDI communication with UT Automotive.<p>
<CENTER>Go to the <a href="sec141.htm">Next Section - Section 14.1</a></CENTER>

