<H2>Handling, Storage, Packaging, Preservation and Delivery</H2><P>
<B>14.1.1     Purpose</B><P>
To provide guidelines for all suppliers to assure proper packaging and shipping practices to protect the quality of deliverable products and to prevent their damage or deterioration.
<P>
<B>14.1.2     Scope</B><P>
This section applies to all products destined for delivery to UT Automotive facilities.
<P>
<B>14.1.3     Responsibility</B><P>
It is the suppliers responsibility to document and maintain a procedure to ensure that packaging and material identification is sufficient to protect product quality and integrity during shipment.  Costs relate to handling, storage, packaging, preservation and delivery shall be included in the original quotation.  Apply QS-9000, Elements 4.6.1 and 4.15.4.
<P>
<B>14.1.4    Packaging</B><P>
Packaging should be in compliance with the UT Automotive receiving facilitys material handling and bar code requirements, and QS-9000.  Contact UT Automotive Purchasing to arrange specific packaging procedures.
<P>
Where applicable, suppliers should use recyclable packaging, point of use package designs (which reduce handling), and/or packaging which otherwise aids in the automation of production.  Suppliers using reusable containers shall document cleaning and handling procedures.  Hand moveable containers should not exceed 45 pounds each.
<P>
<B>14.1.5     Labeling</B><P>
Each container shall have sufficient labeling to insure that part number, quantity, date of manufacturing and revision letter is clearly identified.  This labeling shall be bar code readable in accordance with national standards, and as specified by UT Automotive Purchasing.
<P>
<B>14.1.6    Delivery</B><P>
Suppliers shall establish a goal of 100% on-time deliveries, in the required order quantities, as defined in the UT Automotive purchase order.  UT Automotive typically utilizes third party logistics management to minimize transport costs.  Contact UT Automotive Purchasing for specific transportation procedures.  Apply QS-9000, Elements 4.2.6 (100% on-time delivery) and 4.15.6.
<P>
<B>14.1.7     Restricted Substances </B><P>
Suppliers shall have a process to assure that governmental and safety constraints on restricted, toxic and hazardous substances are complied with relative to purchased products and the manufacturing process.  Apply QS-9000, Element 4.6.3.<p>
<CENTER>
