<H2>Master Services Ordering Agreement</H2><P>
<B>Appendix B<BR>
1/94</B>
<P>
<CENTER><B>UT AUTOMOTIVE</B>
<P>
</CENTER>
<B>THIS AGREEMENT</B>, entered into on the  _____ day of _______________, 199___, by and between <B>United Technologies Automotive, Inc.</B>, a corporation organized and existing under the laws of the State of Delaware, with an office and place of business at 5200 Auto Club Drive, Dearborn, Michigan 48126 (hereinafter referred to as UT Automotive), and _________________________, a corporation organized and existing under the laws of the State of _______________, with an office and place of business at ________________________________________________________________ (hereinafter referred to as Contractor).
<P>
WHEREAS, UT Automotive wishes to avail itself of the services of the Contractor for ________________________________________________________;
<P>
WHEREAS, the Contractor wishes to supply its services to UT Automotive;
<P>
NOW, THEREFORE, it is hereby mutually covenanted and agreed that this Master Services Ordering Agreement Nondisclosure Agreement is mad upon the foregoing and upon the following agreements, conditions, covenants and terms:
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 1 - STATEMENT OF SERVICES</B></CENTER>
<P>
(a)  During the term of this Agreement and during all renewal periods of this Agreement, Contractor agrees to furnish to UT Automotive its services in the capacity of an independent contractor, as more fully described in Attachment A - Work Statement, attached hereto and, by this reference, made a part hereof.  All arrangements for services shall be made only by _____________________ on behalf of UT Automotive and under Purchase Orders duly executed on behalf of UT Automotive by its authorized representative.  All services shall be performed in accordance with the terms and conditions of this Master Agreement.  Although UT Automotive hereby requests that the Contractor be available to perform services for a minimum of ____ days and a maximum of ____ days per month during the term of this Agreement, it is understood and agreed that UT Automotive is not obligated in any way to request the services of the Contractor for any stipulated period of time or to use the Contractors services solely and exclusively.
<P>
(b)  UT Automotive may direct all questions or comments regarding services provided to UT Automotive directly to Contractor.  Contractor shall be subject to the general supervision of UT Automotives supervisors as to the work to be carried out hereunder and shall carry out such work in conformity with UT Automotives directions and procedures.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 2  -  COMPENSATION</B></CENTER>
<P>
(a)  In consideration of the services performed by the Contractor hereunder, UT Automotive agrees to pay Contractor the sum of  $_________.  This compensation will be guaranteed firm by the Contractor for the duration of this Master Agreement, unless an adjustment is mutually agreed upon by both parties.
<P>
(b)  Contractor shall submit invoices to UT Automotive periodically in a form acceptable to UT Automotive.  Each invoice shall fairly and accurately describe in sufficient detail the actual services performed and the period of performance for services rendered under this Agreement.  UT Automotives supervisors shall approve all invoices submitted by Contractor.
<P>
(c)  UT Automotive may require Contractor to furnish such additional written reports concerning the Contractors activities incident to this Agreement as UT Automotive may reasonably require to review the Contractors performance or invoices.
<P>
(d)  UT Automotive agrees to pay Contractors invoiced charges net forty-five (45) days after receipt and approval of invoice.
<P>
(e)  Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, UT Automotive shall be under no obligation to make any payment to the Contractor in excess of the total amount of $____________ for any and all services performed, under the terms of this Agreement.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 3 - TERM</B></CENTER><P>
The term of this Agreement shall commence on the _____ day of __________, 19____ and shall continue in effect unless terminated in accordance with the provisions of this Master Agreement.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 4 - NOTICE</B></CENTER>
<P>
The Contractors invoice and other notices shall be mailed to the following address:
<P>
UT Automotive<BR>
_______________________________<BR>
_______________________________<BR>
_______________________________<BR>
Attn: ___________________________<BR>
<P>
UT Automotives payment and other notices shall be mailed to the following address:
_______________________________<BR>
_______________________________<BR>
_______________________________<BR>
Attn: ___________________________<BR>
<P>
All notices required or permitted hereunder shall be in writing and shall be deemed to be properly given when personally delivered to the contractor or to any officer or designated representative of UT Automotive entitled to receive the notice or, three (3) days after mailing when sent by certified or registered first class mail, postage prepaid, properly addressed to the party entitled to receive such notice at the address set forth above.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 5 - TERMINATION</B></CENTER>
<P>
(a)  Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, UT Automotive may at any time for its convenience and at its option, after giving Contractor a one (1) day written notice, terminate this Agreement and the performance of the services called for herein, in which event UT Automotive agrees to pay Contractor a sum for such pro rata portion of the services as Contractor shall have performed up to the time of such termination, as determined in accordance with Article 3 herein.  Except for payment of such services, UT Automotive shall have no further liability of obligation to the Contractor.
<P>
(b)  The Contractor recognizes that performance of the work hereunder must be satisfactory to UT Automotive in order for UT Automotive to meet its obligations to its customer(s).  Accordingly, in the event that any of the Contractors work is unsatisfactory, Contractor agrees, upon receipt of notice to that effect from UT Automotive, to make such work satisfactory to UT Automotive at its own expense.  If Contractor does not fulfill his obligations under this provision within a reasonable time after receipt of notice from UT Automotive of its dissatisfaction with Contractors performance, this Agreement shall terminate and UT Automotive shall have no further obligations under it, and may consider Contractor in breach of this Agreement.
(c)  Any termination notice for unsatisfactory work pursuant to this Article shall be made effective twenty-four (24) hours after issuance.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 6 - ENTIRE CONTRACT</B></CENTER>
<P>
This Agreement and the Attachments hereto constitute the entire agreement between the parties.  No amendments or changes shall be binding upon the parties unless in writing and signed by both parties.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 7 - INTERPRETATION AND CONSTRUCTION</B></CENTER>
<P>
The construction of this Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of Michigan.  The title designations of the numbered Articles herein are for convenience of reference only and shall not affect the interpretation or construction hereof.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 8 - INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR RELATIONSHIP</B></CENTER>
<P>
The relationship of the Contractor to UT Automotive is that of an independent contractor and nothing herein shall be construed as creating any other relationship.  The Contractor agrees to cooperate fully with, and defer to, UT Automotive with respect to the details of the services performed hereunder, the hours during which such services are to be provided, and the place or places where such services are to be furnished, in order that such details, hours and services shall be consistent with the proper accomplishment of such services ant so that such services shall be performed in a manner calculated to attain the most satisfactory results for UT Automotive.  The Contractor shall be obligated to pay any and all applicable local, state and federal taxes.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 9 - TITLE TO MATERIALS AND EQUIPMENT</B>
</CENTER><P>
All materials and equipment furnished by UT Automotive and all materials and equipment the cost of which shall be reimbursed to the Contractor by UT Automotive hereunder are to be and remain the sole property of UT Automotive and are to be returned to UT Automotive within thirty (30) DAYS AFTER THE EXPIRATION OR EARLIER TERMINATION OF THIS Master Agreement.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 10 - INVENTIONS AND PROPRIETARY RIGHTS</B></CENTER>
<P>
The Contractor agrees to disclose promptly to UT Automotive all inventions, discoveries, improvements, mask works, manuals, computer programs or software and copyrights made or perfected in the performance of, or arising out of, the services furnished to UT Automotive by him or by others associated with him in the conduct of the services furnished hereunder.  All such inventions, discoveries, improvements, mask works, computer programs or software, copyrights and patents therefor shall become the exclusive property of UT Automotive.  The Contractor hereby undertakes and agrees to execute such assignments and other papers which, in the opinion of UT Automotive, are necessary at any time to permit the filing and prosecution of any applications for patents covering the inventions, discoveries or improvements or are otherwise required for compliance with the provisions of this paragraph.  In the event that others are, or may hereafter become, associated with the Contractor or employed by him in connection with the work called for by this Agreement, the Contractor agrees to cause all such individuals who perform work for use by UT Automotive UNDER THIS Agreement to execute an agreement of the form attached hereto entitled UT Automotive - Contractors Intellectual Property Agreement.  Contractor agrees not to assert any rights or take any action contrary to the letter or the spirit of this Master Agreement and, to the extent necessary, waives any preexisting conflicting obligations of such personnel to the Contractor.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 11 - DISCLOSURES AND CONFLICTS OF INTEREST</B></CENTER>
<P>
(a)  The Contractor agrees that during the term of this Master Agreement, including any renewal thereof, and for a period of five (5) years thereafter, the services furnished hereunder and the results thereof, together with all information disclosed in any manner by UT Automotive to the Contractor, shall be considered as confidential proprietary to UT Automotive and that neither the Contractor nor any others associated with or used by Contractor in the conduct or development of the services furnished hereunder shall without the prior written consent of UT Automotive (i) publish, use of otherwise divulge any information relating to such services or the results thereof regardless of whether such information has been furnished to the Contractor by UT Automotive or is original with Contractor, or (ii) discuss the nature of its activities in connection with UT Automotive with anyone except authorized representatives of UT Automotive.
<P>
(b)  The Contractor warrants and represents that no trade secrets or other confidential information of any other person, firm, corporation or government will be wrongfully disclosed by it to UT Automotive in connection with any of the services called for hereunder and that, unless otherwise specifically identified in writing at the time of disclosure, all information disclosed by the Contractor to UT Automotive may be used of disclosed by UT Automotive without restriction.  The Contractor further warrants and represents that none of the provisions of this Master Agreement, nor the services which will be performed by the contractor hereunder, contravenes or is in conflict with any agreement of the Contractor with, or obligation to, any other person, form, corporation or government, including without limiting the generality of the foregoing, employment agreements, consulting agreements, disclosure agreements or agreements for assignment of inventions.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 12 - ASSIGNMENT AND DELEGATION</B></CENTER>
<P>
Neither this Master Agreement nor any right, interest or duty hereunder shall be assignable or delegable by either party unless such assignment or delegation is mutually agreed to in writing by the parties hereto; provided, however, that UT Automotive may assign this Master Agreement to any parent, subsidiary, affiliate or any corporation with which UT Automotive may merge or consolidate or to which UT Automotive may assign substantially all of its assets or that portion of its business to which this Master Agreement pertains without obtaining the agreement of the Contractor.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 13 - FAILURE</B></CENTER>
<P>
Neither the Contractor nor UT Automotive shall be charged with any liability for failure or delay in performance of services under this Master Agreement when such failure or delay is due to any cause beyond the control and without the fault or negligence of either party, provided that notice shall be given to the other party promptly and in writing when  it appears that such cause will delay performance under this Master Agreement.  If any such failure or delay shall threaten to impair UT Automotives ability to meet its obligations, UT Automotive shall have the right, at its option and without being under any liability to the Contractor, to cancel the affected portion or portions of this Master Agreement by written notice to the Contractor.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 14 - UT AUTOMOTIVE EXAMINATION</B></CENTER>
<P>
The Contractor shall permit UT Automotive to examine its books, records, documents and other evidence and accounting procedures and practices, sufficient to reflect properly all direct and indirect costs of whatever nature claimed to have been incurred for performance of this Agreement.  Such right of examination shall include inspection at all reasonable times during the course of normal business hours.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 15 - WARRANTY</B></CENTER>
<P>
The Contractor warrants to UT Automotive that (i) any work performed from time to time under this Master Agreement will be performed in accordance with the direction and specifications received from UT Automotive employees; (ii) the work and goods will be suitable for the purposes intended, whether express or reasonably implied.
<P>
(a)  The Contractor agrees to secure and protect itself, and shall secure and indemnify UT Automotive and UT Automotives directors, officers and employees from any liability, claim of liability, expense, causes of action, loss or damage whatsoever for any injury, including death, to himself or any person or property in the performance of this Agreement, unless such injury is caused by the sole negligence of UT Automotive, it being the intent of this Agreement to protect and indemnify UT Automotive from any and all losses arising out of or in connection with the services performed under this Agreement, unless such loss is caused by the sole negligence of UT Automotive.
<P>
(b) The Contractor and any subcontractor agrees that in the performance of the services hereunder (i) it will comply with all applicable fire safety requirements of the National Fire Protection Association, (ii) it will adhere to all federal, state and local laws pertaining to fire protection, and (iii) it will abide and be governed by the rules and regulations pertaining to fire and plant protection prescribed by UT Automotive.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 17 - EQUAL OPPORTUNITY</B></CENTER>
<P>
The contractor agrees to abide by all federal, state and local laws regarding discrimination because of race, religion, sex, creed, color, national origin, marital status, handicap or veteran status.
<P>
<CENTER><B>ARTICLE 18 - GOVERNING TERMS</B></CENTER>
<P>
In the event that UT Automotive issues a purchase order, or release, covering the services to be provided pursuant hereto, such purchase order shall be incorporated herein by this reference.  In the event of a conflict between the terms and conditions appearing on the face or reverse sides of such purchase order and this Agreement, the latter shall supersede and control.
<P>
In the event that the Contractor issues a purchase order acknowledgment or other documentation regarding the services to be provided pursuant hereto, and in the event that such purchase order acknowledgment or documentation contains terms and conditions, such terms and conditions shall be superseded in their entirety by this Agreement.
<P>
<B>IN WITNESS WHEREOF</B>, each of the parties has caused its duly authorized representative to execute this Master Agreement on this _____ day of ____________________, 199__.
<P>
<B>UT Automotive</B>
