<center><B>Appendix D</B></CENTER>
<P>
The following distributed documents form a part of the Partners in Excellence UT Automotive Supplier management policy.  Supplier practice shall be consistent with the applicable portions of these documents.
<UL>
<LI>QS-9000 - Quality System Requirements

<LI>QSA - Quality System Assessment

<LI>PPAP - Production Part Approval Process

<LI>APQP & Control Plan - Advanced Product Quality Planning & Control Plan

<LI>PFME - Potential Failure Mode & Effects

<LI>FMEA - Failure Mode & Effects Analysis

<LI>MSA - Measurement Systems Analysis

<LI>FSPC - Fundamentals of Statistical Process Control
</UL>
The above documents have been published and are copyright protected, through a cooperative effort between General Motors, Ford and Chrysler, as part of an effort to aid in the standardization of supplier quality system verification.
<P>
UT Automotive suppliers are expected to maintain the latest version of each of the above documents as part of their quality system.  The documents may be purchased from Automotive Industry Action Group for North America and the Pacific Rim and Carwin Continuous Ltd. in Europe, at the following addresses:
