<HEAD>
<TITLE>UT Automotive Products: Junction Boxes<</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#173973" VLINK="#777777" ALINK="#C8D838" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<map name="products">
<area shape="rect" coords="361,23, 449,53" href="/jobs/jobs.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="268,23, 362,54" href="/doing/doin.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="201,00, 268,67" href="/protech/prod.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="114,23, 201,54" href="/media/medi.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="34,23, 115,53" href="/general/gene.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="00,22, 34,54" href="/index.htm">
</map>

<IMG SRC="../PROD.GIF" ALIGN=BOTTOM WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="68" BORDER="0" usemap="#products" border="0">
</center>
<!--header ends here-->

<h2>Junction Boxes</h2>


<p>
UT Automotive manufactures junction boxes using stamped metal fret and/or printed circuit board
technologies.
<p>
Printed circuit board technologies include hard, flexible and combination boards with flexible
circuits.
<p>
UT Automotive has product design, engineering and manufacturing facilities for junction boxes in the United
States and Spain. In developing new junction boxes, UT Automotive uses advanced quality planning tools
such as quality function deployment, design failure mode effects analysis, design verification
planning and report, and process failure mode effects analysis.
<p>
Such tools help UT Automotive define customer requirements and develop plans to meet those requirements.
UT Automotive also conducts continuous benchmarking of competitive products to ensure that any new
product we develop utilizes best-in-class design practices.
<p>
Other tools used in the development of junction boxes include:
<ul><li><strong>3-D computer aided design</strong> - This provides our designers with the
ability to examine the part more completely in the areas of form, fit and function.
<li><strong>Finite element analysis</strong> - This ensures that the mechanical latches and
mounting features will perform as required for the life of the product, and provides a tool to
evaluate the thermal electrical performance of the circuit inside the junction box.
<li><strong>Mold fill analysis</strong> - This allows UT Automotive to test mold design and material
fill processes to ensure high product quality and performance.
</Ul>
<p>
UT Automotive's product development laboratories verify performance of our junction box designs, provide
state-of-the-art equipment for testing junction boxes for complex environmental exposure,
thermograph mapping of circuits to determine hot spots, and computerize high pot testing across
circuits to guarantee isolation of circuits.
<p>
UT Automotive uses state-of-the-art, automated manufacturing processes to ensure consistent high quality.
For example, stamped metal frets are brought into assembly with plastic insulators using precise
pick-and-place machines. Robotics systems are used to load components onto printed circuit
boards and to install fuses and relays to the boxes. Advanced color recognition systems are used in
the process to ensure that parts/components are in their correct location.
<p>
Some of our advanced research in junction box technology has helped in the development of
intelligent boxes, which combine circuit protection, low current switching, multiplexing and
integration with vehicle functions.

