<IMG SRC="../PROD.GIF" ALIGN=BOTTOM WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="68" BORDER="0" usemap="#products" border="0">
</center>
<!--header ends here-->

<h2>Modular Power Network Boxes</h2>

Unlike today's other modular components, UT Automotive's modular power distribution
systems offer a choice: pieced-together modules and mounting brackets that form
a fuse and/or relay center; or modules assembled in a frame to construct a
power distribution center.
<p>
UT Automotive modular components improve flexibility when packaged for circuit protection
and low current switching, and also provide electrical system designers a
product that is flexible enough to meet the power distribution needs of
different car lines.
<p>
The products are available today and can be used immediately to solve your
application needs.
<p>
UT Automotive modular power distribution systems:
<ul>
<li>Can be used with a power distribution center frame to create a large
variety of fuse panels or power network boxes.
<li>Can be built into arrays to form a custom configuration of fuses and relays.
<li>Can be used with an assortment of snap-on mounting brackets.
<li>Can be located almost anywhere in a vehicle.
<li>Accept standard autofuse, minifuse, maxifuse, ISO relays and half-ISO
relays.
<li>Offer increased packaging flexibility.
<li>Are pre-assembled according to customer specifications.
</Ul>

