<!--header ends here-->

<h2>Connection Systems</h2>

<IMG SRC="images/consys.gif" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH="334" HEIGHT="254">

<p>
UT Automotive is a full-service supplier of connection systems, including connectors,
terminals, junction boxes, power distribution boxes, fuse panels, troughs,
shields and brackets. We also provide turn-key design, development,
manufacturing and testing capabilities.
<P>
Many UT Automotive facilities are automated with state-of-the-art equipment. We maintain
our own plastic injection molding facility, a fully integrated mold and die
development center and two technology centers (in Dearborn, Mich., and Fort
Wayne, Ind.).
<P>
Our testing facilities provide a full complement of equipment to test systems
and components in a wide range of automotive environments - physical,
electrical, chemical and noise/vibration. We also have an extensive materials
laboratory, supported by <a href="http://www.utrc.utc.com/">United Technologies
Research Center's</a> global material data base, to optimize material selection
and develop new materials.
<P>
UT Automotive is the only known supplier with both metal fret and printed circuit board
capabilities, and we are exploring hybrid designs to further improve their
capabilities. Our advancements in fiber-optic and multiplex connectors have
made us a leader in connections systems technology.
<P>
All of these capabilities provide UT Automotive with the ability to convert challenging
design requirements into high quality products for our customers.


