<h2>Instrument Panels and Consoles</h2>

<IMG SRC="images/panel.gif" ALIGN=TEXTTOP WIDTH="266" HEIGHT="337">
<p>
UT Automotive designs and manufactures a wide variety of padded trim products, including:
<ul>
<li>Full instrument panels.
<li>Topper pads.
<li>Passive restraint doors.
<li>IP retainers.
<li>Nose pads.
<li>Full consoles.
<li>Rear seat consoles.
<li>Overhead consoles.
</ul>

UT Automotive works with a variety of skin and substrate materials and process technologies to provide the
appropriate surface finish, color and feel, and to ensure a common flow within the interior.
UT Automotive also designs and manufactures the stampings used as skeletons within these padded trim
products.
<P>
In addition, UT Automotive provides electroforming, painting and decorating, in-mold decorating, and
model and mandrill making.
<P>
Considerable efforts are under way to maximize the recycling of padded trim products and the
reduction of waste, to remain cost competitive and to address environmental concerns.

