<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML 3.0//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>UT Automotive Products: Remote/Keyless Entry Systems</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#173973" VLINK="#777777" ALINK="#C8D838" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<map name="products">
<area shape="rect" coords="361,23, 449,53" href="/jobs/jobs.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="268,23, 362,54" href="/doing/doin.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="201,00, 268,67" href="/protech/prod.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="114,23, 201,54" href="/media/medi.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="34,23, 115,53" href="/general/gene.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="00,22, 34,54" href="/index.htm">
</map>

<IMG SRC="../PROD.GIF" ALIGN=BOTTOM WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="68" BORDER="0" usemap="#products" border="0">
</center>
<!--header ends here-->

<h2>Remote/Keyless Entry Systems</h2>

<p>
UT Automotive is one of the world's largest providers of remote entry systems. Now in the third generation
of design, our remote entry systems use surface acoustic wave transmission, serial data bus, all
surface mount construction and proprietary encryption algorithms. We offer a number of features,
including:

<ul>
<li><strong>Illuminated Entry</strong> - Interior lights are activated by any remote control
function and operation of outside front-door handles, and deactivated by ignition or a certain
period of time.
<li><strong>Automatic Lock/Unlock</strong> - All doors lock when the transmission is shifted
out of the park position. The user may program this feature to unlock the doors or leave them
unlocked when the transmission is shifted back into park.
<li><strong>Automatic Unlock Upgrade</strong> - An additional feature that allows the user
to unlock the driver's door only when the transmission is shifted back into park.
<li><strong>Automatic Lock (Last Door Closed)</strong> - A delayed door lock operated
when the ignition is off and all doors are closed.
<li><strong>Lock-out Prevention</strong> - Door locking is inhibited if key is left in ignition.
<li><strong>Key Option</strong> - Door locking is prohibited if key is left in ignition.
<li><strong>Audible Feedback</strong> - A signal from the module may be used to activate a
horn to indicate a valid transmitter signal has been received or a specific remote control function
has been completed.
<li><strong>Remote Alarm (Panic)</strong> - Horn or siren may be activated remotely.
<li><strong>Theft Deterrent</strong> - System is armed by a proper locking sequence (remote
or manual) and disarmed by proper unlocking (remote or key). Improper unlocking, ignition or
entry causes alarm (flashing headlights and pulsing horn). Alarm stops after 3 minutes but system
remains armed and will reactivate if another improper action is detected. Alarm can be shut off
by remote unlock or key unlock.
<Li><strong>Changing Code and Encryption</strong> - Transmitted code changes after each
use to prevent playback. Encrypting algorithm prevents prediction of the next code.
<Li><strong>Personalization</strong> - Signal from module indicates which of four
transmitters was used to unlock vehicle. Other vehicle systems may use this signal to
accommodate individual setting and preferences such as memory seat and mirror positions,
climate control and radio station.
<li><strong>Seat Easy Entry and Anti-theft Positioning</strong> - When door is opened,
driver's seat moves downward and rearward to provide easy entry. Seat is positioned in fully up
and forward position when theft deterrent is activated.
<li><strong>Fuel Door Release</strong> - Fuel door can be released by remote operation.
<li><strong>Post Crash Unlock and Illuminate</strong> - Module, using a signal from a
vehicle crash sensing system, will unlock all doors and illuminate the interior lights after a fixed
delay time.
<li><strong>Retained Accessory</strong> - Accessory power remains on after ignition is turned
off to allow continued operation of power windows, radio, etc. Power is deactivated by opening
the driver's door or after a certain period of time.
<li><strong>Battery Saver/Upgrade</strong> - If a door is left open, this feature deactivates
interior lights after 10 minutes. The upgraded feature provides monitoring of trunk, glove box and
underhood lamps and limited their activation time to prevent battery from running down.
<Li><strong>Serial Data Bus</strong> - A diagnostic link for assembly plant testing,
verification and troubleshooting.
</Ul>

<!--footer begins here-->
