<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML 3.0//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>UT Automotive Products: Motors</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#173973" VLINK="#777777" ALINK="#C8D838" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<map name="products">
<area shape="rect" coords="361,23, 449,53" href="/jobs/jobs.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="268,23, 362,54" href="/doing/doin.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="201,00, 268,67" href="/protech/prod.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="114,23, 201,54" href="/media/medi.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="34,23, 115,53" href="/general/gene.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="00,22, 34,54" href="/index.htm">
</map>

<IMG SRC="../PROD.GIF" ALIGN=BOTTOM WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="68" BORDER="0" usemap="#products" border="0">
</center>
<!--header ends here-->

<h2>Motors</h2>


<IMG SRC="images/dcmotor.gif" ALIGN=TEXTTOP WIDTH="335" HEIGHT="268">

<p>
UT Automotive is one of the largest independent producers of fractional-horsepower DC
motors in North America - and a major producer in Europe. UT Automotive designs and
manufactures a broad spectrum of motors, ranging from 1.2 to 4.8 inches in
diameter, for a variety of automotive and commercial applications.
<P>
In Europe, UT Automotive meets customer needs through its Gate SpA subsidiary. Gate is
one of Europe's largest independent producers of radiator cooling fan motors
and modules and heater blower motors.
<P>
Technology and management expertise are shared by UT Automotive's North American and
European operations, including sophisticated test and development facilities
on both continents. UT Automotive relies on its fully equipped laboratories to complete
the product design and verification process.
<P>
Laboratory capabilities include dynamometer testing, vibration and shock, cycle
durability and environmental simulation, acoustic and EMI measurement,
prototype development and wind tunnel testing.
<P>
UT Automotive also uses the technology base of 800 engineers, scientists, technicians and
support personnel at the <a href="http://www.utrc.utc.com/">United Technologies
Research Center</a> in East Hartford, Conn.
<P>
In addition to the motors described here, UT Automotive will build motors to a
customer's specific requirements.

<h3>Model 1.5-II Windowlift Motor</h3>
<p>
The model 1.5-II windowlift motor is a compact and robust product designed for
high-volume automated production.
<P>
UT Automotive offers several windings to meet a wide range of performance requirements.
The motor is intended for arm and sector, drum and cable, and other regulator
systems. It is designed to meet the specifications of North American auto
manufacturers.
<P>
The 1.5-II is fully sealed and is suitable for the most adverse automotive
environmental conditions.

<h3>ABS Motors</h3>
<p>
The standard 2.5-inch motor has been adapted to meet the stringent demands of
anti-lock braking systems (ABS). Various performance characteristics are
available for specific applications.
<P>
This robust motor, which utilizes brake fluid-resistant components, is designed
to meet criteria specified by worldwide vehicle manufacturers. Sealing
capabilities are suitable for automotive environmental conditions. A laser bar
code scanning system records individual motor performance characteristics.

<h3>Truck, Off-Highway and Marine Motors</h3>
<p>
In addition to products for passenger cars and light trucks, UT Automotive produces a
variety of fractional-horsepower DC motors for use on medium and heavy trucks,
school buses, delivery vans, motor homes, agricultural vehicles, lawn and
garden equipment, and boats.
<P>
Applications include windshield wiper systems, starters for small gasoline and
outboard engines, blowers, winches and actuators. Motors for these and other
uses are designed for the specific application environment, providing
unsurpassed reliability.

<h3>DC Motors for Diverse Applications</h3>

UT Automotive offers a wide range of motors and motor-driven products tailored for
diverse applications. Such products include an idle speed actuator, seat
bolster, door lock actuator, electric shift motor and air pump motor for
emission control.
<P>
Various performance levels are available for specific applications.
<P>
The air pump system was developed by UT Automotive to help vehicle manufacturers control
emissions and meet stringent state and federal emissions legislation. This
12-volt, two-inch motor system helps eliminate complicated engine design and
space problems associated with mechanical air pump systems.
<P>
The electric shift motor and sensor replace a mechanical shifter. Advantages
include increased floor space, ease of shifting and logic control for precise
shifting.
<P>
Chief assets of these motors are small size, lightweight packages, long life
and world-class quality.

