<h2>Planning makes DN-101 GEM of opportunity for electronics teams</h2>

<p>
<IMG SRC="images/mod1.gif" ALIGN=BOTTOM WIDTH="240" HEIGHT="194">
<P>	Input Controls has several products on the Taurus/Sable, including a generic electronics module (GEM) developed by UTA's advanced engineering team.  The module controls 14 separate functions in one box connected to and mounted on the car's junction box (also a UTA component).  The 14 functions were controlled by eight or nine different modules on earlier versions of the Taurus/Sable, so, in addition to being a tremendous technical achievement, the GEM represents a significant cost savings for the customer.
<P>	Some of the 14 functions controlled by GEM are familiar, such as warnings for safety belts.  Others are new for the Taurus, such as a battery saver feature which will protect the car from battery current drain while the engine is shut off.  If there are no inputs to the GEM after 40 minutes, the GEM shuts off any accessories or interior lamps left on. (See below for full description of functions)</P>
<P>	Service workers can ask the GEM for system conditions or can run tests on the GEM to verify the integrity of the system and its connections.</P>
<P>	The Tampa, Fla.-built GEM will handle 14 separate electrical activities for the new Ford Taurus/Sable, including:</P>
<OL TYPE="1" START="1">
		<LI>Battery Saver - protects car from inadvertent battery drain by turning off accessories and interior lamps after 40 minutes of inactivity.
		<LI>Illuminated Entry/Courtesy Lamps - anytime a door is opened, interior lamps will go on and remain on for 25 seconds after all the doors are closed.
		<LI>Safety Belt Warning - if the driver's safety belt is not buckled when the ignition is turned to RUN, a lamp will light up in the instrument panel for 60 seconds and a chime will sound for 6 seconds.
		<LI>Key-In-Ignition Warning - if the key is in the ignition and not in the RUN position, a chime will sound when the driver's door is opened.
		<LI>Headlamps On - if the headlamps are on when the driver's door is open, a chime will sound continuously.
		<LI>Door Ajar Warning - if the ignition switch is in RUN, the GEM will sound a chime when any door is open and light up the Door Ajar lamp in the instrument panel.
		<LI>Front Wiper/Washer Control - the GEM decodes inputs from the multifunction switch (made by Input Controls in Traverse City, Mich.) and controls the low and high speed wipers, front windshield washer and seven pulse wipe intervals.
		<LI>Heated Backlight - activates the rear window and side mirror defrosters; turns off after 10 minutes.
		<LI>One Touch Down Power - the driver's side window down switch is momentarily pressed, the GEM activates the relay and lowers the window (motor by UT Automotive).
		<LI>Delayed Accessory - allows power windows and moonroof circuits to be closed for 45 seconds after the car is turned off.
		<LI>Steering System (VAPS II Variable Assist)-closed loop control of the current to the variable assist power steering actuator based on speed of car.
		<LI>Driver Door Lock Disable - prevents the driver's door from being locked if the key is left in the ignition.
		<LI>Central/Two-Step Unlock - allows all door locks to be unlocked form the driver's or passenger's key cylinder by turning the key to the unlock position twice.
		<LI>Low Coolant Level Indication - if coolant level drops below a preset level, the GEM will light up an indicator on the instrument panel and sound a chime.
</OL>
<CITE>Source: UT Automotive News, February, 1995</CITE>
