<h2>UT Automotive to build new engineering/technology center in the Philippines</h2>

<STRONG>CEBU, Philippines, Nov. 22, 1996</STRONG> - UT Automotive, a United Technologies company, today announced plans to invest $5 million in the construction of a 60,000-square-foot engineering and technology center in Cebu.
The new Philippine Engineering and Technology Center will replace a 13,000-square-foot facility currently located in a UT Automotive manufacturing facility in Cebu.<p>
UT Automotive expects the number of employees at the center will grow from 93 to more than 250 over the next five years. The new facility will accommodate the anticipated growth in personnel, as well as expand the laboratory and development areas.<p>
The center also will strengthen UT Automotive's commitment to serving customers in the Asia-Pacific region.<p>
"Although the Philippine Engineering and Technology Center has seen steady growth over the past four years, we have only scratched the surface of its potential," UT Automotive President Norm Bodine said. "The use of the Philippine Engineering and Technology Center by all UT Automotive business units provides a tremendous opportunity for business synergies through the sharing of information, pooling of resources on common projects, and development of systems proposals for new business ventures."<p>
"The Philippine Engineering and Technology Center will truly be a resource shared by all of UT Automotive."
<p>UT Automotive first established a Philippine Engineering and Technology Center in 1992 to provide engineering support to the Cebu manufacturing facilities, to establish design and quoting capability in Cebu, and to enhance UT Automotive's business presence in Asia-Pacific.<p>
The center initially supported UT Automotive's Wiring Systems business unit, but has provided support to the company's other business units - Input Controls, Interiors and Motor Systems - since 1995.<p>
The center, which is linked to other company engineering centers in North America and Europe, helps UT Automotive provide its customers with round-the-clock engineering capabilities throughout the world.
Operations at the Philippine center include computer-aided design (CAD), testing, modeling, warranty and reliability, parts-submission warrant (PSW) dimensional layout, and benchmarking.<p>
The center supports all quoting of new business proposals for Asian/Pacific customers, provides product engineering liaison to manufacturing operations, and conducts value-engineering/value-analysis (VE/VA) activities to ensure competitive quotes.<p>
UT Automotive, with headquarters in Dearborn, Mich., is a major supplier of electrical and interior trim systems and components to car and light truck manufacturers.<p>
UT Automotive is a unit of Hartford, Conn.-based <A HREF="http://www.utc.com">United Technologies Corp.</A>, which provides a broad range of high-technology products and services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.


