<h2>Michael Brown Named Vice President, General Counsel for UT Automotive</h2><IMG WIDTH=182 HEIGHT=260 BORDER=0 SRC="/general/people/pics/brown.gif">
<p>

<p><strong>
DEARBORN, Mich., Sept. 16, 1996</strong> - Michael O. Brown has been named vice president, general counsel for UT Automotive.  The announcement was made by Norman R. Bodine, president and chief executive officer for the company.
<p>
	Brown, 39, who has served as General Counsel at UT Automotive since February 1995, will continue to provide overall leadership for the legal function and its services for UT Automotive worldwide.  He will report directly to Bodine.<p>
Before joining UT Automotive, Brown was associate general counsel at United Technologies Corporation, UT Automotive's parent company.  During 14 years with United Technologies, he also has served at the company's Pratt & Whitney jet engine and Sikorsky helicopter units.<p>

He holds a bachelor's degree in international relations from Eisenhower College, Seneca Falls, New York, and a master's degree in international relations from <A HREF="http://www.syr.edu">Syracuse University</A>.  He also received his law degree from Syracuse University, where he graduated Cum Laude.<p>

Brown is a member of the Michigan, Connecticut and Florida Bar Associations.  He also had served as a member of the board of directors of Daewoo-Sikorsky Aerospace, Ltd. <p>
	UT Automotive is a major supplier of electrical, electronic and interior trim systems and components to car and light truck manufacturers.  Its products are part of nearly every passenger vehicle built in North America and Europe, and a growing number in Asia. <p>

UT Automotive is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based United Technologies Corp., (NYSE:UTX) which provides a broad range of high-technology products and services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.
<p>
