<H2>UT Automotive to reduce operations at Thomson, Ga., facility</H2><P>
<P><STRONG>THOMSON. Ga., June 28, 1996</strong> - UT Automotive today 
informed employees of the company's intention to reduce its operations in Thomson, Ga.</p>
<P>The company plans to move production of one of its lines of acoustical products from Thomson 
to a UT Automotive facility in Michigan by the third quarter of 1996.
Fewer than 50 of Thomson's 200 employees are expected to be affected by the consolidation.</P>

<P>This consolidation is part of ongoing cost and productivity improvement activities throughout
 the company. UT Automotive made the announcement today to provide as much advance notice as possible to
  its employees.</P>
<P>UT Automotive, with headquarters in Dearborn, Mich., is a major supplier of electrical and interior trim 
systems and components to car and light truck manufacturers. Its products are part of nearly
 every passenger vehicle built in North America and Europe.</P>
<p>UT Automotive is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corp.</a>, which provides a broad 
range of high-technology products and services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive 
industries.</P>
