<H2>UT Automotive to close Howe, Ind., facility</H2><P>
<P><STRONG>HOWE, Ind., June 27, 1996</STRONG> - UT Automotive today informed
 employees of the company's intention to discontinue operations at its Howe, Ind., facility in the
  first quarter of 1997. The closing will affect 220 employees.</P>
<P>The closing is part of ongoing cost and productivity improvement activities throughout the company.
 Production of interior trim and acoustical components at Howe will be transferred to UT Automotive 
 facilities in Michigan, where similar products are made.
The company made the announcement today to provide as much advance notice as possible to its 
employees.</P>
<P>UT Automotive, with headquarters in Dearborn, Mich., is a major supplier of electrical and interior trim 
systems and components to car and light truck manufacturers. Its products are part of nearly 
every passenger vehicle built in North America and Europe.
UT Automotive is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corp.</a>, which provides a broad 
range of high-technology products and services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive 
industries.</P>
