<H2>UT Automotive Names Linda M. Cummins Vice 
President, Communications and External Affairs</H2>
<IMG SRC="../images/cummins.gif" ALIGN=TEXTTOP WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="287">

<P>	<STRONG>DEARBORN, Mich., June 17, 1996</STRONG>  - Linda M. Cummins has been named vice president, Communications and External Affairs at UT Automotive, reporting to Norman R. Bodine, UT Automotive President and CEO.
<P>  	Cummins, who joins UT Automotive from the <A HREF="http://www.ford.com/" NAME="Ford Motor Company">Ford Motor Company</A>, will be responsible for UT Automotive's worldwide internal and external communications programs.  UT Automotive is a leading supplier of electrical and interior trim systems, with operations in 15 countries.</P></P>
<P>	"Lin has built strong worldwide relationships with the news media while at Ford," Bodine said.  "She brings to us a deep understanding of the automotive business and experience in developing and executing communications strategies, major programs and product marketing communications."</P>
<P>	Cummins had been associated with  Ford since 1977 and held a variety of communications positions, including her most recent assignment as manager of broadcast news.  She also held communication management assignments in Ford's International Operations, and with Ford Credit, Ford Tractor Operations and Ford Times  magazine.</P>
<P>	Cummins has a bachelor of science degree and a master of arts degree in communications from <A HREF="http://www.wayne.edu/">Wayne State University</A>, located in Detroit, Mich.  She is an accredited member of the <A HREF="http://www.prsa.org/" NAME="Public Relations Society">Public Relations Society of America</A>.</P>



	UT Automotive is a subsidiary of <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corporation</a> of Hartford, Conn. (NYSE: UTX), which provides a broad range of high technology products and services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.


