<H2>UT Automotive Names Northern to Head Interiors Business
</H2>

 <IMG SRC="../images/northern.gif" ALIGN=TEXTTOP WIDTH="192" HEIGHT="277">
<P>	<STRONG>DEARBORN, Mich., Feb 19, 1996</STRONG> - Ed Northern has been named vice president and general manager of UT Automotive's Interiors business unit.  The announcement was made by Norman R. Bodine, president and chief executive officer of UT Automotive.
<P>	Northern joined UT Automotive from Pratt & Whitney, both subsidiaries of United Technologies Corp. (NYSE:UTX), where he was general manager of the jet engine makers turbine airfoil product center in North Haven, Conn. During three years there, he implemented strategic initiatives in cellular manufacturing, total quality management and just-in-time delivery to achieve world-class standards in manufacturing..</P></P>
<P>	Prior to Pratt & Whitney, Northern served as vice president and general manager of the aerospace division of SKF/MRC Corp., and Interturbine Corp. He also worked for 24 years with General Electric's Aircraft Engine Group.</P>
<P>	He holds bachelor of science degree from the <a href="http://www.uc.edu">University of Cincinnati</a> and a master of business administration
    degree from <a href="http://xavier.xu.edu:8000/">Xavier University</a>.</P>
