  <head>
    <title>
      UTA Reduces Workforce at Newtion, Ill, Plant
    </title>
  </head>

  <body bgcolor="#ffffff">

    <p align="center">
    <img src="/images/heads/about.head.gif" width="550" height="150"
    alt="[about uta]">
    </p>

    <h5>Contact: Michael Scholl
      <a href="mailto:mscholl@uta.com">
        mscholl@uta.com
      </a>
      <br>
      (313) 593-9672
    </h5>

    <h2>United Technologies Automotive Reduces Workforce by 80 at Newton,
    Ill, Plant</h2>

    <strong>NEWTON, Ill., Jan. 8, 1996</strong> - United Technologies 
    Automotive's Newton manufacturing plant reduced its workforce of 558 by 80
    employees today. The reductions, which were communicated to the plant's 
    workforce last week, will affect production and production support 
    positions, largely in the plant's rotary (assembly) and indirect labor 
    areas.
    <p>
    The workforce reduction was based upon a need to realign the plant¹s 
    workforce to efficiently meet its production/plant load requirements, said
    Greg Clark, plant manager. The reduction mostly will affect employees with
    the shortest terms of service.
    <p>
    UTA¹s Newton plant, located on Marshall Drive, manufactures wiring 
    harnesses for trucks, sport utility vehicles and cars.
    <p>
    UTA, headquartered in Dearborn, Mich., is a major supplier of electrical,
    electronic and interior trim systems and components to car and light truck
    manufacturers worldwide. UTA is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based 
    <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corporation</a>
    (NYSE:UTX).

    <hr>

    <p align="center">
      <img src="/images/footers/about.footer.rev.gif">
