  <head>
    <title>
      Planar Systems, UTA to Develop Displays
    </title>
  </head>

  <body bgcolor="#ffffff">

    <p align="center">
    <img src="/images/heads/about.head.gif" width="550" height="150"
    alt="[about uta]">
    </p>

    <h5>
      Contacts: David Long - UTA
      <a href="mailto:dlong@uta.com">
        dlong@uta.com
      </a>
      <br>
      (313) 593-9615
      <p>
      Jerry Vieira - Planar Systems
      <br>
      (503) 690-7383
    </h5>

    <h2>
      Planar Systems, United Technologies Automotive Agree to Develop Displays
      for the Automotive Industry
    </h2>

    <strong>DEARBORN, Mich., - January 24, 1996</strong> -
    <a href="http://www.planar.com/">Planar Systems, Inc.</a> (NASDAQ: PLNR)
    and United Technologies Automotive (UTA), Inc. a subsidiary of
    <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corporation</a>
    (NYSE: UTX) announced today that they have entered into a series of
    agreements focused at jointly developing display products for the passenger
    automobile market.  
    <p>
    Under the agreement, Planar will supply UTA with customized display
    subsystems that will be incorporated into UTA products marketed to
    automotive manufacturers around the world. Such systems may provide
    navigation, vehicle tracking, function controls, security, trip computing,
    mapping/routing and other features.
    <p>
    "We are partnering with Planar to develop these products for the automotive
    market utilizing their electroluminescent (EL) capability because of the
    unique attributes of the technology for this difficult environment," said
    Norm Bodine, president and CEO of United Technologies Automotive. "Wide
    viewing angle, the ability to operate in a wide range of temperature and
    light environments and the inherent ruggedness of Planar's thin film EL
    technology make it ideally suited for these applications. In Planar, we
    have selected a partner that has a proven capability of moving core display
    technologies into high quality products," he said.
    <p>
    "We are very pleased to be a part of the UTA team," said Jim Hurd, president
    and CEO of Planar." UTA has a well established track record of supplying
    electronic subsystems to automobile manufacturers worldwide, and there is a
    very large additional potential for systems with displays in passenger cars.
    We are convinced that these systems will need the kind of high performance
    visual and environmental display attributes that are inherent in Planar EL
    display technology."
    <p>
    UTA is a full service supplier of electrical, electronic and interior trim
    systems to car and light truck manufacturers. Its products are part of
    nearly every passenger vehicle built in North America and Europe and a
    growing number in Asia.
    <p>
    Planar Systems, Inc. is a worldwide leader in the development, manufacture
    and marketing of high performance flat panel and CRT-based display products
    and systems. The primary market sectors that Planar serves today are
    medical, industrial, transportation, instrumentation, defense,
    communications and business/office equipment. The Company competes on a
    global basis with full development, manufacturing and marketing operations
    in both the United States and Europe.

    <p>

    <a href="ftp://www.uta.com/pub/primages/planar_image.jpg">
      <img src="/general/pr/images/planar_image.small.jpg">
      Click here
    </a>
    to download a high-resolution image.

