      <br>
      (313) 593-9672
    </h5>

    <h2>
      United Technologies Automotive Reduces Workforce by 95 at Newton,
      Ill., Plant
    </h2>

    <strong>NEWTON, Ill., Jan 26, 1996</strong> - United Technologies
    Automotive's Newton manufacturing plant reduced its workforce today by 95
    employees. The reductions, which were communicated to the plant's in-house
    union committee Wednesday, are the result of a reduction in production
    releases from the plant's major automotive customer. "It's unfortunate that
    we had to lay off these associates at this time," said Bob Smith,
    manufacturing manager for UTA's Newton plant. "We're in the process of
    setting up new lines for some incoming wiring harness business and hope to
    be able to call back most of them over the next few months."
    <p>
    UTA's Newton plant, located on Marshall Drive, manufactures wiring harnesses
    for trucks, sport utility vehicles and cars. 
    <p>
    UTA, headquartered in Dearborn, Mich., is a major supplier of electrical,
    electronic and interior trim systems and components to car and light truck
    manufacturers worldwide. UTA is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based
   <a href="http://www.utc.com/"> United Technologies Corporation</a>
   (NYSE:UTX).

