(313) 593-9672</h5>

    <h2>UT Automotive Names Lane Manager, Diversity</h2>

    <strong>DEARBORN, Mich., Nov.  13, 1995</strong> - Gloria J. Lane has been
    named manager, diversity programs at UT Automotive.
    The announcement was made by <a href="/general/people/meisner.htm">Rick
    Meisner</a>, UT Automotive's vice president of Human Resources.
    <p>
    Lane will be responsible for planning and implementing strategies and
    actions in support of UT Automotive's diversity programs and work environment. Lane
    also will chair UT Automotive's diversity panel.
    <p>
    Before joining UT Automotive,  Lane worked for Textron Automotive where she lead the
    design team for the 1992 Buick Skylark instrument panel. She has more than
    20 years of experience in automotive engineering-related positions. 
    Lane joined UT Automotive in 1991 as a senior product engineer, and most recently
    worked in UT Automotive's Interior Systems & Components unit.
    <p>
    She holds a bachelor's degree in mathematics from Claflin University,
    Orangeburg, S.C.
    <p>
    UT Automotive is a major supplier of electrical, electronic and interior trim
    systems and components to car and light truck manufacturers. Its products
    are part of nearly every passenger vehicle built in North America and
    Europe and an increasing number in Asia.
    <p>
   UT Automotive is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based 
    <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corp.</a> (NYSE:UTX),
    which provides a broad range of high-technology products and services to
    the aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.


