<h2>UT Automotive wins Honda multiplex business</h2>

<p>
<strong>DEARBORN, Mich., August 9, 1995</strong> - UT Automotive
has been awarded the electronic multiplex system business for a future Honda
model to be built at Honda of America Mfg. in Ohio.  

<p>
"UT Automotive has supplied electronic and switch products to Honda of America
Mfg. for several years, but this award is the company's first multiplex business
with a Japanese automaker, and offers UT Automotive the opportunity to demonstrate a
complex electronics system in Honda's very sophisticated design environment,"
said UT Automotive President <a href="/../general/people/norm.htm">Norman R. Bodine</a>.  

<p>
"This multiplex system development win is a credit to the UT Automotive hardware
and software design team in Dearborn, Michigan and to the plant in Tampa,
Florida where the products will be manufactured," Bodine said.

<p>
UT Automotive, Inc., headquartered in Dearborn, Mich.,
is a major supplier of electrical and interior trim systems and components to
car and light truck manufacturers worldwide.

<p>
UT Automotive, Inc. is a unit of <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies
Corporation</a> based in Hartford, Connecticut, U.S.A., which provides a broad
range of high technology products and services to the aerospace, building
systems and automotive industries.

