<h5>Contact: Michael Szudarek<br>
<em>or</em>
<a href="/people/scholl.html">Michael Scholl</a>
(<a href="mailto:mscholl@uta.com">mscholl@uta.com</a>)<br>
(313) 593-9672</h5>
<hr>
<h2>United Technologies Automotive's Tampa Electronics
Facility Had Hand in Redesign Of Popular Ford Taurus/Sable.</h2>

<p>
<strong>TAMPA, Fla., Aug. 14, 1995</strong> - The all new 1996 Ford Taurus and 
Mercury Sable models started rolling off assembly lines June 19 in 
Atlanta, packed with sophisticated features and state-of-the-art 
technology.

<p>
United Technologies Automotive's Tampa facility had a hand in
the completely redesigned models by supplying a sophisticated generic 
electronic module (GEM).

<p>
UTA's GEM is a revolutionary electronic module that is
responsible for a remarkable 14 separate electrical activities. One of the GEM's 
features includes Battery Saver, which protects the car from
inadvertent battery drain by turning off accessories and interior lamps after 40 
minutes of inactivity. Another feature, Driver Door Lock Disable,
prevents the driver's door from being locked if the key is left in the ignition. 

<p>
"The GEM has been a key project here in Tampa," Dan O'Dell,
plantmanager, said. "We've spent over two years preparing for the GEM
and have installed world-class manufacturing equipment to make it to
the highest quality standards. It is a real honor for the GEM to be such an 
integral part of the '96 Taurus/Sable programs.  I believe this is a
fine example of teamwork between UTA and <a href="http://www.ford.com/">Ford</a>."
 
<p>
Ford will honor associates at UTA's Tampa facility today by 
giving them a preview of the 1996 Taurus and Sable models. The
visit will be part of Ford's Supplier/Ford Plant "Appreciation Tour." 

<p>
This summer's tour began June 16 at two Ford plants in
Michigan and will wrap up Sept. 18, in Boston.     

<p>
"This tour is our chance to say thanks in a personal way to our 
suppliers, who have the same pride in producing quality products as
our employees all over the globe." Richard Landgraff, Taurus and Sable 
Vehicle Line Director, Ford Motor Company, said . "They are big 
contributors to Taurus being the top-selling car three years
running."
                
<p>
A large percentage of components in the 1996 models were
designed and manufactured by UTA. 

<p>
UTA was responsible for the complete electrical distribution
system, the power network box and 80 percent of the wire harnesses. UTA
also will supply components that include the keyless entry switch,
multifunction turn signal and ignition switch. 

<p>
In addition, UTA will provide exterior mirrors, the rear sail patch 
and steering wheels. UTA also is supplying four windowlift motors
per car. The Taurus/ Sable models will contain more UTA components
than any previous vehicle.

<p>
UTA is a major supplier of electrical and interior trim
systems and components to car and light truck manufacturers. Its products are
part of nearly every passenger vehicle built in North America and Europe.

<p>
UTA is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United
Technologies Corp.</a>, which provides a broad range of high-technology products and 
services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive
industries.     

