<h2>UT Automotive Names Galliker Treasurer</h2>

<p>
<strong>DEARBORN, Mich., Aug. 17,1995</strong> - Julia L. Galliker has been named 
treasurer of UT Automotive. The announcement was 
made by <a href="/../general/people/shah.htm">Rajesh K. Shah</a>, UT Automotive vice president and chief financial officer.

<p>
Galliker will oversee UT Automotive's treasury activities, including credit and  
collections, cash management, bank-relations, foreign exchange and risk 
management. 

<p>
Before joining UT Automotive, Galliker was with the Asia Pacific division of the 
Carrier Corp., where she most recently was deputy general manager, Carrier 
Guam. Before that, Galliker served as product planning manager at 
Carrier's Asia-Pacific headquarters in Singapore. She also held positions with 
Carrier as business analysis manager and international treasury manager.  
Carrier also is a unit of <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corporation.</a>
In addition, Galliker spent three years in financial management with 
<a href="http://www.ford.com/">Ford Motor Company</a>.

<p>
She holds a bachelor's degree in economics from Bucknell, a master's 
degree in international relations from Carleton University and an MBA from 
Pennsylvania State University.                                              

<p>
UT Automotive is a major supplier of electrical and interior trim systems and 
components to car and light truck manufacturers. Its products are part of
nearly every passenger vehicle built in North America and Europe. 

<p>
UT Automotive is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.- based <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corp.</a>,
which provides a broad range of high-technology products and services to the 
aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.  
