<h2>UT Automotive Reduces Workforce
by 45 at Columbus, Miss. Plant</h2>

<p>
<strong>Columbus, Miss., July 21, 1995</strong> - UT Automotive's
Columbus., Miss. manufacturing facility is reducing its workforce by
45 associates.  Plant Operations Manager Johnny Davis said the reductions
affect 45 salaried associates in the plant's operations area.

<p>
The reduction is part of a restructuring of the plant's overall
operations, which was initiated because of increasing competitiveness in
the North American automotive industry.  The plant manufactures a
variety of fractional horsepower DC motors for the automotive and
commercial/industrial markets.

<p>
UT Automotive's Columbus plant, located on S. McCrary Road, opened in 1954
and was expanded on six occasions to its present size of 550,000 square
feet.  The facility employed approximately 1,280 associates on June 1,
1995.

<p>
UT Automotive, headquartered in Dearborn, Mich., is a major supplier of
electrical, electronic and interior trim systems and components to car and
light truck manufacturers worldwide.  UT Automotive is a subsidiary of Hartford
Conn.-based <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corporation</a> (NYSE: UTX).

