<h2>Michael Brown Named General Counsel for United Technologies Automotive</h2>

<p>
<strong>DEARBORN, Mich., March 27, 1995</strong> - Michael O. Brown has been named
general counsel for UT Automotive.  The
announcement was made by Evelyn Simon, vice president, business
development and legal affairs for UT Automotive.

<p>
Before joining UT Automotive, Brown was associate general counsel at 
<a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corporation</a>, UT Automotive parent 
company.  During 14 years with United Technologies, he also has served 
at the company's Pratt & Whitney jet engine and Sikorsky helicopter divisions. 

<p>
Brown, 38, holds a bachelor's degree in international relations from
Eisenhower College, Seneca Falls, New York, as well as a Master's degree
in international relations and a law degree from <a href="http://www.syr.edu/">
Syracuse University</a>, Syracuse, New York.

<p>
Brown is a member of the Florida Bar Association and lectures
frequently on a variety of environmental law topics.  He also had served as
a member of the board of directors of Daewoo-Sikorsky Aerospace, Ltd.  

<p>
UT Automotive is a major supplier of electrical and interior trim systems and
components to car and light truck manufacturers.  Its products are part of
nearly every passenger vehicle built in North America and Europe.  

<P>
UT Automotive is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based 
<a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corp.</a>,
(NYSE:UTX) which provides a broad range of high-technology
products and services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive
industries.
