<h2>UT Automotive Names Raj Shah Vice President, 
Chief Financial Officer</h2>


<p>
<strong>DEARBORN, Mich., Feb. 27, 1995</strong> - UT Automotive (UTA) has named 
<a href="/people/shah.html">Rajesh K. Shah</a> as vice president and chief financial officer.  
The announcement was made by <a href="/people/norm.html">Norman R. Bodine</a>, president of UTA.

<p>
Shah will have responsibility for all of UTA's financial functions.   Prior
to joining UTA, Shah was with Varity Corporation, where he most recently was
executive vice president at the company's Dayton Walther division.

<p>
Before Dayton Walther, Shah held senior financial positions at Varity at
the corporate level and within two of its key operating divisions.  He served as
vice president, finance and planning at Kelsey-Hayes from 1989 to 1994, with
responsibility for its financial operations, and prior to that he was director of
finance for the Perkins Engine division in Peterborough, England.

<p>
In addition to his experience in the auto industry, Shah, who is a certified
public accountant, also has several years of experience in public accounting
with Arthur Andersen & Co.

<p>
He holds a bachelor of commerce degree from the University of Bombay,
India, and a master of business administration degree from 
<a href="http://www.bgsu.edu/">Bowling Green State University</a>, Ohio. 

<p>
UTA is a major supplier of electrical and interior trim systems and components
to car and light truck manufacturers.  Its products are part of nearly every
passenger vehicle built in North America and Europe.  

<p>
UTA is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies
Corp.</a>, which provides a broad range of high-technology products and
services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.

