<H2>UT Automotive to close Bennettsville, S.C., facility</H2>

<P>	<STRONG>DEARBORN, Mich., Jan. 9, 1995</STRONG> - UT Automotive today informed employees at its operations in Bennettsville, South Carolina, of the company's intention to discontinue operations at the facility by the end of March 1996. The closing will affect 264 employees.</P>
<P>	The closing is designed to reduce an excess in UT Automotive's manufacturing capacity as part of ongoing cost and productivity improvement activities. The manufacture of wiring systems at Bennettsville will be transferred to UT Automotive facilities in Illinois, Ohio, and the Philippines, where similar products are made.s are made.s are made.</P>
<P>	The company made the announcement today to provide as much advance notice as possible to its employees.</P>
<P>	UT Automotive is a major supplier of electrical, electronic and interior trim systems and components to car and light truck manufacturers worldwide.</P>
<P>	UT Automotive is a subsidiary of Hartford, Conn.-based <a href="http://www.utc.com/">United Technologies Corporation</a> (NYSE:UTX), which provides a broad range of high-technology products and services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.

