<H2>UT Automotive to close St. Matthews, S.C., facility</H2>

<P>	<STRONG>DEARBORN, Mich., Jan. 9, 1995</STRONG> - UT Automotive today informed employees at its operations in St. Matthews, South Carolina, of the company's intention to discontinue operations at the facility by the end of1996. The closing will affect 410 employees. UT Automotive produces electromechanical switches at the facility.</P>
<P>	The closing is part of ongoing cost and productivity improvement activities throughout the company. The work performed in St. Matthews will be transferred to UT Automotive facilities in Ohio and Mexico, where similar products are made.</P>
<P>	The company made the announcement today to provide as much advance notice as possible 
to its employees.</P>
<P>	UT Automotive, headquartered in Dearborn, Mich., is a major supplier of electrical, electronic and interior trim systems and components to car and light truck manufacturers worldwide.
<P>	UT Automotive is is a unit of United Technologies Corp., which provides a broad range of high-technology products and services to the aerospace, building systems and automotive industries.<!--footer begins here-->
