<head>

<TITLE>Wiring Systems makes cost-cutting changes</TITLE>

</head>

<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#173973" VLINK="#777777" ALINK="#C8D838" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">


<!--UT Automotive World News, a monthly publication by the Communications & External Affiars Department, is for the men and women of UT Automotive-->




<CENTER> <!---THIS CENTERS THE WHOLE PAGE ON THE SCREEN--->





<TABLE WIDTH="460" BORDER=0>

<TR>

<TD NOWRAP>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="nov/utmast.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE BORDER="0">
<CENTER>

</TD>

</TR>

</TABLE>



<p>





<TABLE WIDTH="460" CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0>

<TR>

<TD WIDTH="110" VALIGN="TOP">


<FONT SIZE=2 >
<A HREF="sloan.htm">SHOWING OFF IN PARIS</A>

<P>


<A HREF="wiring.htm">WIRING SYSTEMS MAKES COST-CUTTING CHANGES</A>

<P>

<A HREF="juarez.htm">JUAREZ EARNS ISO-9002</A>

<P>

<A HREF="women.htm">INTERIORS' WOMEN'S  GROUP ASKS THE QUESTION: <BR>'WHAT IF?'</A>

<p>

<A HREF="around.htm">AROUND UT AUTOMOTIVE</A>


</FONT>



</TD>






<TD WIDTH=350ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN="TOP">







<!---##########STORY STARTS HERE##########--->





<h1>Wiring Systems makes cost-cutting changes</h1>

<p>


Wiring Systems on Oct. 3 announced a series of changes in an effort to cut costs and consolidate work. 
The company will discontinue operations at its Newton, Ill., and North Manchester, Ind., facilities.  And some work produced at 
the Zanesville, Ohio, plant will move to Mexico.

<p>The closing of the Newton facility, which will be completed in the first quarter of 1997, will affect 450 associates.  
Production of wire harnesses at Newton will be transferred to UT Automotive facilities in Mexico and the Philippines.  

<p>Operations at the North Manchester plant also will be discontinued in the first quarter of 1997.  The closing, which was originally 
announced two years ago, will affect about 170 associates. Production of battery cable harnesses and related 
business will be consolidated at Wiring Systems facilities in Zanesville, Ohio.

<p>And production of some select wire harnesses will move from Zanesville to company facilities in Mexico. Work-force requirements in Zanesville are still under consideration because of the production changes 
at the plant. 

<p>The changes are part of ongoing cost-improvement activities throughout the company, said Ed Buker, vice 
president, Wiring Systems.

<p>"We regret these changes will result in a downsizing of our work force, and in the closing of our Newton and North Manchester facilities," he said.  "But unfortunately, in order to compete in our highly competitive business, these difficult decisions had to be made."

<p>In an effort to support associates in Newton and North Manchester, the company is developing plans to offer 
special outplacement services to associates affected by the change. Associates will be informed of such services as they 
become available.



