<head>

<TITLE>Juarez earns ISO-9000</TITLE>

</head>

<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#173973" VLINK="#777777" ALINK="#C8D838" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">


<!--UT Automotive World News, a monthly publication by the Communications & External Affiars Department, is for the men and women of UT Automotive-->




<CENTER> <!---THIS CENTERS THE WHOLE PAGE ON THE SCREEN--->





<TABLE WIDTH="460" BORDER=0>

<TR>

<TD NOWRAP>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="nov/utmast.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE BORDER="0">
<CENTER>

</TD>

</TR>

</TABLE>



<p>





<TABLE WIDTH="460" CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0>

<TR>

<TD WIDTH="110" VALIGN="TOP">


<FONT SIZE=2 >
<A HREF="sloan.htm">SHOWING OFF IN PARIS</A>

<P>


<A HREF="wiring.htm">WIRING SYSTEMS MAKES COST-CUTTING CHANGES</A>

<P>

<A HREF="juarez.htm">JUAREZ EARNS ISO-9002</A>

<P>

<A HREF="women.htm">INTERIORS' WOMEN'S  GROUP ASKS THE QUESTION: <BR>'WHAT IF?'</A>

<p>

<A HREF="around.htm">AROUND UT AUTOMOTIVE</A>


</FONT>



</TD>






<TD WIDTH=350ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN="TOP">







<!---##########STORY STARTS HERE##########--->





<h1>Juarez earns ISO-9000</h1>

<p>


Plant 042 in Juarez, Mexico, has earned ISO-9002 certification -- the first UT Automotive  plant in 
North America to earn such distinction. ISO-9002 is step one in a two-step process required to achieve 
QS-9000 registration.<p>

The Input Controls plant, which employs 1,000 associates, manufactures switches for Ford, Chrysler, General 
Motors, Mazda and Nissan. <p>

Plant manager Jeff Moore said "there's no magic involved" in obtaining the 
certification.  "You have to make QS-9000 a way of life, a routine," Moore said. <p> 

"And, just as important, you have to do what you say you're going to do."<p>

Associate teamwork and ownership, as well as upper management support, also were key to the plant's 
success.<p>

"We have had great support from our management," Moore said. "You can't get done what needs to be 
done without the person power, and our management made sure we got what we needed."<P>

Tom Wolanzyk, vice president and general manager, Input Controls, applauded the effort.<p>

"What Plant 042 has done is highly commendable," Wolanzyk said.<p>

"In spite of tremendous influx of new work, associates were still able to pursue certification."<p>

Plant 042 subscribes to the 5 "S's" and conducts exit interviews with every visitor for feedback as well as ideas
for improvement, Moore said. <p>

"We try to manage by reflection over here," he said.


<TD WIDTH="130" VALIGN=TOP>


</TD></TR></TABLE>
