<head>

<TITLE>Interiors' Women's group asks the question: 'What if?'</TITLE>

</head>

<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#173973" VLINK="#777777" ALINK="#C8D838" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">


<!--UT Automotive World News, a monthly publication by the Communications & External Affiars Department, is for the men and women of UT Automotive-->




<CENTER> <!---THIS CENTERS THE WHOLE PAGE ON THE SCREEN--->





<TABLE WIDTH="460" BORDER=0>

<TR>

<TD NOWRAP>

<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="nov/utmast.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE BORDER="0">
<CENTER>

</TD>

</TR>

</TABLE>



<p>





<TABLE WIDTH="460" CELLPADDING=5 BORDER=0>

<TR>

<TD WIDTH="110" VALIGN="TOP">


<FONT SIZE=2 >
<A HREF="sloan.htm">SHOWING OFF IN PARIS</A>

<P>


<A HREF="wiring.htm">WIRING SYSTEMS MAKES COST-CUTTING CHANGES</A>

<P>

<A HREF="juarez.htm">JUAREZ EARNS ISO-9002</A>

<P>

<A HREF="women.htm">INTERIORS' WOMEN'S  GROUP ASKS THE QUESTION: <BR>'WHAT IF?'</A>

<p>

<A HREF="around.htm">AROUND UT AUTOMOTIVE</A>


</FONT>



</TD>






<TD WIDTH=350ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN="TOP">







<!---##########STORY STARTS HERE##########--->





<h1>Interiors' Women's group asks the question: 'What if?'</h1>

<p>


What does a woman look for when buying a new car?<p>

This is the question a group of UT Automotive associates -- specifically, female associates -- 
is trying to answer.<P>

The Interiors' Women's Advisory Committee, a diverse group of 30 female associates -- including managers, 
secretaries, technicians and financial analysts -- meets at least once a month to discuss women's 
concerns about vehicle interiors.<p>
 
"Since approximately 78 percent of vehicle purchases are influenced by women, it quickly becomes 
evident why so much emphasis should be put on addressing women's concerns," said Gloria Lara, strategic 
planning and marketing, Interiors, who founded the women's group. <p>

"We go after the 'unobserved' needs, such as vanity mirrors that are inadequately lit, and the lack of storage 
compartments suitable for cellular phones, purses, shoes or baby bottles.  We discuss these ideas and then 
let our designers come up with the solutions."<p>

A recent meeting of the committee, attended by members of the Detroit media, demonstrated how the 
"what if?" brainstorming sessions work.  Participants discussed potential new products designed to 
stow trash and women's purses.<p>

Since the group was formed roughly four months ago, new product ideas have increased 
by more than 15 percent, according to Lara.  Some of these enhancements will be 
incorporated into prototype vehicles for presentation to OEM customers in the fourth quarter -- 
an idea-to-prototype time improvement of at least 20 percent.<p>

"Vehicle interiors are taking on greater importance with consumers, since vehicles are becoming an extension 
of a person's lifestyle," said Lara.<p>

Lara said she hopes the Interiors' women's committee is just the beginning. <p>

"We're hoping to deploy the concept of women's groups UT Automotive- and UTC-wide," she said.  <p>

Associates who have an idea for a vehicle's interior should  E-mail Lara at <A HREF="mailto:glara@uta.com">glara@uta.com</A>.




<TD WIDTH="130" VALIGN=TOP>


</TD></TR></TABLE>
