<!---##########STORY STARTS HERE##########--->





<h1>Around UT Automotive</h1>

<p>



<STRONG>Chihuahua, Mexico</STRONG><BR>
UT Automotive last month participated in the first Maquiladora Industry Parts & Components Trade Show 
in Chihuahua, Mexico. The trade show attracted more than 7,000 visitors and 330 exhibits.  United Technologies Automotive Electrical Systems de Mexico in Chihuahua 
displayed its wares in an effort to solicit potential suppliers, according to Max Vargas, manufacturing director, |
Chihuahua and Honduras operations.

<br>

"We attended the trade show in an effort to increase 
our Mexican supply base," Vargas said.  "Part of our business strategy is to develop local vendors who 
can provide quality materials at a competitive price."<p>

<STRONG>Columbus, Mississippi</STRONG><BR>
United Technologies Motor Systems in Columbus donated $10,000 to the Plymouth Bluff Center, a teaching, 
conference and environmental center operated by the Mississippi University for Women.

<br>

"Companies that 
are going to be successful in the future must have a work force that is exceptionally well trained in world-class 
practices and techniques," said Johnny Davis, director of  operations in Columbus. 



