<!--header ends here-->
<H2>Linda M. Cummins</H2>
<H3>Vice President<BR>
Communications and External Affairs</H3>
<IMG SRC="/media/pics/cummins.gif" ALIGN=TEXTTOP WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="287">
<P>Lin Cummins was named vice president, Communications and External Affairs, in June 1996. She is responsible for developing and communicating a strong UT Automotive image and reputation to customers, employees, suppliers and stockholders through a comprehensive communications strategy that improves UT Automotive's position in the marketplace.</P>
<P>Cummins had been with <A HREF="http://www.ford.com" NAME="Ford Motor Company">Ford Motor Company</A>'s communication department for 19 years. Her most recent assignment at Ford was manager, broadcast news, in which she was responsible for significantly growing Ford's product coverage in the broadcast media to worldwide audiences.</P>
<P>Cummins has a bachelor of science degree and a master of arts degree in communications from <A HREF="http://www.wayne.edu" NAME="Wayne State University">Wayne State University</A>.</P>

