<!--header ends here-->
    <h2>Jim Lloyd</h2>
    <h3>Vice President, Information and Network Resources</h3>
    <IMG SRC="pics/lloyd.gif">

    <P>

    <STRONG>James W. Lloyd</STRONG> was named vice president, Information
    Network Resources on March 31, 1993. His responsibilities include managing
    the information network that links the company's plants and facilities
    around the world.
    <P>
    Lloyd, who had been director, Information Network Resources, joined UT Automotive    in 1989.
    <P>
    Lloyd began his career in 1972 at Cutler Williams. He also held management
    positions at American Motors, and following its purchase, Chrysler Corp.
    <P>
    Lloyd holds a bachelor's degree from the
    <A HREF=http://www.uta.edu>University of Texas-Arlington</A> and a master's
    of business administration (MBA) degree from
    <A HREF=http://www.physics.wsu.edu>Wayne State University</A>.
    <P>
