<HEAD>
<TITLE>UT Automotive Test Facilities</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#173973" VLINK="#777777" ALINK="#C8D838" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<map name="general">
<area shape="rect" coords="362,23, 449,54" href="/jobs/jobs.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="273,24, 363,54" href="/doing/doin.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="198,23, 274,53" href="/protech/prod.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="122,24, 199,53" href="/media/medi.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="47,00, 122,67" href="../gene.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="01,23, 34,54" href="/index.htm">
</map>
<IMG SRC="../gene.gif" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="73" usemap="#general" border="0">
</center>
<!--header ends here-->
    <h2>5. Test facilities</h2>

 

    <p>
    UT Automotive performs rigorous testing on all of its products, and they are conducted
    at some of the most extensive engineering and test facilities in the world.
    <P>
    We analyze product performance in a full range of simulated environments.
    <P>
    Our physical testing laboratory provides mechanical/physical testing,
    artificial weathering, fogging testing, colorimeter/gloss meter analysis,
    hot/cold thermal chambers (minus 73 to 200 degrees Fahrenheit), sun lamp
    analysis, humidity testing chambers, abrader/wear testing analysis and
    automatic capillary rheometer.
    <P>
    UT Automotive also offers key functional testing capabilities that include an air bag
    deployment lab; steering wheel resonant frequency, vibration and durability
    testing; component/modular thermal cycling; coordinate measurement/part
    layout facilities; acoustical and ultrasound testing; and a mini-impact sled
    system.
    <P>
    During design and testing, and after products have been in the field, UT Automotive
    conducts extensive value engineering/value analysis programs to optimize
    ease of assembly, improve quality and lower cost.

<p>

    <p align="center">
      <a href="/general/info/capabilities.htm">[back]</a>
      <a href="/general/info/closer.htm">[top]</a>
      <a href="/general/info/process.htm">[next]</a>
    </p>

