<HEAD>
<TITLE>UT Automotive Systems Integration</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#173973" VLINK="#777777" ALINK="#C8D838" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<map name="general">
<area shape="rect" coords="362,23, 449,54" href="/jobs/jobs.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="273,24, 363,54" href="/doing/doin.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="198,23, 274,53" href="/protech/prod.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="122,24, 199,53" href="/media/medi.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="47,00, 122,67" href="../gene.htm">
<area shape="rect" coords="01,23, 34,54" href="/index.htm">
</map>
<IMG SRC="../gene.gif" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="73" usemap="#general" border="0">
</center>
<!--header ends here-->
    <h2>9. Systems Integration</h2>


    <p>
    UT Automotive's complete understanding of the various components and systems in a
    vehicle and how they interact is unmatched among automotive suppliers. More
    importantly, it offers our customers potential savings in vehicle assembly
    and improved product quality and reliability.
    <P>
    Examples of UT Automotive's systems integration abilities include:
    <ul>
      <li>Modular instrument panels or door panels with built-in wiring,
      switches and electronics, which can reduce cost, simplify vehicle assembly
      and improve reliability.
      <li>Door panels that include wiring, windowlift motors and door lock
      assemblies.
      <li>Modular headliners that integrate substrate, sunshades, switches,
      lamps, assist handles and other components into one tool-free, snap-in
      system.
      <li>A steering wheel system that incorporates the wheel and air bag module
      with a stub shaft containing redundant radio controls and other input
      switches.
    </Ul>
    <p>
    UT Automotive is heavily involved in the area of "mechatronics" - the integration of
    mechanical and electronic systems into one unit. This capability optimizes
    performance characteristics and can provide more efficient packaging,
    increased functionality and higher reliability.
    <P>
    UT Automotive has used mechatronics in creating a generic electronic module and
    junction box, a four-wheel-drive shift-on-the-fly transfer case, a smart
    windowlift motor system and a transmitter fob for remote entry systems.


    <p align="center">
      <a href="/general/info/pm.htm">[back]</a>
      <a href="/general/info/sysint.htm">[top]</a>
      <a href="/general/info/rnd.htm">[next]</a>
    </p>


