<area shape="rect" coords="01,23, 34,54" href="/index.htm">
</map>
<IMG SRC="../gene.gif" ALIGN=TOP WIDTH="450" HEIGHT="73" usemap="#general" border="0">
</center>
<!--header ends here-->
    <h2>10. Research and Development</h2>

   

    <p>
    UT Automotive constantly is finding ways to improve our products and develop new
    automotive applications through innovation, technology transfer and
    extensive research and development.
    <P>
    To provide our customers with the best technology in the world, technology
    transfer and information exchange occurs regularly among our operations in
    North America, Europe and Asia. We also are working with many other renowned
    private, government and university laboratories.
    <P>
    In addition, the <a href="http://www.utrc.utc.com/">United Technologies
    Research Center</a> has been a leading initiator of technical change
    throughout <a href="http://www.utc.com/">UTC</a>. Central to the
    <a href="http://www.utrc.utc.com/">Research Center's</a> technical
    leadership are innovations that enable change, like computer-aided design
    systems; innovations that drive product change, like advances in digital and
    power electronics in photonics and magnetics; and process innovations that
    are essential to maintaining competitive advantage, like rapid prototyping
    and integrated product development.
    <P>
    For example, the <a href="http://www.utrc.utc.com/">Research Center</a>
    helped UT Automotive apply surface acoustic wave technology to develop hand-held
    remote vehicle entry systems, a first application outside of the aerospace
    industry.
    <P>
    The ingenuity of <a href="http://www.utc.com/">UTC's</a> engineers and
    scientists is represented by the 12,000 patents held by the company
    worldwide.  Strong research and development investment - about $1.8 billion
    annually in company, customer and government funds - helps assure
    <a href="http://www.utc.com/">UTC's</a> continued technology leadership.

    <Hr>

    <p align="center">
      <a href="/general/info/sysint.htm">[back]</a>
      <a href="/general/info/rnd.htm">[top]</a>
      <a href="/general/info/hr.htm">[next]</a>
    </p>


