<!--header ends here-->
    <h2>Edwin L. Buker</h2>
    <h3>Vice President and General Manager, Wiring Systems</h3>
    <img src="pics/buker.gif">

    <p>

    <strong>Ed Buker</strong> was named
    Wiring Systems vice president & general manager on Aug. 28, 1995. He is
    responsible for the business unit that designs and manufactures electrical
    distribution systems for automotive applications, including wire harnesses,
    control modules, junction boxes, power network boxes, relays, fuse boxes,
    terminals and connectors.
    <P>
    Buker had been with BMW for three years, most recently as vice
    president-Munich, Germany office for BMW Manufacturing Corp. Previously he
    was vice president, Manufacturing, at BMW's U.S. vehicle plant in
    Spartanburg, S.C., during its start-up.
    <P>
    Before joining BMW, Buker spent eight years with Honda of America
    Manufacturing, Inc.  Buker has a bachelor's degree in mechanical engineering
    from Tri-State University and a master's degree in business administration
    from <a href="http://www.ohiou.edu/">Ohio University</a>.

