    <h2>Kathleen Ligocki</h2>
    <h3>Vice President & General Manager<br>Motor Systems</h3>
<IMG SRC="pics/ligocki.gif" ALT="Ligocki" ALIGN=BOTTOM WIDTH="199" HEIGHT="261"> 

<p><strong>Kathleen Ligocki </strong>was named vice president & general manager, Motor Systems, on July 8, 1996. She is the leader of the business unit responsible for windowlift, ABS, starter and wiper motors; transfer case actuators; and treadmill drive motors.
<P>Ligocki joined United Technologies Corp. (UTC), UT Automotive's parent company, in 1994 as director of manufacturing and purchasing for Carrier's European transcontinental operations in Paris, France.</P>
<P>Before joining Carrier, she spent 15 years with Delco Electronics in a variety of positions including production supervisor, manager of field sales, program manager, factory manager and operations manager.</P>
<P>Ligocki has a bachelor's degree in liberal arts from <A HREF="http://www.indiana.edu/" NAME="Indiana University">Indiana University</A> and an MBA from <A HREF="http://www.wharton.upenn.edu/" NAME="Wharton School">Wharton School</A> of the University of Pennsylvania.</P>
