<!--header ends here-->

    <h2>Ed Northern</h2>
    <h3>Vice President and General Manager,<br>
    Interior Systems &amp; Components</h3>
    <img src="pics/northern.gif">

   

    <p>

    <strong>Edward W. Northern</strong> is vice president and general manager,
    Interiors. Northern joined UT Automotive from
    <a href="http://www.utc.com/PW4000/pw4000.html">Pratt & Whitney</a>, where
    he was general manager of the jet-engine maker's turbine airfoil product center in
    North Haven, Conn. During three yearsthere, he implemented
    strategic initiatives in cellular manufacturing, total quality management and just-in-time delivery to achieve world-class standards in manufacturing.
    <p>
    Prior to Pratt & Whitney, Northern served as vice president and general manager of the
    aerospace division of SKF/MRC Corp., and Interturbine Corp. He also worked for 24 years with General Electric's Aircraft Engine Group.
    <p>
    He holds bachelor of science degree from the <a href="http://www.uc.edu">University of Cincinnati</a> and a master of business administration
    degree from <a href="http://xavier.xu.edu:8000/">Xavier University</a>.
    <P>

