    <h2>Francis J. Macielak Jr.</h2>
    <h3>Director, Human & Natural Resource Protection</h3>
    <img src="pics/macielak.gif">


    <p>
    As director of Human and Natural Resources Protection, <strong>Frank
    Macielak</strong> is responsible for planning, directing, implementing and
    controlling the environmental, industrial hygiene, safety and workers'
    compensation programs for all of UT Automotive's worldwide operations.

    <p>
    Macielak joined UT Automotive in 1981 and manager, Industrial Hygiene and Safety,
    in the Automotive Products Division. Before joining UT Automotive, Macielak was
    with General Electric Corp. and Kemron Environmental Services.

    <p>
    Macielak has a bachelor's degree from
    <a href="http://www.wmich.edu/">Western Michigan University</a>. He is a
    certified industrial hygienist and a certified safety professional. 

