    <h2>Rick Meisner</h2>
    <h3>Vice President of Human Resources</h3>
    <IMG SRC="pics/meisner.gif">

    <P>

    <STRONG>Richard L. Meisner</STRONG> was named vice president, Human
    Resources on March 4, 1991. He provides human resource leadership to UT Automotive's
    42,000 employees worldwide, and reports directly to UT Automotive President 
    <A HREF="/general/people/norm.htm">Norm Bodine</A>.
    <P>
    Meisner joined <A HREF=http://www.utc.com>United Technologies Corp.
    (UTC)</A> in 1976. He has held human resource and labor relations positions
    with <A HREF="http://www.utc.com/pweh.htm">Pratt &amp Whitney</A>, <A HREF="http://www.hamilton-standard.com">Hamilton Standard</A> and at UTC corporate offices in
    Hartford, Conn. Before coming to UT Automotive, Meisner was vice president of 
    human resources and industrial relations for <A HREF="http://www.carrier.com">Carrier Corp.</A>'s North 
    American Operations in Syracuse, N.Y.
    <P>
    Meisner holds a bachelor's degree in psychology from the
    <A HREF=http://www.uconn.edu>University of Connecticut</A> and  a master's
    degree in psychology from <A HREF=http://www.sjc.edu>St. Joseph College</A>.
    <P>

       
