    <h2>Mike O'Day</h2>
    <h3>Vice President<br>
    Quality and Enterprise Productivity</h3>
   <IMG SRC="pics/oday.gif" ALIGN=TEXTTOP WIDTH="192" HEIGHT="279"> 

 

<P><STRONG>Mike O'Day</STRONG> was named vice president, Quality and Enterprise Productivity, on
 May 22, 1996. </p>
<p>He is responsible for the development of quality systems and improvement processes, including QS-9000, 
business process re-engineering and UT Automotive's product development and launch (PDL) process.</P>
<P>O'Day had been director of sales and marketing for UT Automotive-Europe. Before his assignment in Europe, O'Day 
served as plant manager of UT Automotive's electronics facility in Tampa, Fla.</P>
<P>O'Day joined UT Automotive in 1986 from General Electric, where he was responsible for quality initiatives 
leading to GE's supplier certification with General Motors, Ford and utility market suppliers.
O'Day has a bachelor's degree in mechanical engineering and a MBA from the <a href="http://www.umich.edu/">University of Michigan</a>.
</P>

