<!--header ends here-->
    <h2>Raj Shah</h2>
    <h3>Vice President of Finance and CFO</h3>
    <IMG SRC="pics/shah.jpg">



    <P>

    <STRONG>Rajesh Shah</STRONG> joined UT Automotive
    on Feb. 27, 1995 as vice president and chief financial officer. He has
    responsibility for all of UT Automotive's financial functions.
    <P>
    Before joining UT Automotive, Shah was executive vice president at the Dayton
    Walther division of Varity Corp. Before moving to Dayton Walther, Shah 
    held senior financial positions at Varity and within two of its divisions:
    He was vice president, finance and planning, at Kelsey-Hayes; and he was
    director of finance for Perkins Engine in Peterborough, England.
    <P>
    Shah, a certified public accountant, also has several years of experience
    in public accounting with Arthur Anderson &amp Co.
    <P>
    Shah holds a bachelor's degree in commerce from the University of
    Bombay, India, and a master's of business administration (MBA) degree
    from <A HREF=http://www.bgsu.edu>Bowling Green State University</A>.
    <P>

