<!--header ends here-->
<h2>Michael M. Scholl</h2>
<h3>Manager, Public Relations</h3>
<IMG SRC="/media/pics/scholl.gif" ><p>
    Michael M. Scholl was named manager, public relations in May 1994. He is 
    responsible for managing UT Automotive's external communications, including media
    relations, advertising, exhibits and displays and other special projects.
    <P>
    Scholl joined UT Automotive from Eisbrenner Public Relations in Troy, Mich., where
    he had been for seven years, most recently as vice president. His account
    responsibilities there included communications consulting for a variety
    of automotive supplier, computer software and engineering clients.
    <P>
    He earned a bachelor's degree in public relations with a minor in music
    from <a href="http://www.byu.edu/">Brigham Young University</a> and holds
    membership in the Public Relations Society of America, Automotive Press
    Association, Society of Plastics Engineers and the Automotive Public 
    Relations Council of the Motor Equipment Manufacturers Association.
 
