<h1>BREED purchases Steering Wheels</h1>

<p>



<IMG SRC="wheels2.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="192" BORDER="0" HSPACE="4" VSPACE="2">

On Sept. 23, United Technologies Automotive Systems, Inc. announced it agreed in principle to sell its 
Steering Wheels operation to BREED Technologies, Inc.  The proposed acquisition is expected to be completed 
as soon as possible following any required regulatory reviews.  Financial terms of the agreement were not disclosed.<p>

The sale includes UT Automotive's steering wheel manufacturing facilities in Grabill, Ind., and Birmingham, England, 
as well as its leather wrap capabilities in Interiors' Monterrey, Mexico, facility.  The Niles, Mich., Steering Wheels plant 
will close in early 1997.<p>

"Our customers are moving quickly toward sourcing the steering wheel, air bag module and cover as a complete,
integrated system," said President Norm Bodine. <p>
 
"After carefully examining the possibilities, we concluded that systems integration should best be managed by the 
combination of an air bag manufacturer with a steering wheel manufacturer."<p>

BREED, which employs more than 7,000 people in 42 locations, provides a complete range of occupant safety 
systems and other components to the world's major automotive manufacturers.  Headquartered in Lakeland, Fla., 
BREED manufactures electronic and electromechanical sensors, air bag modules, steering wheels, bumpers, instrument 
panels, interior and exterior trim and inflators.<p>

BREED operates 24 manufacturing and 18 engineering and sales facilities 
in England, Finland, France, Germany, Hungary, Italy, Japan, Mexico and the United States.<p><p>

<center><A HREF="breed.htm">TOP OF PAGE</A><p>

