<h1>Cebu wins President's Award</h1>

<p>



<IMG SRC="plant222.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="322" HEIGHT="209" BORDER="0" HSPACE="10" VSPACE="4">

Plant #222 in Cebu, Philippines, has been selected to receive UT Automotive's President's Award for 
Environment, Health and Safety for 1995.<p>

The annual award is presented on a worldwide basis to the operation that has
demonstrated excellence in environmental, health and safety performance.<p>

Frank Macielak, director, Environment, Health and Safety (EH&S), said the President's Award is intended to 
acknowledge sustained significant improvement in the environmental, health and safety performance over the 
most recent three-year period.<p>

"This award is our way of acknowledging exceptional 
performance in the protection of the environment and our associates' health and safety," 
he said<p>

Plant #222's environmental, health and safety performance was evaluated in the following areas:  
occupational injuries and illnesses, air emissions, hazardous waste and regulatory compliance.<p>

Jon Villaflor, Plant 222 manager, said the success of the plant can be credited to 
associates' commitment to EH&S programs.<p>

"We believe that in order for each  individual to work safely and be safety conscious, he or she must be properly trained," he said.
Cebu reported a low number of lost work days due to job-related incidents in 1993 and 1994 and improved on that record by reporting zero lost work days in 1995.<p>

"To obtain and, more importantly, maintain the level of performance that Plant #222 has is a reflection of the 
commitment to and the involvement of everyone in the pursuit of environmental, health and safety 
excellence," Macielak said. 

<p><p>

<center><A HREF="cebu.htm">TOP OF PAGE</A><p>

