<h1>Around UTC</h1>

<IMG SRC="pratt.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="36" HEIGHT="37" BORDER="0" HSPACE="3" VSPACE="0">
Pratt & Whitney has apparently won a sizable contract -- perhaps worth $500 million -- from United Airlines.  
United has placed a $2.5 billion order for an unspecified 
number of Boeing 747s, 757s and 777s.<p>

<IMG SRC="pratt.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="36" HEIGHT="37" BORDER="0" HSPACE="3" VSPACE="0">
Pratt & Whitney has been selected by the U.S. Air Force to supply engines to power four new C-32A 
executives and Congressional transport aircraft.  The total value of the order, including installed engines and 
spares, is $534 million.  The equipment will be delivered in 1998.<p>

<IMG SRC="otis.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="36" HEIGHT="35" BORDER="0" HSPACE="3" VSPACE="0">
Otis has introduced its new worldwide integrated building transit 
system called "Odyssey," which will make possible the next 
generation of high-rise building design.  The system will use vehicles 
capable of moving people horizontally and vertically; whether in a super-tall 
or very wide structure.  By integrating horizontal and vertical movement in a single design, 
Odyssey will make it possible for passengers to travel from a remote parking lot to the very
top of the adjacent tall building in the same cab.<p>

<IMG SRC="otis.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="36" HEIGHT="35" BORDER="0" HSPACE="3" VSPACE="0">
Otis Elevator hopes Beijing's plans to increase the supply of low-cost housing will reignite flagging 
sales growth in China.  This, combined with the government's plans to direct about $602 million toward 
housing loans during the second half of the year, will change the market for elevators and 
escalators significantly.<p>

<IMG SRC="carrier.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="36" HEIGHT="36" BORDER="0" HSPACE="3" VSPACE="0">
Carrier has penetrated deeply into the Chinese air conditioning market and was one of the biggest 
exhibitors at this year's China Refrigeration Show in Shanghai.  Carrier-China is developing the largest 
operation outside of the United States, and Carrier's global strategies place its 
Asia-Pacific operations side-by-side with its North American operations.<p>

<IMG SRC="sikor.gif" ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="36" HEIGHT="35" BORDER="0" HSPACE="3" VSPACE="0">
Sikorsky may be among the bidders when Turkey makes its expected purchase of 145 assault helicopters 
worth $3 billion over the next 10 years.  





<p><p>

<center><A HREF="utc.htm">TOP OF PAGE</A><p>

