<h2>Aspen Internet Services Adopts Watkins Mill High School</h2>

Aspen Internet Services has volunteered its expertise and services
to Watkins Mill High School (WMHS), located in Montgomery Village,
Maryland, in the development of a World Wide Web site for its
teachers and students. As more schools are being connected to
the Internet, its value as an educational resource that is available
24 hours per day, 7 days per week is being recognized.
<p>
The Watkins Mill Web site, currently in development, will serve
as an <i>educational resource</i> for students, a <i>communications
tool</i> for faculty and parents, and an <i>information dissemination
vehicle </i>for the school. Aspen will help guide teachers and
students in the creation of the site. Major content areas planned
for the WMHS Web site include school news and activities; study
assignments and resources; information for parents; and information
for students, including an online newspaper.
<p>
"Aspen is pleased to volunteer its services to the community,
especially for such an important project as the WMHS Web site,"
said Scott Crocket, Vice President of Aspen Internet Services.
"Watkins Mill has recognized the value of the Internet as
an educational resource for its students, and we are pleased to
help the school achieve its goals in this area."
<p>
The Watkins Mill Web site is expected to be completed in early
1997.

<p><br>

<H2>New Aspen-Developed Sites Now On the Web</H2>
Aspen Internet Services is pleased to announce that the Web sites for <A HREF = "http://www.umm.edu/"><B>University of Maryland Medicine</B></A>, <A HREF = "http://www.fmbancorp.com/"><B>Farmers and Mechanics National Bank</B></A>, and the <A HREF = "http
://www.naima.org/"><B>North American Insulation Manufacturers Association</B></A> are now available on the World Wide Web.  Developed by Aspen, these sites offer useful information and exciting, interactive features.<P>

In developing Web sites for our clients, Aspen provides a full range of support. Among the services we offer are creation of overall site design and navigational strategy; consultation on site content and organization; HTML coding; scanning; CGI-scripting
 and other Web production services; and general project management.<P>

For more information on Aspen's Internet Services, please contact Scott Crocket at (301) 251-5126 or via e-mail at <a href=mailto:scrocket@aspensys.com><B>scrocket@aspensys.com.</B></A>
<P><BR>

