<TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=500>
<TR><TD>
<FONT SIZE=4>Information is the cornerstone of any organization's existence.
Information is used daily to
make key decisions about products and services, costs, and
productivity -- factors that
influence success. An ongoing challenge for all organizations is
the sheer volume of
information that must be identified, gathered, managed, and
disseminated. Staff resources,
technology, and deadlines also affect the ability to maximize the
use and value of
information.<P>

Aspen Systems Corporation offers solutions to help manage
information for success. We
have the experience, staff, and technology to make information
work to your benefit. Over
the past three decades, we have pioneered many of the information
management standards in
use today. Our <!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="timel2.html">timeline</A> shows just a few of these major achievements.<P><BR>


<H2>About Aspen</H2>
Aspen Systems Corporation was founded in 1958 and, since that
time, has successfully
served clients in all sectors of business and government. In the
past 10 years alone, the
company's sales have tripled. We currently have more than 1,800
employees, offices across
the country, and a growing and diverse customer base.<P>

In 1993, the company was purchased by our employees, creating an
even greater level of
commitment toward achieving our corporate mission: to provide the
tools, knowledge,
personnel, and technology needed to maximize the impact of
<A HREF="clientsf.html">our
clients'</A> most precious
resource -- information.<P><BR>

<H2>Using information to achieve success</H2>

Identifying, gathering, and analyzing information is critical for
effective decision-making.
Aspen converts information into a valuable resource that supports
your organization's
objectives. We achieve this transformation by offering a full
range of information
management services, including:


<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>

<LI> <A HREF="#survey">survey design, data collection, and analysis</A>
<LI>
<A HREF="#centerdesign">information center design and management </A>
<LI>
<A HREF="#healthdata">health data and information management</A>
<LI>
<A HREF="#litigat">litigation support</A>
<LI>
<A HREF="#systel">information systems and telecommunications technical support</A>
<LI>
<A HREF="#print">print and electronic publishing services</A>
<LI>
<A HREF="#orderful">order fulfillment and distribution services</A>
<LI>
<A HREF="#techassis">technical assistance and training</A>
</UL>

 <P><BR>

<H3>
<A NAME="survey">Survey design, data collection, and analysis</A></H3>

Every organization needs to collect and analyze data to identify
market trends, measure
customer satisfaction, or serve as the foundation for new
programs. Aspen's expertise in
survey and sample design, data collection, and primary and
secondary data analysis is
supported by more than 20 years of experience and our use of
innovative research
technologies. Our staff includes professionally trained
researchers and statisticians, many
with advanced degrees in basic and applied research, information
management, and science
and technology. We offer a full complement of services,
including:


<UL>
<LI>research study and sample design
<LI>customized data collection through mail, telephone, focus groups, field surveys, and electronic forms
<LImeasurement and instrumentation studies
<LI>data analysis, including program evaluations and qualitative research studies 
</UL>

We specialize in surveying professional and business populations
that are often hard to reach,
requiring innovative followup. We employ both basic and emerging
tools and protocols,
including e-mail, Internet surveys, and interactive telephone
response. Our state-of-the-art
Survey Operations Center manages a full range of computer-based
survey services to collect,
process, and report data in an efficient and accurate manner. All
research results are
presented in written, graphical, and electronic formats that
include recommended solutions
for your organization.<P><BR>

<H3>
<A NAME="centerdesign">Information center design and management</A></H3>

<IMG WIDTH=122 HEIGHT=160 ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="Sysph.gif">
Effective information management is critical to provide relevant
information to the right
people in the most appropriate format. For example, government
agencies need to provide
timely information to their constituency audiences. Policymakers
need detailed analyses to
make more informed decisions, researchers require
government-compiled data to identify
new solutions to common problems, and the general public needs
practical,
easy-to-understand information. Aspen is skilled in maximizing
the value of information
through the design and management of information centers. This
includes:

<UL>
<LI>information collection, analysis, and synthesis
<LI>database development and maintenance
<LI>library and reference services
<LI>information center design and management
<LI>telephone hotline operation
<LI>document production and distribution
</UL>

We identify the information needs of different audiences,
organize all available information
resources, and provide each audience with useful information in
the desired formats, resulting in an integrated approach to information management that is
efficient, responsive, and
cost effective. <P><BR>

<H3>
<A NAME="healthdata">Health data and information management</A></H3>

Changes in payment systems, technology, and the delivery of
healthcare services mean that
healthcare organizations are called upon to provide more and
better services, often with
fewer resources. Quality data and the ability to produce, store,
retrieve, and use health
information are essential to financial success. Aspen provides a
range of results-oriented
health information services. We offer:


<UL>
<LI>workflow analysis and design services
<LI>customized data collection, including clinical coding
<LI>clinical data abstraction
<LI>database design and creation
<LI>data analysis and synthesis
<LI>systems and telecommunications technical support
</UL>

Among our clients are hospitals and HMOs, third-party payors, and
Federal, state, and local
government agencies that contract with Aspen to monitor data
quality, improve business
processes, and design and implement health information systems.

<H3>
<A NAME="litigat">Litigation support</A></H3>

Since 1973, Aspen has been providing litigation support services
to both government and
private industry clients. Our professionals help attorneys
prepare for a case or investigation
by acquiring, organizing, and managing legal documents and
information. Paralegals,
systems engineers, and other project personnel assist attorneys
in preparing for pretrial and
trial activities. We also offer AspenView&reg;, a software tool that
combines index-based and
full-text searching with image retrieval capabilities. Additional
technical services offered
include:


<UL>
<LI>document indexing and coding
<LI>optical imaging and OCR/ICR
<LI>microfilming and film-to-image conversion
<LI>document and image retrieval solutions
<LI>document repository operations
</UL>

Imaging and OCR data capture are supported by Aspen's Image
Processing Center, a full-service document conversion facility that routinely processes large amounts of information in a timely, cost-efficient manner.<P><BR>

<H3>
<A NAME="systel">Information systems and telecommunications technical support</A></H3>

Aspen's systems developers and software engineers assist our
clients in developing and
implementing effective information systems and telecommunications
networks. Whether using
commercial off-the-shelf software or creating customized systems,
we specialize in
integrating data from multiple sources and formats to create
responsive and practical systems.<P>


For both information systems and telecommunications networks, we
provide the right mix of
technical support at each phase of the information systems life
cycle: requirements analysis,
software selection, systems design and development, testing,
documentation, implementation,
operation, training, enhancement, and evaluation.<P><BR>

<H3>
<A NAME="print">Print and electronic publishing services</A></H3>

<IMG WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=156 ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="timpub.gif">
Professionally developed print and electronic communications can
set you apart from your
competitors. Aspen understands this and has the skills and
resources to produce print, video,
and electronic products that get noticed. We work with our
clients to determine key
messages, identify target audiences, and determine the most
appropriate formats to ensure
successful communication. Our award-winning writers, editors, and
graphic designers create
a wide range of products using the latest desktop and
computer-assisted publication tools. We
conceptualize and produce everything from logos to CD-ROMs --
each with compelling
graphics and targeted messages for diverse audiences.<P><BR>

<H3>
<A NAME="orderful">Order fulfillment and distribution services</A></H3>

Aspen manages several distribution centers that support outreach
efforts for many
organizations. The distribution centers feature integrated
computer systems to track
inventory, sales, and billing procedures. Our sophisticated
mailing centers utilize a database
that automatically compares shipping alternatives to arrive at
the most efficient and
economical option. Our print-on-demand and fax-on-demand services
provide fast response to
time-sensitive projects. We also maintain customer mailing lists,
provide management
reports, and offer direct mail services.<P><BR>

<H3>
<A NAME="techassis">Technical assistance and training</A></H3>

Changes in programs, policies, and technology require ongoing
training to ensure a skilled
and knowledgeable workforce. Through years of experience, Aspen's
technical assistance
professionals have honed the capability to communicate changes
and introduce new concepts
effectively. Our services include:


<UL>
<LI>needs assessments
<LI>site visits for data collection and research
<LI>instructional design
<LI>curriculum and training materials development
<LI>onsite training assistance
<LI>interactive Internet training
<LI>video and computer conferencing
</UL> 

Many organizations also turn to Aspen for meeting and conference
management. We help
design the program and agenda, produce all materials, manage the
registration process,
design and staff exhibits, and prepare and distribute conference
proceedings. Our conference
management specialists provide support services for hundreds of
conferences annually.<P><BR>

<H2>Our commitment to people  </H2>

<IMG WIDTH=121 HEIGHT=160 ALIGN=RIGHT SRC="Comit.gif">
Aspen provides clients with the right people to do the job right. 
We employ specialists
whose knowledge, experience, and skills translate into practical
and achievable results. For
any assignment, Aspen draws upon a variety of professional
disciplines to deliver the precise
blend of information management programs and services needed to
meet your requirements
and exceed your expectations.<P>

Aspen's commitment doesn't stop with hiring people who have the
right skills and
experience. We hire individuals with a commitment to good client
relations. Our
corporatewide standard of responsive, creative, and courteous
customer service is put into
practice every day with every client.<P>

We also provide our employees with the resources and training
needed to stay abreast of
trends in information management practices and in specialized
content areas such as energy,
telecommunications, health, public housing, justice, and
education. Our ongoing commitment
to training, broadening, and strengthening staff skills results
in reduced turnover and helps
Aspen maintain continuity of service to our diverse customer
base.<P><BR>

<H2>Our commitment to technology</H2>

Technology is the underpinning of an organization's ability to
create and use information
effectively. One of Aspen's principal strengths is our investment
in new technologies to
achieve our clients  objectives. We help you determine the best
systems and technological
resources needed to increase productivity. Our technology support
services include:


<UL>
<LI>commercial off-the-shelf software integration
<LI>computer modeling and simulation 
<LI>customized software development
<LI>database development and administration
<LI>imaging solutions
<LI>network and systems design, training, and documentation
<LI>pen-based computer data collection
<LI>telecommunications services, including fax technologies and interactive voice recognition
<LI>desktop and electronic publishing
</UL>

Aspen's commitment to provide our clients with the latest
technologies includes our
comprehensive Internet services. We offer the knowledge,
experience, and services to create
and maintain high-quality Internet sites. We offer installation
and maintenance of Internet
connections, consulting, electronic publishing, systems support,
and customer service. We
can develop and manage your Internet presence; establish gopher,
telnet, and file transfer
protocol (ftp) sites; and design and develop World Wide Web home
pages and searchable
online databases. Our Internet services can expand and enhance
your organization's image
and help you convey information to those who need it -- quickly
and economically. <P><BR>

<H2>Innovative solutions that lead to bottom-line results</H2>

Throughout our history, Aspen has remained at the forefront by
using technology to manage
information. We invest in people and emerging technologies to
offer our clients the most
effective information management solutions. We recruit
results-oriented employees whose
entrepreneurial spirit and strong customer service orientation
have enabled Aspen to maintain
a leadership position in the information management field. Our
wide array of services offers
a cohesive yet flexible approach to managing a full range of
information needs. <P>

Aspen's innovative approach to information management continues
as we approach the 21st
century. Our commitment to help our clients provide the right
information to the right people
at the right time goes hand in hand with our pioneering spirit.
With Aspen as your partner,
you are guaranteed high-quality, innovative, and successful
programs that maximize the
benefits of one of your organization's most important assets --
information.<P><BR>


<H3>Print and Acrobat PDF formats of 
<A HREF="corpbro.pdf">Aspen's Corporate Brochure</A></H3>


A print copy of Aspen's corporate brochure can be provided to you
upon request. To receive a copy, please contact us by e-mail at 
<A HREF="MAILTO:info@aspensys.com">info@aspensys.com</A>
or (301) 738-6650.<P>

In addition, the brochure is also available as an Adobe Acrobat
PDF (portable document format) file. This format will enable you
to view and print the document in its original hardcopy form.
However, to be able to view Aspen's corporate brochure, you will need to
<A HREF="http://www.adobe.com/Acrobat/readstep.html">download</A> a copy of the Acrobat reader, which is free. <P>

