<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Internet Career Opportunities</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="White">

<H2><U><CENTER>Internet Career Opportunities</U></CENTER></H2>
<P> Listed below are positions currently open at Aspen. For further information, contact Kevin Attanasio at (301) 251-5443, e-mail <B><A HREF="MAILTO:kattanasio@aspensys.com">kattanasio@aspensys.com,</A></B>
or Hank Miller at (301) 251-5075, e-mail <B><A HREF="MAILTO:hmiller@aspensys.com">hmiller@aspensys.com.</A></B>
Please fax your resume with the appropriate reply code to (301) 251-5445.<P>

<B>Sales Representative</B><UL>
<LI>Highly motivated individual with proven sales background<BR>
<LI>Experience with Internet related services and markets</UL><P>

<B>Internet Systems Manager</B><BR>
Responsible for the management of an energetic team of analysts and developers and the development and administration of Internet applications and software. Requires:
   <UL>
   <LI>Proven success in management and development of Internet-based software solutions<BR>
<LI>Expertise in tracking and assessment of evolving Internet technology<BR>
<LI>Experience in assessment of evolving Internet technology<BR>
<LI>Strong communication and proposal writing skills<BR>
<LI>Excellent organization skills and ability to challenge/motivate technical staff
</UL><P>

<B>Internet Applications Developers</B><BR>
Work with cutting edge Internet applications and software, customize Web-based interactive features, and build database gateways and electronic commerce services. Requires:
   <UL>
<LI>Expertise with HTML, CGI, and Perl<BR>
<LI>Knowledge of Web server applications and/or online databases<BR>
<LI>Aptitude for learning and developing with new tools (i.e. Java and ActiveX)<BR>
<LI>UNIX or WindowsNT (preferred) background</UL><P>

<B>Internet Analyst</B><BR>
Experienced analysts to lead technical projects and people through the SDLC. Requires:
   <UL>
   <LI>Project management experience<BR>
<LI>Analytical talent with a broad-based skillset of Internet technology<BR>
<LI>Excellent organizational skills and leadership qualities<BR>
<LI>Proposal experience a plus</UL><P>

<B>Senior Network Engineer</B><BR>
Manage connectivity and security issues of an extensive wide area network including UNIX and NT-based Internet and Intranet services. Requires:
<UL><LI>UNIX network topology<BR>
<LI>TCP/IP and NFS</UL><P>

<B>Electronic Publishing/Systems Manager</B><BR>
Manage a team of Web site designers, LAN administrators, and electronic publishing specialists. Guide clients and staff in designing and developing outstanding electronic products. Requires:
   <UL>
<LI>Knowledge of current Internet technologies<BR>
<LI>Expertise in cross platform conversions, desktop publishing, and other topics that bear on electronic design and implementation</UL><P>

<B>Internet Product Coordinator</B><BR>
Work with clients, conceptualize and develop Web site schematics, edit electronic text and displays; and lead an Internet editing/QC team. Requires:
   <UL>
<LI>Knowledge of HTML, conversion packages, Web management software, and other tools</UL><P>

<B>Web Site Designers</B><BR>
Structure complex Web sites and create functional graphic interfaces. Devise effective solutions to address issues like screenloading, cross platform video display, graphics manipulation, and browser compatibility. Requires:
   <UL>
<LI>Excellent design skills and judgment<BR>
<LI>Experience with Illustrator 5.5/6.0 or Freehand, Photoshop, HTML 3.0, Netscape extensions, and knowledge of systems interface</UL><P>

<B>Web Graphics Specialists</B><BR>
Use HTML 3.0, Web management and conversion software. Write CGI scripting and Java applets. Requires:
   <UL>
<LI>Graphics skills and techniques</UL>

