<HEAD><TITLE>Aspen Portfolio</TITLE></HEAD> 

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#127CBB" VLINK="#CA0904"> 


<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=586 HEIGHT=78 BORDER=0 ALT="Portfolio" ALIGN=TOP SRC="isdpormt.gif">
<BR>
<BR>

<CENTER><table border=0 width=460 cellpadding=6 cellspacing=0>
<tr>
<td valign=top colspan=2>




<FONT SIZE=3>Aspen's Internet Services Division develops exciting Web sites for both commercial and government clients. Listed below are samples of just some of the successful sites we have created along with a description of the types of information and interactive features they offer. <P>
</td></tr>

<tr>
<td width=120>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://www.umm.edu"><IMG WIDTH=53 HEIGHT=108 BORDER=0 ALT="University of Maryland Medicine"ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE SRC="umlogo.gif"></A></CENTER>
</td>
<td>

<A HREF="http://www.umm.edu"><FONT SIZE=4><B>University of Maryland Medicine</B></FONT></A><P>

This 700-page, content-rich site is among the most comprehensive Aspen has produced to date.  Among the site's features are information on the Center's specialty services such as oncology, cardiology, neurocare, and transplantation; recent news releases and publications; a searchable database of job opportunities at the Medical Center; and a complete School of Medicine catalog for prospective medical students.  A searchable database of more than 1,000 Medical Center physicians and their specialties is currently in development.<P>
</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=100>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://www.fmbancorp.com"><IMG WIDTH=79 HEIGHT=38 BORDER=0 ALT="F&M Logo"ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE SRC="fmlogo.gif"></A></CENTER>
</td><td>

<A HREF="http://www.fmbancorp.com"><FONT SIZE=4><B>Farmers and Mechanics National Bank</B></FONT></A><P>

This site provides visitors with useful information on F&M's various business and personal banking services.  Among its features are a state-of-the-art Investment Analyzer to compare a personal portfolio to F&M's professionally managed portfolio; a Financial Profile form to help customers determine which services are right for them; financial calculators to assist in making sound investment decisions; and a Tip of the Day page for helpful financial hints.<P>
</td></tr>

<tr>
<td width=100>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<!-- Link Tag -->
<CENTER><A HREF="http://www.naima.org"><IMG WIDTH=101 HEIGHT=33 BORDER=0 ALT="NAIMA Logo"ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE SRC="naimalgo.gif"></A></CENTER>
</td><td>
<A HREF="http://www.naima.org"><FONT SIZE=4><B>North American Insulation Manufacturers Association (NAIMA)</B></FONT></A><P>

NAIMA's Web site allows homeowners and the construction industry to obtain important information on the safety and benefits of various American insulation products.  In addition, visitors can access the results of studies conducted on the safe production and use of these products.  Features of the site include access to recently-released press releases, news articles, and updates; a complete listing of all NAIMA publications along with a printable order form; and hot links to NAIMA member companies for more information about insulation products and services.<P>
</td></tr>

<tr>
<td width=100>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<!-- Link Tag -->
<CENTER><A HREF="http://www.genengnews.com"><IMG WIDTH=64 HEIGHT=64 BORDER=0 ALT="Genetic Engineering News Logo"ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE SRC="genlogo.gif"></A></CENTER>
</td><td>
<A HREF="http://www.genengnews.com"><FONT SIZE=4><B>Genetic Engineering News (GEN)</B></FONT></A><P>

GEN's Web site allows users to access selected highlights and abstracts from current and past editions of <I>Genetic Engineering News</I> magazine -- the preeminent source for news on biotechnology, bioregulation, bioprocess, bioresearch and technology transfer. Visitors to the site can subscribe to the publication using an online form; contact GEN staff directly; and access an advertising calendar.<P>

</td></tr>

<tr>
<td width=100>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<!-- Link Tag -->
<CENTER><A HREF="http://www.medlantic.mhg.edu/"><IMG WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=26 BORDER=0 ALT="Medlantic Healthcare Group Logo "ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE SRC="medlogo.gif"></A></CENTER>
</td><td>

<A HREF = "http://www.medlantic.mhg.edu/"><font size=4><b>Medlantic Healthcare Group</b></font></A><P>

The Medlantic Web site highlights the healthcare group's services and subsidiaries and provides valuable information for patients, physicians, the public, and insurers.  It offers health tips, descriptions of state-of-the-art medical procedures, lists of upcoming events, and visitor information, including maps and directions. <P>
</td></tr>

<tr>
<td width=100>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<!-- Link Tag -->
<CENTER><A HREF="http://www.co.mo.md.us"><IMG WIDTH=92 HEIGHT=90 BORDER=0 ALT="Montgomery County, MD Logo"ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE SRC="mclogo.gif"></A></CENTER>
</td><td>

<A HREF="http://www.co.mo.md.us"><FONT SIZE=4><B>Montgomery County, Maryland</B></FONT></A><P>

The Montgomery County Web site provides important and useful information for County residents, the media, and local government officials. Through the Web site, users are able to correspond with the County Executive, find contact information from the extensive phone directory, and obtain up-to-date press releases on County events and activities.<P>

</td></tr>

<tr>
<td width=100>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<CENTER><!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://www.hsus.org"><IMG WIDTH=110 HEIGHT=34 BORDER=0 ALT="HSUS Logo" ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE SRC="hsuslogo.gif"></A></CENTER>
</td>
<td>

<A HREF="http://www.hsus.org"><FONT SIZE=4><B>The Humane Society of the United States</B></FONT></A><P>

The Humane Society of the United States' Web Site provides information on the world's largest animal protection society, with more than 2.5 million constituents.  Among its features are a photo gallery, tips on pet care, a visitor feedback page, information on regional offices, and an electronic membership form.<P>

</td>
</tr>

<tr>
<td width=100>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<!-- Link Tag -->
<CENTER><A HREF="http://www.nagb.org"><IMG WIDTH=103 HEIGHT=103 BORDER=0 ALT="National Assessment Governing Board Logo" SRC="nagblogo.gif"></A></CENTER>
</td><td>

<A HREF="http://www.nagb.org"><FONT SIZE=4><B>National Assessment Governing Board (NAGB)</B></FONT></A><P>



This site contains detailed information on NAGB, the board established to set policy for the National Assessment of Educational Progress (NAEP).  The site lists NAGB meeting dates and other important events; contains NAGB publications, plus an online ordering form for obtaining print copies; and offers a visitor guestbook.  It also invites users to comment on NAGB's draft policy.<P>

</td></tr>

<tr>
<td width=100>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<!-- Link Tag -->
<CENTER><A HREF="http://www.cdcnac.org"><IMG WIDTH=110 HEIGHT=64 BORDER=0 ALT="CDC Logo"ALIGN=ABSMIDDLE SRC="cdclogo.gif"></A></CENTER>
</td><td>

<A HREF="http://www.cdcnac.org"><FONT SIZE=4><B>CDC National AIDS Clearinghouse</B></FONT></A><P>



Created for the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, the National AIDS Clearinghouse Web site is the most comprehensive source for HIV/AIDS-related information on the Internet. In addition to the on-line searchable database, it features video and audio clips of CDC public service announcements, an Internet poster gallery, surveys and questionnaires, and an online order form.  <P>

</td></tr>

<tr>
<td width=100>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
