<HTML> 

<HEAD><TITLE>Electronic Commerce and Secure Transactions</TITLE></HEAD> 

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#127CBB" VLINK="#CA0904"> 



<CENTER>
<!-- Graphic Tag -->
<IMG WIDTH=540 HEIGHT=72 BORDER=0 ALT="Electronic Commerce and Secure Transactions"ALIGN=TOP SRC="transmst.gif"></CENTER>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER><table border=0 width=460 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr>
<td>


<FONT SIZE=3><P>Estimates for electronic commerce transactions in the year 2000 are as high as $5 billion, up from less than $500 million today.  It is no longer a question of whether the Internet will become a viable market for conducting business, but more a matter of when you will start conducting business on the World Wide Web.</P>


<P>The advent of electronic commerce necessitates secure transaction capabilities to protect your customers' privacy.  The availability of a secure transaction feature allows organizations to safely transmit credit card numbers, application forms, confidential documents such as financial statements, employee records, and product ordering information across the Internet.</P>


<P>Electronic commerce and secure transaction capabilities will enable you to:</P>

<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI>increase your market recognition and penetration
<LI>provide around-the-clock operations and customer service
<LI>expedite delivery of products and services
</UL>


<P>Aspen Internet Services continually monitors emerging technologies in electronic commerce and secure transactions so that our clients benefit from the most up-to-date, technically advanced solutions available.  Our secure transaction features include:</P>


<BLOCKQUOTE><P><B><I>CyberCash</I></B>. This option provides merchants with the opportunity to offer goods and services over the Internet through the use of CyberCash software, which directly connects the customer transaction to the merchant's bank.  Customers simply download the software and establish an account with CyberCash by providing a credit card number across the Internet only at the initial installation.  Once customers have established an account, they can order products without sending their credit card information over the Internet.  Because there is no credit card information stored on the merchant's server, the liability and need for a secure server are reduced.</P>



<P><B><I>Secure Server Encryption</I></B>. Secure server environments allow for transmission of encrypted data packets via the TCP/IP communications protocol.  Using widely accepted standard security technologies, including RSA encryption keys and SSL protocol, the server receives and transmits information that is only viewable by the sender and/or receiver.  A secure server eliminates the possibility that such sensitive information is captured or viewed during transmission.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>


<P>For further information on these technologies call our toll-free number at (888) 851-7472 or e-mail us at <!-- MailTo Tag -->
<A HREF="MAILTO:info@aspensys.com">info@aspensys.com</A></P></FONT>




</td>
</tr>
</table>
<BR>
<BR>

