<HTML><HEAD>


<TITLE>About the ERIC Database</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="white" link="blue" vlink="teal" background="bgtile.gif"> 
<A NAME="abouttop"> </A>

<TABLE width=550 border=0 cellpadding=5>

<TR valign=top>
	<TD rowspan=100><A HREF = "navbar.map"><img border=0 src="navbar.gif" ISMAP></A></TD>
	<TD rowspan=1 colspan=3><FONT color="000080" SIZE=5><B>About the ERIC Database</B></FONT></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
	<TD colspan=3><HR size=5></TD>
</TR>


<TR>
	<TD colspan=3><h3>Table of Contents</h3></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
	<TD colspan=3>


<ol>


<li><a href=#10>What is the ERIC database?</a>


<li><a href=#20>What will you receive when you do an ERIC search?</a>


<li><a href="resumeed.html">Sample ERIC Document Resume</a>


<li><a href="resumeej.html">Sample ERIC Journal Resume</a>


</ol>
</TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD colspan=3>
<HR size=2>

<i>It is hoped that by reading this section a new user can have a better understanding of the structure of the ERIC database.  As stated below, the database contains more than 850,000 abstracts of documents and articles in the field of education. If you are searching for information and cannot locate anything, contact the <a href="barak.html">ERIC Clearinghouse</a> for subject help, or contact ACCESS ERIC at 1-800-LET-ERIC and we will be happy to refer you to the proper component.</i><hr>
</TD</TR>

<TR>
<TD colspan=3>

<h3><a name=10>What is the ERIC Database?</h3><P>

</TD</TR>

<TR>
<TD colspan=3>
<dl>


The ERIC database is the world's largest source of education information. The database contains more than 850,000 abstracts of documents and journal articles on education research and practice. You can access the ERIC database via the internet through <A HREF="http://ericir.syr.edu/ERIC/eric.html">World Wide Web</a>, via <a href="gopher://vmsgopher.cua.edu.:70/11gopher_root_eric_ae:[_search]">Gopher</a>, or via commercial vendors and public networks. You can also access printed ERIC abstracts in <a href="defrie.html"><i>Resources in Education</i></a> and <a href="defcije.html"><i>Current Index To Journals in Education</i></a>. The database is updated monthly (quarterly on CD-ROM), ensuring that the information you receive is timely and accurate.</dl>


</TD</TR>

<TR>
<TD colspan=3>

<h3><a name=20>What will you receive when you do an ERIC search?</a></h3> <p>

</TD</TR>

<TR>
<TD colspan=3>
<DL>


You will receive a <a href="defcit.html">citation</a> and an <a href="defabs.html">abstract</a>  to educational literature, this is referred to as a document <a href="defres.html">Resume</a>. There are two types of resumes in the ERIC database: <a href="resumeed.html">ERIC Documents (ED)</a> and <a href="resumeej.html">ERIC Journal Articles (EJ)</a>. <P>
<CENTER>
<Hr size=5><BR
clear=left>

</TD</TR>

<TR>
<TD colspan=3>

<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=-1>
	<A HREF = "barak.html">Links to all ERIC Sites</A> | 
