<HTML><HEAD>

<TITLE>ERIC Reference Directories</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="white" link="blue" vlink="teal" background="bgtile.gif"> 

<TABLE width=550 border=0 cellpadding=5>

<TR valign=top>
	<TD rowspan=100><A HREF = "navbar.map"><img border=0 src="navbar.gif" ISMAP></A></TD>
	<TD rowspan=1 colspan=3><FONT color="000080" SIZE=5><B>ERIC Reference Directories</B></FONT></TD></TR>

<TR>
	<TD colspan=3><HR size=5></TD>
</TR>


<TR>
	<TD colspan=3>
ACCESS ERIC develops a number of education-related directories,
 including an <EM>ERIC Directory of Education-Related Information
 Centers</EM>, a <EM>Directory of ERIC Resource Collections,</EM> and
 an <EM>ERIC Calendar of Education-Related Conferences</EM>. 
 <P>
 You can find the information included in the <EM>ERIC Directory of
 Education-Related Information Centers</EM> and the <EM>Directory of
 ERIC Resource Collections</EM> online in the <A
 HREF="http://oeri.ed.gov:8888/RESOURCES/Directory.htm">Education
 Resources Directory</A> hosted at the <A
 HREF="http://www.ed.gov">U.S. Department of Education's </A>Web site.
 <P>
 The <EM>1997 ERIC Calendar of Education-Related
 Conferences</EM> will soon be hosted in a BRS/NetAnswer database for
 easy searching by date, topic, and location. We are currently collecting the information for this
 database and will announce the online address as soon as it is
 available.
 <P>
 In addition, ACCESS ERIC is working on posting a searchable online
 publications catalog, a spin-off of our popular
 <EM>Catalog of ERIC Clearinghouse Publications</EM>, that will enable you to
 order more than 100 ERIC Clearinghouse publications online. The
 address of the prototype will be announced in Spring 1997.
 <P>
 All are of these reference and referral directories are currently
 available in print format. For more information about ordering the
 print products, contact ACCESS ERIC at <font
 color="#6600ff">1-800-LET-ERIC</font> or e-mail us at
 <A HREF="mailto:acceric@inet.ed.gov">acceric@inet.ed.gov</A>.
</TD</TR>

<TR>
<TD colspan=3>

