<title> Definition: Resources in Education</title>

<strong><i>Resources in Education</i></strong> also commonly refered to as <strong>RIE</strong>

is a paperbound monthly (12 issues per year) abstract journal that announces documents dealing with

all aspects of education, e.g., research reports, program descriptions, instruction materials, etc.  Approximately 13,000

documents are announced annually.  
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT19-B35-264</DOCNO>
