<title> Definition: ED</title>
The <strong>ERIC Document Number</strong> also known as the <strong>ERIC Accession Number</strong> 
is an identification number sequentially assigned to documents as they are processed.
The <strong>ED</strong> prefix alerts you to the fact that the document is 
probably available as microfiche or print copy of the microfiche from the 
ERIC Document Reproduction Service, 1-800-443-ERIC.  There are also
more then 900 locations that subscribe to the ERIC Document Microfiche
Collection.  To find if a library in your area has the collection  search the <a href="gopher://gopher.ed.gov:70/11/programs/ERIC/Publications/providers">Information Services Providers
Directory</a>.
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT19-B35-295</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA060-000330-B007-88</DOCOLDNO>
