Content-length: 450
</DOCHDR>
<title> Definition: CHN</title>

The <strong>Clearinghouse Accession Number</strong> abrivated <strong>CHN</strong>

is assigned by the ERIC Clearinghouse that indexed 

and abstacted the document or article.  After the <a href="defed.html">ED number</a> or <a href="defej.html">EJ number</a> is 

assigned this number is not used in the identification process of a document.  

It is helpful, however, to know what clearinghouse abstracted the item.
</DOC>
