<title> Definition: ISBN</title>

An <strong>Interternational Standard Book Number</strong> more commonly referred to as the <strong>ISBN Number</strong> is a

unique identifying number assigned by publishers to each distinct

book or monograph.  Journals have a simmilar number assigned to them called the <a href="defissn.html">ISSN</a>.
</DOC>
