<title> Definition: Target Audience</title>

<strong>Target Audience</strong>--documents and journal artices in ERIC are sometimes written for

paticular audiences.  ERIC cataloges these audiences in a special <strong>

Target Audience</strong> field. <i> The field is used when an author clearly specifies an 

intended audience; otherwise, it is left blank</i>.<p>

Eleven distinct audiences have been defined by ERIC, as follows:

<ul>

<li>Policymakers

<li>Researchers

<li>Practitioners

<uL><li>Administrators

<li>Teachers

<li>Counselors

<li>Media Staff

<li>Support Staff

</ul>

<li>Students

<li>Parents

<li>Community

</ul>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT19-B35-304</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA060-000330-B007-395</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.aspensys.com:80/eric/defdes.html 198.77.70.150 19970115035154 text/html 458
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
Date: Wed, 15 Jan 1997 03:47:31 GMT
Server: NCSA/1.5
Content-type: text/html
Last-modified: Mon, 18 Nov 1996 20:53:19 GMT
Content-length: 285
</DOCHDR>
<title> Definition: Descriptors</title>

<strong>Descriptors</strong> are subject terms that are assigned to the document by the 

abstractor.  The descriptors come from the <a href="defthe.html"><i>Thesaurus of ERIC Descrptors</i></a>.  Major descriptors are preceded

by an asterisk.
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT19-B35-305</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA060-000330-B007-431</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.aspensys.com:80/eric/defej.html 198.77.70.150 19970115035226 text/html 802
HTTP/1.0 200 Document follows
