</DOCHDR>
<title> Definition: EJ</title>

The <strong>ERIC Journal Article Number</strong> also known as the <strong>ERIC Accession Number</strong> 

is an identification number sequentially assigned to documents as they are processed.

The <strong>EJ</strong> prefix alerts you to the fact that the item is a journal article.

Copies of journal articles announced in ERIC can be found in library periodical

collections, through Interlibrary loan, or from article reproduction services, including the <a href="http://www.umi.com/ach/index.htm">UMI InfoStore</a> and the 

<a href="defveisi.html">Institute for Scientific Information</a>. 
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT19-B35-306</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA060-000330-B008-146</DOCOLDNO>
