<title> Definition: Annotation</title>

An <strong>Annotation</strong> is a brief (no more than 50 words)

notation of subject content. They are written for journal articles whose

titles are not sufficient to adequately convey their content.
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT19-B35-309</DOCNO>
