<HEAD>
<TITLE>Utility DSM Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 2:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: dsm.html -->






<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=7><B>Utility DSM Services</B></FONT><BR>




<FONT SIZE=5><I>DSM and Marketing Support Services for Electric and Gas Utilities</I></FONT><P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT><P><BR>








<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR>
<P>


<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen Systems Corporation provides the full range of demand 
side management (DSM) services to its utility customers.  These 
services include:
<P>
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI><A href="#planning">Program Planning 
and Design

<LI><A href="#operations">Program Operations</A>
<LI><A href="#evaluation">Program Evaluation</A>
<LI><A href="#dsm">DSM Technology</A>
<LI><A href="#support">Regulatory Support</A>
</UL><P><BR></FONT><P>




<H3><A name="planning">Program Planning and Design</H3></A><P>



<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen assists utilities in planning and designing their DSM, customer 
service, and marketing programs for residential, commercial, and/or 
industrial customers.</FONT>


<P><BR>
<H3><A name="operations">Program Operations</H3></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen assists utilities in operating their DSM programs or, if desired, 
Aspen can administer all or portions of the program.  This assistance can vary 
from administering rebate programs to providing DSM program 
marketing assistance.  Aspen can also provide temporary employees for 
short-term assistance in establishing and operating DSM programs.</FONT>

<P><BR>

<H3><A name="evaluation">Program Evaluation </H3></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen performs impact, process, and market evaluations of utility 
DSM programs in the residential, commercial, and industrial sectors.  To 
achieve these evaluations, Aspen uses a variety of methods, including focus 
groups, interviews, and surveys, coupled with state-of-the-art impact 
measurement methodologies.  To support its survey work, Aspen maintains a 
computer assisted telephone interview (CATI) capability and an in-house data 
entry facility.</FONT>


<P><BR>
<H3><A name="dsm">DSM Technology</H3></A>

<FONT SIZE=4><P>Aspen maintains expertise in state-of-the-art DSM technology and methods. 
 For example, Aspen has helped pioneer end-use metering techniques.  
Aspen staff are expert in sampling and statistical techniques -- staff 
members literally "wrote the book" for EPRI on sampling of utility customers.

</FONT>
<P><BR>
<H3><A name="support">Regulatory Support</H3></A>

<FONT SIZE=4><P>Aspen personnel have extensive experience in regulatory testimony before 
a variety of venues.  Aspen experts are prepared to testify before public 
service commissions and other bodies, and to assist in the technical support 
necessary to meet regulatory mandates, including justification for cost recovery, 
lost revenues, and DSM incentives.<P></FONT>


<FONT SIZE=4><B>For More Information Contact:</B>
<P>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>

Energy & Technology Services Division<BR>

962 Wayne Avenue, Suite 701<BR>

Silver Spring, MD  20910<BR>


<P><B>Telephone:</B>  (800) 638-2784     
<P>
<B>Fax:</B>  (301) 495-8562<P></FONT>
<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
