<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Customer Market and Load Research</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 2:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: resear.html -->

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=7><B>Customer Market and Load Research</B></FONT><BR>




<FONT SIZE=5><I>Full Service Market Research for Utilities</I></FONT><P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT>




<HR>
<P>






<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen Systems Corporation provides a wide range of services in support 
of customer and market research for utilities:  These include:
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#survey">Survey Research and Analysis</A>
<LI><A HREF="#market">Market Segmentation and Analysis</A>
<LI><A HREF="#focus">Focus Groups</A>
<LI><A HREF="#load">Load Research</A>
<LI><A HREF="#end">End-Use Analysis and Modeling</A>
</UL>
<P>
<B><A name="survey">Survey Research and Analysis</A></B>:  Aspen has extensive experience in 
all aspects of utility survey research.  Aspen staff are expert in survey design and 
analysis, and can develop any type of utility survey instrument needed.  Aspen's 
experience includes telephone, mail, and in-person data collection, including use of 
pen-based computer technology.
<P>
Our analytical staff can work with your market research team to develop the full 
range of research findings available from the data, or our survey staff will turn the data 
over to your team for your analysis.

<P>To assist in data collection, Aspen maintains a computer assisted telephone 
interview (CATI) capability as well as a Data Management Center for data entry and 
coding operations.  Our staff employs state-of-the-art statistical software, including SAS 
and SPSS.  Our staff is expert in univariate, bivariate, and multivariate data analysis 
for utility applications.

<P><B><A name="market">Market Segmentation and Analysis</A></B>:  Aspen will segment 
utility markets and provide analyses of market penetration probabilities by segment.  We 
can provide likelihood of marketing program successes.  Statistical techniques, 
including conjoint analysis, cluster analysis, and standard demographic analysis, are applied 
to estimate market response to utility programs and marketing efforts.
<P>
<B><A name="focus">Focus Groups</A></B>:  Aspen employs focus groups for its utility customers to 
identify qualitative and sometimes subtle effects of programs.  For this, we often use 
treatment and comparison groups of program participants and non-participants.  Focus groups 
are also used in identifying unanticipated difficulties in program development 
and implementation.  Aspen uses an in-house staff of trained focus group moderators 
with expertise in utility programs.
<P>
<B><A name="load">Load Research</A></B>:  Aspen is an industry leader in load research, including rate 
load research and customized metering project design.  The latter are designed to 
measure the impacts of various innovative rate strategies and targeted end-use programs.  
Aspen load research professionals are active contributors to advancing the state-of-the-art 
in load research, and have authored numerous publications on load research topics.  
Aspen provides utility clients with a range of load research services, including sample 
design, analysis, and field coordination of metering studies.
<P>
<P><B><A name="end">End-Use Analysis and Modeling</A></B>:  Aspen has extensive experience in 
end-use metering of residential, commercial, and industrial energy consumption for utilities. 
 Aspen has developed software to analyze consumption and demand patterns.  
Aspen can provide the necessary analysis of end-use load data, on a per-unit or overall basis. 
 Aspen has also developed models of energy consumption, resulting from 
proposed innovative rate strategies.<P>


<B>For More Information Contact:</B>
<P>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>

Energy & Technology Services Division<BR>

962 Wayne Avenue, Suite 701<BR>

Silver Spring, MD  20910<BR>

<P>
<B>Telephone:</B>  (800) 638-2784<P>

     

<P><B>Fax:</B>  (301) 495-8562</FONT><P>
