<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Statistical Analysis and Modeling</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 2:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: stat.html -->




<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=7><B>Statistical Analysis and Modeling</B></FONT><BR>




<FONT SIZE=5><I>Expertise to Meet Tomorrow's Industry Challenges</I></FONT><P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT>




<HR>
<FONT SIZE=4><P>
Aspen Systems Corporation provides clients with proactive solutions 
to management problems involving the collection, analysis, and 
management of data for marketing and demand side program design, forecasting, 
and evaluation.

<P>Aspen has extensive experience in:<P>


<UL>
<LI>Sample Design
<LI>Statistical Modeling
<LI>Conjoint Analysis
<LI>Forecasting
<LI>Building Simulation Modeling
</UL></FONT>







<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen possesses the personnel and expertise to meet all of your analytical needs.
<P>
Sample design may range from simple to complex, and utilizes 
techniques appropriate to the research application.  Aspen's sampling statisticians are 
nationally recognized for their expertise in complex utility sampling applications.

<P>Aspen employs conjoint analysis to ascertain customer preferences and the 
potential for market penetration of a given product, service, or rate.

<P>Building simulation modeling is used to predict the impact of changes on 
energy usage and demand patterns.  Available simulation tools used extensively by 
Aspen engineering staff include DOE-2, Micro-AXCESS, and ASEAM.

<P>Aspen possesses in-depth experience in utility forecasting applications.  Aspen 
has hands-on experience with many of the major end-use forecasting tools, such 
as COMMEND, CDMS, and REEPS.

<P>Statistical modeling entails behavioral and technical explanations based on sets 
of probabilities.  For example, Aspen has recently developed statistical methods 
to estimate the load impacts of peak activated rates.

<P>To provide these services, Aspen staff have expertise in a variety of software 
tools, including spreadsheets (Lotus and Excel), data base managers (dBase IV), 
statistical packages (SAS and SPSS), as well as specialized software for specific applications. 
 Aspen staff use both Apple and IBM-compatible microcomputer systems, as well 
as in-house computing resources for larger applications.

<P>To support our data analysis capabilities, Aspen maintains fully automated 
data collection and data entry installations.  These include an in-house computer 
assisted telephone interview (CATI) center.  Aspen has also developed and 
administered complex mail and on-site survey instruments for its clients, and maintains full 
survey capabilities.  To provide support for statistical and modeling projects requiring 
large volumes of data, Aspen has recently opened a Data Management Center to 
handle data entry and coding operations.  Aspen is also the industry leader in the 
application of pen-based computer technology for on-site data collection.





<P><B>For More Information Contact:</B><P></FONT>



<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>

Energy & Technology Services Division<BR>

962 Wayne Avenue, Suite 701<BR>

Silver Spring, MD  20910<BR>


<P><B>Telephone:</B>  (800) 638-2784     

<P><B>Fax:</B>  (301) 495-8562<P></FONT></FONT>
