<HEAD>
<TITLE>Utility Program Evaluation</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 3:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: eval.html -->



<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>



<FONT SIZE=7><B>Utility Program<BR>
 Evaluation</B></FONT><BR>


<FONT SIZE=5><I>Impact, Process, and Market Evaluations</I></FONT><P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT><P>

<P>



<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR>
<P>








<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen Systems Corporation, an early leader in the field of Demand 
Side Management (DSM) analysis, applies state-of-the-art techniques 
in performing evaluations of utility DSM programs.  Aspen's 
evaluation experience includes:
<P>
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#impact">Impact Evaluations</A>
<LI><A HREF="#process">Process Evaluations</A>
<LI><A HREF="#market">Market Evaluations</A>
</UL></FONT><P><BR>

<H3><A name="impact">Impact Evaluation</A></H3><P>


<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen has extensive experience in performing impact evaluations for its utility 
clients.  An impact evaluaion is designed to determine the energy and 
demand savings, as well as other benefits which result from the program.  To 
calculate program benefits, both load and energy impacts must be determined.  
Free ridership must be ascertained.  Program costs must be known or estimated.  
Aspen is expert at applying a variety of evaluation techniques, including 
statistical, engineering, simulation, and metering approaches to utility DSM 
program evaluations.</FONT>

<P><BR>

<H3><A name="process">Process Evaluation</A></H3><P>


<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen has performed numerous process evaluations for its clients.  
Process evaluations review program administrative and operational considerations.  
They assess implementation effectiveness including market efficiency, 
customer acceptance, and trade ally impact as well as program flexibility and response times.

<P>Aspen offers several innovative approaches to DSM process evaluations, 
including use of "paired" focus groups, development of specialized telephone 
survey instruments, and techniques for measuring the effects of "information 
only" programs.</FONT>
<P><BR>



<H3><A name="market">Market Evaluation</A></H3>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=4><P>Market evaluations generate data on customer understanding and acceptance 
of program offerings.  Market evaluations typically focus on the impacts of 
specific marketing activities on utility program objectives. They provide the 
information needed to design more effective marketing strategies and campaigns.
<P>
Aspen's full range of market research and survey services offer utilities all of 
the capabilities needed for full-service market evaluations.  Our market evaluations 
of DSM programs that we ourselves have operated have revealed 
numerous marketing and non-marketing actions that served to accelerate or reward 
customer participation.  Our experience as a DSM program operations firm gives us 
unique qualifications to perform market evaluations.

<P>Aspen is fully qualified to conduct impact, process, and market evaluations for 
all types of utility programs -- residential, commercial, and industrial.  Our 
highly skilled staff has the statistical, computer, survey, focus group, and 
engineering experience necessary to conduct all phases of evaluation research.  Aspen 
literally "wrote the book" on DSM evaluation for the utility industry (EPRI Publication 
EM 5706, <I>Program Monitoring</I>).<P>



<B>For More Information Contact:</B>
<P>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>

Energy & Technology Services Division<BR>

962 Wayne Avenue, Suite 701<BR>

Silver Spring, MD  20910<BR>

<P>
<B>Telephone:</B>  (800) 638-2784     
<P>
<B>Fax:</B>  (301) 495-8562<P></FONT>
