<HEAD>
<TITLE>Load Research Outsourcing</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 2:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: outsour.html -->




<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=7><B>Load Research<BR>
 Outsourcing</B></FONT><BR>




<FONT SIZE=5><I>Expertise to Handle All of Your Load Research Needs</I></FONT><P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT><P>



<HR>
<P>



<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen Systems Corporation is a recognized expert in the field of 
load research, applying state-of-the-art techniques to perform all facets of 
a load research program.  Aspen's load research experience includes:
<P>
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#sample">Sample Design</A>
<LI><A HREF="#data"> Data Editing and Validation</A>
<LI><A HREF="#analysis">Data Analysis</A>
</UL></FONT>


<P><BR>
 <H3><A name="sample">Sample Design</A></H3><P>



<FONT SIZE=4><P>Aspen has extensive utility industry experience in performing sample designs 
for load research, as well as for DSM and market research.  Load research 
sample designs must take into account multiple objectives in the changing utility market. 
 Sophisticated designs are necessary to ensure that all of these objectives are met. 
 Aspen is familiar with the proper statistical application of state-of-the-art 
sample design techniques, having written several EPRI guidebooks on sampling.</FONT>
<P>
<BR>
<H3><A name="data">Data Editing and Validation</A></H3>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=4><P>Aspen has performed numerous projects requiring editing and validation 
of interval load research data.  Interval load research data requires 
extensive checking, especially during project startup, to ensure that the data recorded 
is reasonable and what is expected.  This is especially true of end-use data, 
for example, which may not be flagged by the software for any apparent problems, 
but may have multiplicative problems built-in due to incorrectly reported 
field information.
<P>
Aspen has written several monographs on the editing and validation of utility 
data for clients.  These monographs indicate the guidelines to use to determine if 
data can be classed as valid for analysis purposes.</FONT>
<P>
<BR>
<H3><A name="analysis">Data Analysis</A></H3>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen has been involved in the analysis of utility load data for over 12 years.  
The data analysis of interval load data involves the use of both &quot;canned&quot; 
analysis software, as well as programming in statistical software languages for 
ad-hoc analyses.  Aspen has extensive experience in analyzing load data using 
the techniques avaliable in canned software packages, as well as writing 
computer code to analyze load data for DSM program evaluation, market research, and 
other utility functions.

<P>Aspen is fully qualified to take over the sample design, data collection, data 
editing and validation, and analysis of all types of utility load data.  Our highly 
skilled staff includes the statistical, economic, engineering, and computer 
programming skills necessary to conduct all phases of a load research program.  This 
highly skilled staff includes nationally renowned sample design experts, as well as 
former utility load research personnel available to work directly on utility load 
research projects.

<P>Outsourcing to Aspen provides complete flexibility to scale up or down the 
load research effort.  For example, utilities facing a rate case or IRP filing can call 
on Aspen to undertake extensive load data analysis activities associated with 
these efforts without the need to divert staff from other critical activities.  Aspen 
also offers a variety of other services, such as data processing systems support and 
load research hardware and software purchase recommendations.<P></FONT>


<FONT SIZE=4><B>For More Information Contact:</B>
<P>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>

Energy & Technology Services Division<BR>

962 Wayne Avenue, Suite 701<BR>

Silver Spring, MD  20910<BR>

<P>
<B>Telephone:</B>  (800) 638-2784     
<P>

<B>Fax:</B>  (301) 495-8562<P></FONT>


