<HEAD>
<TITLE>Technical Support Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 2:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: tech.html -->




<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=7><B>Technical Support<BR>
 Services</B></FONT><BR>




<FONT SIZE=5><I>Short-term or On-going Services for Utilities and Government</I></FONT><P>






<HR>
<P>









<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen Systems Corporation provides technical support to the utility 
industry and to government agencies at the federal, state, and local levels.  
This support takes three general forms:<P>


<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI>Technical Support Services
<LI>Technology Transfer
<LI>Meetings Management
</UL>
<P>





Aspen provides clients with technical and analytical support services. This support ranges 
from development of survey instruments and data entry and management to sophisticated 
statistical analysis, engineering analysis, economic analysis, graphics creation, and report preparation.

<P>Aspen has highly skilled quantitative analysts and statisticians on its permanent staff. 
Aspen maintains IBM-compatible and Apple microcomputers as well as in-house 
computing resources for use in analytical tasks.  Aspen analysts are supported by sophisticated 
computing resources, a Computer Assisted Telephone Interviewing (CATI) survey facility, and a 
Data Management Center.  Aspen analysts are proficient with a variety of software,  including 
SAS, SPSS, Lotus, Excel, dBase, and a variety of other commonly used programs.
<P>
<B>Engineering Analysis</B>:  Aspen engineering staff are experienced in all facets of 
energy engineering, which includes detailed engineering analysis of advanced energy technologies. 
 Our engineers offer clients expertise in a range of supply side technologies, 
including advanced fossil energy, renewable, and electro-technologies.  Aspen engineering staff 
have been retained by utilities and major technology vendors to analyze technical, 
environmental, and cost performance for a range of technological options.  On the demand side, 
Aspen's engineering group offers clients expertise in state-of-the-art end-use technology 
assessment, with special emphasis on energy efficient lighting, HVAC and energy management systems.
<P>
<B>Economic Analysis</B>:  Aspen economists offer hands-on expertise in cost benefit 
analysis, market penetration modeling, economic impact studies, and econometric analysis.  Aspen 
staff economists work closely with our engineering and program design staff to offer 
clients integrated technology assessment services.
<P>
<B>Program/Policy Analysis:  </B>Aspen policy analysts have been involved in the development 
and analysis of energy policy since the 1973 Oil Embargo.  Aspen policy staff have contributed 
to major federal and state energy policy initiatives, including R&amp;D planning, regulatory 
analysis, and the development of policy options on both the supply and demand side.  Aspen's clients 
in this area include the U.S. Department of Energy, the Environmental Protection Agency, 
the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development, the U.S. Air Force, and various 
state level energy research and policy organizations.  Aspen can offer clients both in the public 
and private sector integrated technical support services via the development of 
multidisciplinary project teams with expertise in engineering, economics, and policy analysis.

<P>Legislation in the last decade has mandated that federal agencies make access to new 
energy and environmental technologies easier for the private sector.  
<P>
Aspen has assisted government agencies and industry associations in energy 
related technology transfer.  This assistance includes identification of potential trade associations 
and publications for technology transfer, inventory control of materials, marketing of 
technologies, and the preparation of materials directed at the lay public.

<P><B>Meetings Management</B>:  Aspen assists  government agencies (as well as private sector 
entities)  in  the  planning and management of conferences and meetings.  Aspen 
provides assistance across the full  spectrum  of meeting  requirements,  including identifying 
and securing  the  site, planning   meeting   space,  menu preparation, and, if desired,  
identification of  meeting participants and speakers.<P>



<B>For More Information Contact:</B>
<P>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>

Energy & Technology Services Division<BR>

962 Wayne Avenue, Suite 701<BR>

Silver Spring, MD  20910<BR>


<P><B>Telephone:</B>  (800) 638-2784     
