<HEAD>
<TITLE>Energy Audit Programs</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 2:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: audit.html -->



<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>



<FONT SIZE=7><B>Energy Audit Programs</B></FONT><BR>


<FONT SIZE=5><I>Energy Audits and On-site Surveys</I></FONT><P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT><P>

<P><BR>
<BR>




<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR>
<P>







<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen Systems Corporation provides a wide range of audit services to 
the utility industry.  These services include:
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI>Audit Program Design
<LI>Commercial Audits
<LI>Industrial Audits
<LI>Residential Audits
<LI>One-Stop Audits
<LI>On-Site Surveys
<LI>Pen-Based Automated Data Collection
<LI>Program Integration
<LI>Marketing-Based Audit Programs
<LI>Auditor Training
<LI>Audit Program Evaluation
</UL>
<P>Utilities recognize the value of offering energy audits to their customers as a way 
to encourage efficiency, facilitate participation in other utility programs, and 
enhance customer service and marketing.
<P>
Aspen will design, operate, monitor, and evaluate an energy audit program tailored to 
a utility's customers without the utility having to invest in additional in-house staff 
or software resources to do so.

<P>Aspen serves all of a utility's customers -- residential, commercial, and industrial.

<P>Aspen features staff experienced in all phases of energy audit programs and 
efficient technologies.  These personnel will design the energy audit program to suit a 
utility's needs.  Our philosophy is to provide a customized program the way the utility wants 
it, as opposed to forcing your program to meet a pre-determined format.

<P>Aspen's engineers are available to support the program on a day-to-day basis.  Our 
field staff are degreed engineers with experience in conducting energy audits and 
on-site surveys.

<P>Because of Aspen's extensive experience with utility rebate programs, we are 
often able to integrate audit and rebate programs.  This allows a utility to take advantage 
of the synergy between the two similar programs.  Combined reporting and tracking 
are just two of the benefits of this integration.

<P>Aspen's Program Tracking software, DSMonitor&#153; , and our companion 
product, MarketNavigator&#153; , are designed to capture all data required for evaluations 
responsive to regulatory requirements, and to provide excellent customer service.  Our data 
entry procedures ensure quality assurance checks of all data entered.

<P>Aspen also conducts on-site surveys of commercial, industrial, and residential facilities. 
 Whether collecting end-use nominal performance ratings or conducting 
thorough building surveys for complex computer simulations, Aspen engineers are trained 
for efficient and accurate data acquisition.   Our survey results range from 
simple organized site data to hourly end-use demand estimates by building type 
and geographical region.  Aspen offers the flexibility and experience for a variety of 
utility survey objectives.

<P>Aspen Systems provides a wide range of additional services to the utility industry.  
Our analytical expertise, ranging from market research to econometric 
evaluations, enhances the services we are able to offer our utility clients.  Because Aspen 
has conducted numerous evaluations of utility programs, we know which data must 
be collected in order to evaluate a program, and we understand the value of high 
quality data.

<P>At Aspen, your customers are our customers.  We provide the quality and 
customer service you demand for your valued customers.<P>


