<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Distribution and Fulfillment Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 2:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: dist.html -->


<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=7><B>Distribution and Fulfillment Services</B></FONT><BR>


<FONT SIZE=5><I>DSM Distribution Services for Utilities</I></FONT><P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT><P>






<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR>
<P>



<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen Systems Corporation maintains two Distribution and Fulfillment 
Centers which perform the mailing and distribution services for all of 
Aspen's clients.  The services include:
<P>
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI>Short-term Storage
<LI>Subscription and Mailing List  Services
<LI>Inventory Support
<LI>Messenger Services
<LI>Assembly and Collation
<LI>Shipping Services
</UL>


Aspen's Distribution and Fulfillment Centers can perform a variety of services 
for utility clients, including distribution of compact fluorescent lamps and other 
lighting products, catalogs, newsletters, and other DSM-related and utility 
marketing products.
<P>
The Centers are staffed by a team of 49 trained specialists.  The Centers have 
over 92,000 square feet of space with a storage capacity of 5,000 pallets.  In a recent 
three month period, the Centers processed more than 263,000 orders and distributed 
more than 13 million items.

<P>The Centers house employee offices and a warehouse.  The addition of 
state-of-the-art material handling equipment has produced a highly efficient 
distribution operation.  For example, the shipping area has a scissor lift that lowers the 
loading platform to accommodate delivery trucks.  Other essential equipment includes:
<P>
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI>a conveyor system,
<LI>a pallet flow rack,
<LI>a weight-count scale, and
<LI>a high-speed labeling machine.
</UL>
<P>
The distribution and fulfillment process is done accurately and quickly.  The 
order entry area is where mail sorting and data entry functions take place.  Incoming 
orders arrive and are sorted and divided into batches.  The data entry specialists enter 
this information into a computer database and coordinate the production of mailing labels. 
 Once the order and labels are printed, a quality control check is performed.  
The orders are then sorted and divided for processing.
<P>
<P>When a shipment of items arrives at the receiving area, a specialist checks it by 
type of item and quantity.  The shipment is then assigned a location and stored.  A 
location card is placed with the shipment, and a copy of the card is filed in number 
sequence in a master file.  The information is also entered into a computerized record.
<P>
Order processing is done by the order processors.  To fill an order, the 
processors collect the appropriate items and place them in a bin, which is sent along 
the conveyor system to the quality control station.  (Large orders requiring 10 or 
more cartons are placed on pallets and prepared for freight shipping.)  At the quality 
control station, a processors checks the quantity and verifies the item ordered.  The items 
then continue along the conveyor to the packaging work station.

<P>Once packaged, the order continues along to the metering area.  Here 
metering experts weigh the package on a scale which determines whether U.P.S. or the 
postal service is the more economical method of shipping.  On a daily basis, the 
metering system records and summarizes  by contract the method of shipment, total number 
of packages shipped, and total costs.

<P>Aspen's Distribution and Fulfillment Centers offer utility and government clients 
a highly efficient means of distributing compact fluorescent lamps and other 
products and literature for fulfillment, marketing, customer service, or technology 
transfer purposes.
<P>
<B>For More Information Contact:</B><P>



Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>

Energy & Technology Services Division<BR>

962 Wayne Avenue, Suite 701<BR>

Silver Spring, MD  20910<BR>


<P><B>Telephone:</B>  (800) 638-2784     
<P>
<B>Fax:</B>  (301) 495-8562
