<HEAD>
<TITLE>Market Navigator</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 2:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: marnav.html -->

<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=7><B>Market Navigator&#153;</B></FONT><BR>




<FONT SIZE=5><I>Marketing Tracking System</I></FONT><P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT><P>

<P><BR><BR>






<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR>
<P>







<FONT SIZE=4>The issue is not whether your company offers 
individualized programs for each customer, but how to keep track of every 
marketing activity for each individual customer, especially when you are 
outsourcing program operations.  That's what MarketNavigator&#153; does.

<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI>Tracks Detailed Customer Information

<LI>Coordinates Project and Program Management

<LI>Advanced Scheduling Features
</UL>


<P>

It is a fact that the best way to serve your customers would be to create 
an individual market strategy for each and every customer.  The amazing thing 
is that with the wide variety of marketing programs offered by your 
utility company, and with the possibility for customers to choose to participate 
in multiple programs, you are probably already close to doing just that.  The 
issue is not whether your company offers individualized programs for each 
customer, but how to keep track of every marketing activity for each individual customer.

<P>Aspen's MarketNavigator&#153; operates on the principle that customers are 
people -- not revenue meters attached to service sites.  Even your largest key account is 
a person on the other end of a telephone call.  Human memory is linked to 
events, and MarketNavigator&#153; operates by tracking events that people remember. 
 Aspen uses MarketNavigator&#153; to coordinate project and program 
management, and to insure that contacts with your customers are recorded in complete detail.

<P>Aspen uploads a text extract of information from your billing file 
into MarketNavigator&#153; --  things like customer name (firm or residential), 
contact name, service address and mailing address if different, telephone 
number, customer service representative and telephone number, C&ISIC code, 
C&I market segment and strata, and demand and energy information.  
Often marketing and service representatives have never even had ready access 
to demand and usage information -- now they do.  One strength 
of MarketNavigator&#153;  is that you can load customers for specific programs 
or projects -- such as annual audit projects, market surveys, or energy 
programs which makes it an excellent tool for single program management.  
However, customer events can be recorded for multiple programs and projects 
so MarketNavigator&#153; can load <I>all</I> of your customers.  You can display 
events related to programs, or view a complete history of all customer events.  
Using this information as a base record, MarketNavigator&#153; then goes to work.

<P>As a tool, MarketNavigator&#153; can summarize customer contacts for a 
quick-view chronology, print out a customer history or energy use and demand 
profile, and maintain contact information for residential, commercial, industrial, 
or agricultural accounts.  MarketNavigator&#153; can track customer enrollment 
in multiple programs.  The reports and views are all in the same familiar 
format, accessed by clicking on-screen buttons or menu items.  MarketNavigator&#153; 
can be used by project managers, program managers, marketing representatives, 
and service representatives.

<P>Aspen currently uses MarketNavigator&#153; to manage Aspen program 
operations contracts.  It is also in use at the contracting utility.  That is the key.  We 
use MarketNavigator&#153;.  As users <I>and</I> developers, we were very careful to 
make sure that MarketNavigator&#153; could perform or be adapted for everything 
we need now -- and in the future.  MarketNavigator&#153; has been adapted to 
include scheduling features to support projects.  It has mapped related 
program activity -- such as audit programs linked to equipment retrofit programs 
that utilize the audit recommendations as the basis for rebate applications.

<P>
<B>For More Information Contact:</B>
<P>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>

Energy & Technology Services Division<BR>

962 Wayne Avenue, Suite 701<BR>

Silver Spring, MD  20910<BR>
<P>



<B>Telephone:</B>  (800) 638-2784     
<P>
<B>Fax:</B>  (301) 495-8562</FONT><P>
