<HEAD>
<TITLE>DSMonitor</TITLE> 
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/8/96 2:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: dsmon.html -->

<!-- Generation of PM publication page 1 -->
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0 SRC="asplogo.gif"><P><P>
<BR>

<FONT SIZE=7><B>DSMonitor&#153;</B></FONT><BR>




<FONT SIZE=5><I>DSM  and Marketing Program <BR>
Performance-Based Tracking System</I></FONT><P><BR CLEAR=RIGHT><BR>
<P>

<!-- Horizontal Line Tag -->
<HR>
<P>







<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen Systems Corporation is both a developer and user of computer 
based DSM and marketing program tracking and control software. 
 Aspen's DSMonitor&#153; Program Tracking and Control software is 
a proven application used for:<P>
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<LI>DSM Program Operations Support
<LI>Utility DSM Programs 
<LI>Rigorous Program Evaluation 
</UL><P>

<P>Aspen's DSMonitor&#153; is a computer application developed for use in 
both traditional file server and client server environments.  Running under 
both DOS-text based and Graphical (GUI) interfaces, it is a powerful tool for 
both large and small DSM programs or utility companies.

<P>DSMonitor&#153; provides program managers with the capability to 
track program participation through all stages of your program design.  A 
detailed activity log that provides participant customer and program audit trails 
is maintained through a fully normalized and relational database system. 
 DSMonitor&#153; tracks equipment incentive and direct install programs, 
audit or building characteristics surveys, and hybrid programs such as 
new construction or weatherization programs.  Customers can be sorted 
by activity with reports being generated for activities required, such 
as inspections, installations, or incentive payment, to help manage 
your program implementation.

<P>Aspen Systems developed DSMonitor&#153; to support a multi-million 
dollar commercial and industrial equipment replacement incentive program in 
the state of New York.  The system was developed in an evolutionary 
manner over a period of eight years, beginning in 1987.  As cost recovery 
incentive requirements were set in place, DSMonitor&#153; was adapted to meet the 
strict evaluation requirements for program cost justification.  Using user 
defined values for program measures, DSMonitor&#153; develops savings estimates 
from engineering algorithms that accept variables for free-ridership, 
transmission and distribution loss, and time differentiated rates. Savings 
estimates developed with DSMonitor&#153; have been used  in Public Service 
Commission filings that have resulted in the submitting utility receiving the 
maximum allowable cost recovery incentive in each year.  Statistical summaries 
for user specified periods of performance are generated on demand.

<P>Aspen Systems is an internationally recognized leader in DSM and 
utility marketing programs.  Aspen's experience in DSM led us to the 
conclusion that a better system could be developed.  We are also an 
internationally recognized leader in systems development with our client list including 
the United States Navy and Army, MCI, the Marriott Corporation, and 
many others.
<P>
<P>DSMonitor&#153; is a fully operational, customizable DSM program 
tracking application with a proven track record that boasts evaluators and managers 
as users.  Implementing DSMonitor&#153; is a viable solution to your 
program tracking needs.<P>



<B>For More Information Contact:</B>
<P>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>

Energy &amp; Technology Services Division<BR>

962 Wayne Avenue, Suite 701<BR>

Silver Spring, MD  20910<BR>

<P>
<B>Telephone:</B>  (800) 638-2784     
<P>
