<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Aspen's "Financing Choice Program"</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<!-- System: Aspen Systems Corporation -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/14/96  -->
<!-- Source File: choice.html -->

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">


<IMG align=left hspace=10 SRC="aspnbug3.gif">
<H2>Aspen's "Financing Choice Program" 
Replaces Rebates and Promotes Customer Loyalty</H2><P>


     <FONT SIZE=4>As electric utilities prepare for open competition in the 
electricity market, many are reducing or discontinuing their DSM 
rebate programs.  But they understand that helping their customers 
manage operating costs will be a critical element to retaining customer 
loyalty and attracting new customers in an era of competition.  Aspen offers 
its &quot;Financing Choice Program&quot; to give utilities a  weapon to use in 
the competitive market.
<P>         The Financing Choice Program perpetuates and attracts 
customer loyalty by perpetuating the proactive image created by utilities 
offering rebate programs.  It provides customers two services that 
a traditional loan program does not:


<BLOCKQUOTE><I>The Financing Choice Program identifies and offers the type 
of financing that best matches customers' needs.  The types of financing 
range from traditional commercial loans to energy savings performance contracts.
<P>
The Program eliminates "hassle" by handling all of the financing 
and contracting paperwork except the actual signatures, if the 
customer requests it.  Efficiency through financing is made easier than it 
was with rebates where the customer had to find a contractor and fill out 
an application.</I></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
Aspen, a turnkey operator of utility rebate programs, designed 
the Financing Choice Program using its experience as a fulfiller of 
customer rebate applications and information clearinghouses.  The Financing 
Choice Program can be tailored to your goals and budget.  Its complete range 
of services should cost much less than a tenth of the cost of a rebate 
program, and it can also be used to promote electrotechnologies.
<P>         The utility is not required to buy-down the market interest rate 
or provide loan funds.  Aspen will incorporate utility funding, however, 
if requested.  Aspen uses commercial banks in the utility's service area 
as one source of market financing.  
<P><B>For More Information
</FONT></B><P>




<FONT SIZE=4>Aspen operates the Financing Choice Program as a turnkey program.  
For further information, call Philip Mihlmester at (423) 482-2721.</FONT><P>


