<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Audits as Marketing/Customer Service Tool</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<!-- System: Aspen Systems Corporation -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Greg -->
<!-- Last Update: 5/14/96  -->
<!-- Source File: audits.html -->

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">


<IMG align=left hspace=10 SRC="aspnbug3.gif">
<H2>Audits as Marketing/Customer 
Service Tool</H2><P>
         <FONT SIZE=4>Utility-sponsored audits boomed in popularity during the 
DSM era.  They were seen primarily as a mechanism to identify load 
reduction opportunities.  Over time, however, utilities have learned that 
audit programs and comprehensive large customer audits can provide 
many other valuable services as well.
<P>     <B>Market Research.</B>  Aspen has performed market research on 
customer audit data for two East Coast utilities 
to determine electrotechnology market penetration, end-use energy 
intensities, and typical gas customer floorspace 
by building type.
<P>


<B>Customer Service.</B>  In the Midwest, Aspen runs an audit program where each audited customer -- over 700 per year -- is called by a utility marketing representative to follow up, confirm customer satisfaction, and identify load growth opportunities such as heat pumps.<P>


	<B>Load Growth.</B>  At least one major southeast utility uses audits as a load growth tool.  They believe that anything they can do to improve customer efficiency will improve the chances of customer growth, expansion, or relocation of other divisions into the utility's service territory.  Audits that recommend fuel switching to heat pumps or other electric options is another more conventional load growth opportunity.<P>


	Customers believe that their utilities are experts not just at supplying power, but also on energy-using equipment.  As the market becomes more competitive, maintaining this customer trust is an important value-added service.<P>



<B>For More Information</B><P>


<I>For more information on how Aspen can perform audits in your service territory, please contact Jon Maxwell at (800) 638-2784.</I><P></FONT><P>


<A HREF = "jan1996.html#inthis"><IMG align=left border=0 hspace=0 vspace=5 SRC="redbar.gif"><BR clear=left>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
