<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>Health Care Information on the Internet</TITLE></HEAD> 
<!-- System: Aspen Systems Corporation -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Linda -->
<!-- Last Update: 09/16/96  -->
<!-- Source File: qdprod.html -->
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 
<IMG align=left hspace=3 SRC="aspnbug2.gif">

<H2>Health Care Information on the Internet</H2>


<FONT SIZE=4><B><P>Among the rapidly growing wealth of information available on the Internet are a wide range of health care-related Web sites. Here are some recommendations to get you started:</P></B></FONT>
<BR CLEAR=LEFT>
<UL>
<LI>Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) National AIDS Clearinghouse -- <A HREF="http://www.cdcnac.org">http://www.cdcnac.org</A> -- links to other CDC and AIDS-related online services and publications.
<BR><BR>
<LI>Medscape -- <A HREF="http://www.medscape.com">http://www.medscape.com</A> -- covers specialties, journals, and meetings and conferences, and has a self-assessment feature called "exam room."
<BR><BR>
<LI>Yahoo Search -- <A HREF="http://www.yahoo.com/Health/Health_Care">http://www.yahoo.com/Health/Health_Care</A> -- allows you to narrow the scope of your search to subjects indexed under "health" and "health care." From there you can do a key word search or further narrow your search to companies, conferences, institutes, policies, professionals, and others. 
<BR><BR>
<LI>Care Net -- <A HREF="http://www.care.net">http://www.care.net</A> -- a health care network that supports a health care provider directory (by specialty), lists health care network services, health care-related Web sites, and more.
<BR><BR>
<LI>World Health Organization (WHO) -- <A HREF="http://www.who.ch">http://www.who.ch</A> -- provides information about WHO programs, world health reports, newsletters, and more.
<BR><BR>
<LI>National Institutes of Health (NIH) -- <A HREF="http://www.nih.gov">http://www.nih.gov</A> -- provides information on NIH conferences and workshops, as well as information about NIH-supported research, general health information, and scientific resources. In addition, NIH has a fully developed gopher site -- <A HREF="gopher://gopher.nih.gov:70">gopher://gopher.nih.gov:70</A> -- that provides access to specific subjects such as cancer and AIDS information.
<BR><BR>
<LI>Health Care Financing Administration -- <A HREF="http://www.hcfa.gov">http://www.hcfa.gov</A> -- gives detailed information on the Medicare and Medicaid programs.
</UL>



<P>Listservs on the Web are also a valuable source of health care information. Below are two sites that have health care-related listservs that anyone can join:</P>


<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://tile.net/listserv/medicine.html">http://tile.net/listserv/medicine.html</A>.<BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.lsoft.com/lists/listref.html">http://www.lsoft.com/lists/listref.html</A> (allows you to search lists by key word).
</UL>

Aspen Systems Corporation's Internet Services Division provides the turnkey development support for organizations creating or maintaining an Internet presence. We help organizations create practical, results-oriented sites that meet key objectives such as streamlining operations, improving communications, and promoting goods and services effectively.
<P><I>For more information, call Karen Misita at
(301) 738-6650 or e-mail us at <A HREF="MAILTO:info@aspensys.com">info@aspensys.com</A>.</I><P>

