<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>An Interview with Meryl Bloomrosen</TITLE></HEAD> 
<!-- System: Aspen Systems Corporation -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Linda -->
<!-- Last Update: 09/16/96  -->
<!-- Source File: intcont.html -->
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"> 
<IMG align=left hspace=3 SRC="aspnbug2.gif">

<H2>An Interview with 
Meryl Bloomrosen (continued from <A HREF="intrview.html">Spring 1996 issue</A>)</H2>

<FONT SIZE=4><I><B>Question: How does Aspen improve the 
information management practices of a health care organization?</B></I></FONT>

<P>Aspen has helped many health care organizations evaluate their information management practices by conducting operational assessments of their information management processes. Aspen has also helped organizations with strategic information resources management planning. In addition, Aspen has helped organizations with the design, development, and implementation of enterprise-wide health information management systems.</P>

<P>Another significant way Aspen has helped health care organizations improve their information management practices is by looking at the outcomes of those practices. Those outcomes include the satisfaction of their customers with information received, and the quality and integrity of the data.</P>

<P>Aspen has conducted comprehensive user needs assessments and satisfaction surveys, and has provided independent, expert assessments of the quality and accuracy of coded and abstracted data. </P>

<FONT SIZE=4><I><B>Question: How can Aspen benefit a health care organization?</B></I></FONT>

<P>Health care organizations can benefit from using our services because we offer technical support in areas where they often need additional help to meet staffing shortages or fill critical vacancies. Our health information staff include full-time and part-time employees with training and hands-on experience in ICD-9-CM and CPT coding, clinical data abstracting, business process re-engineering, and conducting coding and data quality studies. For example, with our data quality services, an organization can optimize revenues otherwise lost due to coding discrepancies or incomplete data.
We also offer interim management support for health information management departments. We have helped clients develop more efficient, effective health information departments.We have staffed entire departments or certain functional areas, streamlined operations, and completed departmental evaluations. </P>

<P>Although we are a large organization, we are committed to giving our clients individual attention and we customize solutions that meet their needs. As we are available for long- and short-term projects, clients need not feel that they have to make extensive commitments with us. In most cases, we measure our success by the fact that the client no longer needs our services in a particular area.</P>


<FONT SIZE=4><I><B>Question: How is Aspen unique?</B></I></FONT>

<P>We offer a diverse array of services to each of our clients, including: customized data collection, survey design and analysis, clinical data abstraction, organizing and managing information resources, records management, information systems and telecommunications technical support, and technical assistance and training. We can also support the full range of information management and systems technologies. </P>

<P>Aspen is an employee-owned business, and we have been in operation for over 30 years. We are proud of having experience working with clients of all sizes. This experience has allowed us to recognize what it takes to react quickly, often with little or no advance notice, to new or changing requirements. Moreover, we understand how demanding and unforgiving certain requirements can be in the regulated health care 
environment. </P>

<P>As part of our corporate commitment to being responsive to change, we believe it is critical for us to keep up-to-date with state-of-the-art developments in areas like hardware, software, and telecommunications. We have implemented a conscious, planned effort to stay current. </P>

<HR align=left width=596 size=3>

<P>Meryl Bloomrosen, M.B.A., R.R.A., has been Vice President of Health Information Services at Aspen Systems Corporation since 1987. She has been the Project Director on health information and health data projects for the Federal Government, several State governments, and numerous health care organizations. She has developed and marketed many of Aspen's health information products. 
</P>

<br>
