<title>The Aspen Advantage: An Interview with Meryl Bloomrosen</title><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><IMG align=left hspace=3 
SRC="aspnbug2.gif"><H2>The Aspen Advantage:<BR>An Interview with Meryl Bloomrosen, Vice President of Aspen's Health Information Services Division</H2><BR clear=left>

<FONT SIZE=4><I><B>Question: How did Aspen get started?</B></I><P></FONT>

<A HREF = "redesign.html"><B>Aspen Systems Corporation</B></A> had its start at the University of Pittsburgh when our founders developed a means of storing and retrieving information about the legal codes of various States. So from our very beginning as a corporation, we have been an agent for change. This history reinforces a corporate culture based on finding and applying new and better means of creating, storing, analyzing, and using information. Over the past 30 years, we have pioneered many of the information management standards in use today. Since that time, Aspen has successfully served clients in all sectors of business and government. We currently have more than 1,800 employees, offices across the country, and a growing and diverse client base.<P>

<FONT SIZE=4><I><B>Question: How does Aspen work with its clients?</B></I><P></FONT>

In order to meet client expectations we take great pride in hiring seasoned professionals with the specialized skills necessary to understand and respond to our clients' unique situations. Our staff "speak the language," whatever the subject. We work as a team in relationships with our clients and in our ability to offer our clients a complete range of information management support services. We thrive on client satisfaction. Meeting our clients' expectations efficiently, quickly, and with honesty and poise is one of our main objectives. We strive to deliver the best quality service to a health care industry that is constantly changing and under increasing regulatory pressures. We recognize that many of our clients face new challenges because of changes in payment systems, economic pressures for reorganization, and just the general need to provide more and better services with fewer resources. Our people are our most important resource. This philosophy has promoted a deliberate and consistent growth in our professional staff and its capabilities. Ensuring that company services are of the highest possible quality has always been a priority at Aspen. Aspen's reputation as a firm that provides top quality work is based on the philosophy that satisfaction of client requirements is one of our most important objectives.<P>

<FONT SIZE=4><I><B>Question: What services does Aspen offer to health care clients?</B></I><P></FONT>

We offer a diverse array of services to all our clients, including: customized data collection, survey design and analysis, clinical data abstraction, organizing and managing information resources, records management, information systems and telecommunications technical support, and technical assistance and training. We also support the full range of information management and systems technologies.<P>

We make our services available as individual elements or as components of a complete package. As an ongoing service, we also provide valuable information about changing regulations, codes, and practice guidelines for our clients, making it a lot easier for them to keep abreast in today's constantly changing environment. Our relationship with our clients does not end even after we complete our formal engagement. We make ourselves available to answer client questions on an ongoing basis.<P>

<FONT SIZE=4><I><B>Question: What has Aspen done regarding the Internet?</B></I><P></FONT>

We also now provide a complete range of Internet support services. Our expertise in information management, publishing, systems design, and client service has been successfully applied in our provision of these Internet services, which include the design and development of World Wide Web pages, gopher and file transfer protocol (FTP) sites, and online publications. We have developed several home pages, including our own which can be reached at: <A HREF = "http://www.aspensys.com/"><B>http://www.aspensys.com.</B></A><P>

<HR align=left width=596 size=3>

<B>In the next issue of FOCUS, Meryl will discuss Aspen's uniqueness, and how Aspen can improve the information management practices of a health care organization.</B><P>

Meryl Bloomrosen, M.B.A., R.R.A., has been Vice President of Health Information Services at Aspen Systems Corporation since 1987, where she has been a Project Director on health information and health data products for the Federal Government, several State governments, and numerous health care facilities. She has developed and marketed many of Aspen's information products.<P>

