<title>Coding Corner: Medicare Hospital Manual</title><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><IMG align=left hspace=3 
SRC="aspnbug2.gif"><H2>Coding Corner: Medicare Hospital Manual: Changes Related to Coding, June 1994 -- May 1995</H2>

<FONT SIZE=4><B>The Medicare Hospital Manual is constantly being revised. Aspen receives these updates, identified by transmittal number and date of issue, to add to the manual. Most of the publications relate to billing issues such as new revenue codes, coverage, and reimbursement requirements. Since coding is so closely related to billing, the transmittals below may be of interest to our staff and clients.</B><P></FONT>

<center>
<table border=1 cellpadding=3 height="15%" width="85%">

<tr><th align=center>Transmittal</th><th align=center>Date</th><th align=center>Subject</th></tr>

<tr><td align=center valign=top>666</td><td align=center valign=top>6/94</td><td align=left>Coverage of EPO (epoetin) treatment of anemia in AZT patients, renal failure, and chemo induced non-myeloid malignancies. The anemia standard for ESRD patients must be hct>30 percent hgb>10 percent.</td></tr>

<tr><td align=center valign=top>669</td><td align=center valign=top>9/94</td><td align=left><B>p. 175</B> Resubmitting bills with DRG errors.<P>

<B>p. 189</B> Bone marrow transplant coverage for specific diagnoses.<P>

<B>p. 205</B> Non-specific OR procedures will be rejected unless all OR codes are non-specific.<P>

<B>p. 206</B> Op report is requested on bilateral procedures that don't have a specific code.<P>

<B>p. 279</B> Significant surgery is defined as: incision, excision, amputation, introduction, repair, destruction, endoscopy, suture, or manipulation.<P>

<B>p. 280</B> Reporting scheduled surgery, not carried out.<P>

<B>p. 287</B> OBRA payment rates for ASC groups 1-8.<P>

<B>p. 289</B> List of error types referring to coding errors.<P>
 
<B>p. 433.1</B> DX codes required when billing for Low osmolar contrast material.<P>

<B>p. 494</B> Billing requirements for principal diagnosis with screening mammography:<BR>
<DL><DT><B>High risk:</B>
<DT><B>V10.3</B> personal hx breast CA
<DT><B>V16.3</B> family hx breast CA 
<DT><B>V15.89</B> Null para to age 30
<DT><B>V15.89</B> Pers. hx benign breast disease
</DL>
<I><B>Note:</B> this is an exception to coding rules for using "history-of" V codes as principal dx for these outpatients.</I><P>

<DL><DT><B>Not high risk:</B>
<DT><B>V72.5</B> Other rad. exam.
</DL>

<B>p. 552.14</B> Diagnoses required when billing for clotting factor.</td></tr>
				
<tr><td align=center valign=top>671</td><td align=center valign=top>9/94</td><td align=left>New revenue code 276 for IOL (CPT 66983-66986) charge must be separated for IOL when one of these codes is reported.</td></tr>

<tr><td align=center valign=top>675</td><td align=center valign=top>9/94</td><td align=left>Report V04.81/V03.8 with HCPCS 90732/90724 for PPV/influenza vaccine if the sole purpose was to receive the vaccine. V04.81, V03.8 with HCPCS 90732 (PPV) or 90724 (Influenza) plus Q0124 for the administration.</td></tr>
</table></center><BR>

