<title>Aspen Wins...</title><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><IMG align=left hspace=3 
SRC="aspnbug2.gif"><H2>Aspen Wins Contract From Maryland Health Care Access and Cost Commission</H2>
<H3>Aspen Systems Corporation was recently awarded a contract, along with the Center for Health Policy Studies (CHPS), by the Maryland Health Care Access and Cost Commission (HCACC) to develop the Interim Medical Care Data Base for the State of Maryland. Working with health data and policy analysts, Aspen and the Center for Health Policy Studies analysis staff will develop data collection sources and methodologies to help the Commission produce its annual reports on statewide health services, expenditures, and outcomes and will also design a legislatively mandated State Health Expenditures Account.
</H3>
Aspen is responsible for data base development and analysis of health care expenditure and service data received from multiple data sources. These data sources include Medicaid, Medicare, HMOs, and third party payors such as Blue Cross and Blue Shield. After data are received, Aspen will develop the State data base and perform all data processing activities including data base population, data extraction, processing, and reporting. The initial data base is expected to contain over 60 million records per year for a 2- to 3-year study period.<P>

When fully implemented, Aspen and CHPS staff will provide guidance to the State in developing and implementing a point of sale, online data collection and reporting system to collect data on ambulatory health care services for the State of Maryland. Additionally, it will provide input and lessons learned to the State for the creation of one or more State-sponsored Health Care Claims Processing Clearinghouses.<P> 

<I>For more information, please contact Len Fogelsonger at (800) 395-5055.</I><P>

