<title>In Other News...</title><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><IMG align=left hspace=3 SRC="aspnbug2.gif"><H2><A 
NAME="deptass">Department Assessment: The Key to Improvement</A></H2>
Is it time for a performance checkup? Is your department meeting 
the needs of its customers? Have you been asked to evaluate and 
analyze the performance of your department's services? Are you 
involved in setting budget and financial policy priorities that 
might lead to staffing reductions or layoffs? Is your organization 
preparing for the computerized patient record? If you can answer 
yes to any of these questions, it might be time to conduct a 
formal review of your department's operations.
<P>
Aspen provides technical support to facilities assessing the 
operations of their departments that manage medical records, 
patient accounts, and information systems. As part of our 
services, we will do the following:<P>

<UL><LI> Identify the operating procedures, data flows, reporting systems, quality controls, and productivity standards.
<LI> Analyze the department's operations.
<LI> Identify problems and set priorities for solving them.
<LI> Suggest ways to improve departmental functions and capabilities in response to expected functional changes.
<LI> Develop department business plans.
</UL>

When performing a review of the department's operations, one of 
the first steps is to evaluate the efficiency, productivity, and 
accuracy of the operation. A review of operations usually includes 
making recommended changes that relate to staffing, workflow, 
procedures, and standards. Changes to department operations may be 
necessary to continue to provide current services or to enhance 
services.<P>

To function effectively, the facility's departments cannot operate 
in isolation from the activities of the organization as a whole. 
Services are provided most successfully when 1) there is sound 
administration and information management, 2) the mission of the 
organization is understood, and 3) the lines of responsibility and 
authority are firmly established. In applying its proven 
techniques for health care management, Aspen takes into 
consideration the mission and political nature of the 
organization, as well as the dynamics of today's ever changing 
industry regulations and requirements.<P>

<I>For more information about Aspen's evaluation services, contact 
Meryl Bloomrosen at (800) 395-5055.</I><P>

<IMG border=0 SRC="redbar.gif"><BR><BR>

<IMG align=left hspace=3 SRC="aspnbug2.gif"><H2><A NAME="healpub">Health Care Publishing Services</A></H2>
Hospitals and other health care providers need to communicate 
information to their staff, clients, and communities. <A HREF = "http://www.aspensys.com/servcomm.html">Aspen's 
Publishing Services Division</A> provides professional, customized 
publishing services, from initial idea to finished product, 
including the following:<P>

<UL><LI>Manuals, videos, charts, viewgraphs, computerized learning aids, and other materials for training purposes.
<LI>Brochures and newsletters that inform patients and other recipients of your services or provide patients with information on maintaining good health.
<LI>Promotional brochures, annual reports, media announcements, exhibits, multimedia presentations, and other materials for reaching out to the community.
</UL>

Aspen helps busy health care professionals by offering the entire 
range of services required to meet a particular information 
dissemination need. Aspen's writers, editors, and marketing 
specialists, working closely with the client, develop text 
appropriate to the information, the medium, and the audience. 
Aspen's graphic artists, working on an integrated desktop 
publishing system, develop attractive, functional designs, images, 
and camera-ready pages for a variety of publications and nonprint 
materials including audiovisuals, CD-ROM's, and exhibits of all 
sizes--from tabletop to room-sized. Production professionals, 
working with printing and other vendors, see that the finished 
pieces conform to the client's standards for quality, cost, and 
delivery time.<P>

Depending on the health care client's needs, Aspen's turnkey 
publishing services also incorporate warehousing, mailing list 
management, order fulfillment, and mailing services.<P>

Some clients ask for a range of services, but others have more 
modest requirements. Aspen tailors the scope of services to each 
client's needs. Aspen also relieves health care administrators of 
the need to deal with a variety of vendors about each aspect of 
preparing communications materials for staff, clients, and the 
community. The company has been providing these services to 
government, business, and nonprofit organizations in health care 
and other fields for close to 20 years.<P> 

<I>For more information, contact Scott Crocket at 301-251-5000.</I><P>

