<IMG align=left hspace=3 SRC="aspnbug2.gif"><H2><A NAME="speak">Aspen Staff Speak at National and State Meetings</A></H2>
Aspen health care information management (HIM) specialists have been busy 
during the past few months giving informative and specialized lectures and 
presentations on health information management topics at State and national 
meetings and conventions. Sharing their client information management 
experiences and lessons learned, Aspen staff were featured speakers at the National American Health Information Management Association (AHIMA) meeting in Las Vegas and at several State HIM and Healthcare Financial Management Association (HFMA) meetings and seminars. Meryl Bloomrosen provided an informative presentation on "Meeting the Needs of the User: Factors Contributing to Resistance to Automated Medical Information Systems," while Len Fogelsonger spoke on "Information Resource Management--Strategic Business Planning" at the AHIMA national meeting. Additionally, Ms. Bloomrosen recently addressed the Massachusetts Health Information Management Association on this topic.<P>
 
The following lectures and presentations are scheduled for the remainder of this 
calendar year:<P>

