<title>Hospitals Benefit...</title><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><IMG align=left hspace=3 
SRC="aspnbug2.gif"><H2>Hospitals Benefit From Aspen's Management of Their 
Medical Record Departments</H2>
<H3>Housekeeping. Dietary services. Emergency rooms. These are just some of 
the hospital departments that have turned to <A HREF = "contract.html">contract management</A> to 
improve their operations and reduce costs. Even the administration of 
hospitals has been contracted out to organizations that specialize in that 
area. Medical record departments are no exception. Aspen Systems 
provides contract management to medical record departments. In some 
cases, Aspen manages the entire department; in others, only certain 
functions are managed.</H3>
<P>
Aspen has been able to improve operations and reduce operating costs in 
the medical record departments and the functional areas it manages 
because of its wide-ranging expertise in medical record operations. Aspen 
contract management provides a distinct advantage over the hiring by the 
hospital of a single individual to solve all the problems a department or 
functional area might have. While one person may have significant 
expertise in one or two areas, he or she generally cannot provide a high 
level of expertise in all required areas, and are limited also by the 
multiple demands on their time.</p>
<P>
In contrast to other medical record consulting organizations, Aspen brings 
<I>a team approach</I> to the management of medical record departments as 
well as to the management of specific department functions, such as 
coding. Our health information professionals have significant expertise 
and experience in all areas of medical record operations, including:</p>
<DIR>
<LI>information systems planning and implementation;
<LI>chart completion;
<LI>policy and procedure development;
<LI>coding and abstracting;
<LI>record system management;
<LI>utilization review;
<LI>transcription services;
<LI>microfilming; and
<LI>optical disk system selection.
</DIR>
<P>
Aspen is able to evaluate all aspects of existing department operations 
and provide both prescriptions and implementation at far less cost than a 
hospital would incur hiring permanent staff to do it. Staff with specific 
expertise are available to review each problem area in depth, and develop 
and initiate its resolution. Implementation of solutions may involve still 
other Aspen staff, when appropriate.</p>
<P>
The advantages to hospitals lie in their ability to use Aspen's staff of 
experts without having to hire permanent staff. Aspen staff are provided 
in each instance only for as long as they are needed to solve given 
problems, and implement permanent improvements. In most settings, 
Aspen provides a full-time manager or supervisor, with department staff 
either remaining hospital employees or becoming Aspen employees.
<P>
Aspen's contract management efforts in medical record departments have 
resulted in:</p>
<DIR>
<LI>Significant reductions in accounts receivable and operating costs (Aspen's charges 
have more than paid for themselves!);
<LI>Elimination of backlogs (coding, release of information, loose report filing, etc.);
<LI>Improvement in service to other departments (both internal and external 
"customers");
<LI>Improvement in turnaround time (transcription, coding/abstracting, chart deficiency 
analysis, record retrieval, etc.);
<LI>Elimination of duplicative efforts;
<LI>Development of performance standards (productivity and quality) for each 
department task;
<LI>Development of job descriptions, policy and procedure manuals;
<LI>Redefinition of documentation requirements in medical records;
<LI>In-service training sessions for department staff; and
<LI>Streamlining of file operations.</DIR>
<H4><I>If you would like to discuss the potential of contract management of your entire 
medical record department, or a functional area within it, contact Paul Gustafson, 
Director, Health Records Services, at (800) 395-5055.</I></H4>

