<title>OIG Releases Report...</title><BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><IMG align=left hspace=3 
SRC="aspnbug2.gif"><H2>OIG Releases Report on Coding Physician Services</H2>
<H3>The Office of the Inspector General (OIG), Department of Health and Human 
Services, has recently (May 1994) released a report which "describes the 
vulnerabilities in the maintenance, use, and management of the Current 
Procedural Terminology, Fourth Edition (CPT-4) as they relate to Medicare 
reimbursements."</H3>
<P>
The report, entitled "The Coding of Physician Services" (OEI-03-91-00920) is based on a 
two-phase inspection process. The first phase involved the compilation and review of 25 
reports on CPT-4-related topics. The second phase involved contacting 41 medical 
specialty societies, 12 Medicare carriers, the American Medical Association, the 
American Health Information Management Association, the American Hospital 
Association, the Blue Cross/Blue Shield Association, and the Health Insurance 
Association of America. In addition, an on-line search of a data base of medical journals 
was searched to identify CPT-4-related articles.
<P>
A companion report, entitled "A Compendium of Reports and Literature on 
Coding of Physician Services" (OEI-03-91-00921), provides a detailed 
summary of each document. Some of the findings included the following: 1) 
Incorrect coding affects Medicare reimbursement and causes inequities in 
payment under the Medicare Fee Schedule. 2) The methods by which HCFA 
has incorporated CPT-4 into Medicare's coding system do not ensure 
appropriate reimbursement to Medicare providers. A series of 
recommendations were made to HCFA and AMA to address these and other 
issues identified by the OIG. Contact the OIG if you want more information 
on these reports.</p>

<br><center><font size=4><b><a href="scalesec.html">Next Article</a> | <a href="hospbene.html">Previous Article</a> | <a href="fall1994.html#inthis">Contents of Fall 1994 Issue</a> | <a href="hismain.html">HIS FOCUS Home Page</a></b></font></center><br><br>

