<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Info. Center Design & Management</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: David -->
<!-- Last Update: 3/19/96 10:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: servicdm.htm -->


<BR><CENTER><!-- Header Tag -->
<H2>Information Center Design and Management</H2><BR>
</CENTER>

<FONT SIZE=4>
Aspen is the leading supplier of clearinghouse services to the federal government, having provided such services to numerous agencies within the U.S. Departments of Education, Health and Human Services, Housing and Urban Development, and Justice since 1974.  Clearinghouses, or information centers, are vehicles used by sponsoring agencies to help disseminate program, research, and policy information to their constituency audiences.  These audiences range from federal and state policy officials to local community leaders; from direct service providers to academicians and other researchers; and from members of the media to members of the general public.  Clearinghouses offer these audiences ready access to the information they need to make more informed decisions, identify solutions to common problems, and better understand current trends that may affect future directions.<P>

Aspen designs and manages each clearinghouse in accordance with the specialized dissemination needs of sponsoring agencies.  Most clearinghouses involve performance of the following functions:<P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>Information collection and analysis.</B>  Aspen builds centralized repositories of information on subject areas of coverage of each clearinghouse. Types of information collected may include documents, program descriptions, funding sources, and names and contact information of subject experts. We identify materials to collect by screening internal and external information resources and acquire those most relevant to clearinghouse user interests.<P>

<B>Database development and management.</B> Information collected is synthesized and organized in databases that facilitate access and use.  We apply the latest technologies to create easy-to-use databases that enable individuals to search and retrieve the precise information being sought, whether it is a publication date of a particular study, a telephone number of a local organization, or a statistic from a recently released research report.<P>

<B>Reference and library services.</B>  Individuals seeking information assistance most often contact Aspen's clearinghouses via toll-free 800 lines.  Reference specialists, who are subject matter experts, help callers locate the information they need by reviewing clearinghouse resources maintained and offer a range of responses that match specific needs.  Responses may include providing results of a database search, sending a publication, or making a referral to an external organization. Many of Aspen's clearinghouses also offer library services, including public reading room access, interlibrary loan, and copy reproduction services, which further enhance the identification and acquisition of needed information. <P>

<B>Networking and outreach.</B>  Aspen conducts extensive networking and outreach activities to promote agency initiatives and to inform individuals of clearinghouse products and services. We routinely attend professional conferences and represent client agencies at conference exhibitions.  These exhibitions enable staff  to meet with conference participants, discuss their issues of concern, and direct them to the publications and other resources available that may help resolve concerns.  We also conduct targeted promotional mailings, conduct special marketing to intermediary groups such as professional associations and media organizations, and host clearinghouse briefings and tours. <P>

<B><A HREF = "servcomm.html">Publications and product development</A>.</B> Aspen provides editorial, graphics, and production support in the development of publications distributed by the clearinghouses.  These publications include research reports, program evaluations, journals, bulletins, and newsletters that describe agency sponsored initiatives.  We also create promotional brochures, catalogs, fact sheets, conference exhibits, audiovisual presentations, and other materials that highlight clearinghouse resources and capabilities.<P>

<B><A HREF = "servdist.html">Mailing list management</A>.</B> To support dissemination needs of each clearinghouse, Aspen maintains comprehensive mailing lists composed of audiences served by the sponsoring agencies.  We typically compile mailing lists of registered users, who are individuals who have completed registration forms indicating interest in receiving materials distributed by the clearinghouse. We also develop targeted mail lists, which reflect specific audiences (i.e., state legislators or local community leaders) that sponsoring agencies wish to reach. We have developed sophisticated methods for acquiring, maintaining, and updating mail list information in automated database systems that facilitate access and generation of mailing labels and help to ensure accuracy and currency.<P>

<B><A HREF = "servdist.html">Document distribution</A>.</B>  Each Aspen clearinghouse has extensive document distribution requirements, including publication receipt and storage, inventory management, order processing and fulfillment, and performance of targeted mailings. <P>

<B>Electronic dissemination services.</B>  Increasingly, Aspen is using new information technologies to enhance access and expedite delivery of information available from our clearinghouses.  We design and manage bulletin board systems that enable users to learn of new resources available, order publications, and establish electronic forums or discussion groups with other users.  We offer fax-on-demand and fax broadcasting technologies that facilitate dissemination of time sensitive materials. We also provide a range of <A href="isdhome.html">Internet services</A>, including gopher, World Wide Web, and listservs.<P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

For more information, contact Janet Rosenbaum at <a href=mailto:jrosenbaum@aspensys.com>jrosenbaum@aspensys.com</A>.<P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>
1600 Research Boulevard<BR>
Rockville, MD 20850<P>

Phone: (301) 251-5000<BR>
<A HREF = "http://www.aspensys.com/">http://www.aspensys.com</A><P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>


