<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Legal Services</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: Kai -->
<!-- Last Update: 12/26/96-->
<!-- Source File: servlegl.htm -->


<BR><CENTER><!-- Header Tag -->
<H2>Legal Support Services</H2><BR>
</CENTER>

<FONT SIZE=4>
<H3>Legal Information Management Services Group</H3>

<a href="http://www.legaltechcpi.com/NewYork97/index.html"><img width=50 height=80 border=0 align=left src="tech.gif"></a>

On January 27-29, stop by Aspen's booth (#220-224) at New York Legal Tech in the New York Hilton & Towers, 1335 Avenue of the Americas. We will be demonstrating and discussing various strategies to control the cost of litigation, and presenting our many internet services capabilities.<p>

Aspen's Legal Information Management Services (LIMS) Group is unparalleled in supplying litigation support services to both commercial and Federal Government clients. The LIMS 
professionals offer specialized skills in discovery and document processing as well as database creation and online retrieval to meet the unique requirements of our customers.<P>

LIMS understands and is prepared to deliver the broad spectrum of services that organizations involved in litigation require: evidentiary document file management, legal analysis and research, and customized database products. The division also conducts needs assessments and statistical analyses; designs integrated databases; and develops alternative ways to collect, process, and disseminate information.<P>

Two divisions offer specialized services for LIMS clients. The Federal Litigation Services Division as well as the Commercial Division provide customers with information management services, including project planning and management, document acquisition 
management, document screening, document imaging/optical character recognition processing, document indexing and coding, and document center management.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Federal Litigation Services Division
</H3>

For a decade, we have provided Federal Government agencies with incomparable information management and litigation support. Our team of trained and experienced professionals work in partnership with the Government to streamline document processing and information management activities and to help reduce the costs of litigation. Our extensive experience has encompassed some of the largest and most complex matters ever contested, including cases involving the Bank of Commercial and Credit International (BCCI) and the South Florida Everglades.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Commercial Division</H3>

Aspen's team of litigation professionals within the LIMS Commercial Group has successfully provided legal support for many of the major law firms and corporations in the United States. Our staff has worked in virtually every area of the law, including breach of contract, negligence, antitrust, securities, pharmaceuticals, insurance, and many others. We realize that our clients have a broad range of litigation requirements and are prepared to work very closely with them throughout the entire project, either onsite at 
their offices or in our own facilities. The LIMS Commercial Group offers superior service, including project planning and system design, discovery management, document screening, document optical/imaging character recognition processing, document 
indexing and coding, and depository and facilities management.<P>

In addition, Aspen offers extensive database and image retrieval support through AspenView, the industry's first litigation software to use image management technology to bring the full power of
imaging to the computer desktop. Our staff designed AspenView specifically to meet the unique requirements of litigating attorneys and their support staff. With AspenView, users have total
control over the thousands of documents involved with the discovery process. Users can locate key documents, add value to them, continually access them, track their use, and print them quickly and at low cost.<P>

<HR>
For more information, contact Mel Goldenberg at <a href=mailto:mgoldenberg@aspensys.com>mgoldenburg@aspensys.com</A><P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>
1600 Research Boulevard<BR>
Rockville, MD 20850<P>

Phone: (301) 251-5000<BR>
<A HREF = "http://www.aspensys.com/">http://www.aspensys.com</A><P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>


