<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Library Services</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: David -->
<!-- Last Update: 3/19/96 10:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: servlibr.htm -->


<BR><CENTER><!-- Header Tag -->
<H2>Library Services</H2><BR>
</CENTER>

<FONT SIZE=4>
Aspen provides library and information support services for the operation and management of libraries and records centers, as well as electronic publishing services for administrative policies and procedures.<P>

As a major contractor for full-service libraries, our services include the implementation and operation of automated systems, collection development, acquisition, cataloging, indexing, reference, circulation, distribution, and interlibrary loans.<P>

For more than 12 years, we have been successfully providing these library services for more than seven different agencies in the Federal Government. We also are well positioned to provide comparable services in special libraries and law firms. Life cycle records management services are provided for records processing and management from source data capture to database development, storage, and retrieval of records. Record centers are operated for government, utility companies, banks, law firms, private hospitals, and chemical and pharmaceutical companies.<P>

In addition, we develop and operate databases of government publications for electronic distribution via the Internet and other online systems, both in a bulletin board format and as a full-text search and retrieval service.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Two online services that we manage are HUDCLIPS and HUDCLIPS-Plus.</H3>

HUDCLIPS (the Department of Housing and Urban Development Client Information and Policy System) offers free access to HUD's database of official policies; procedures; announcements, including Federal Register notices and Mortgagee letters; and other materials issued within the past 6 months. Current HUD forms in .gif format are also available from this service.<P>

HUDCLIPS-Plus is an expanded version of HUDCLIPS and offers full-text search and retrieval capabilities for all formal HUD policy, including legislation, regulation, and directives.<P>

Internet services offered include:

<UL>
<LI><A HREF = "telnet://telnet://bbs@hudclips.aspensys.com/">Telnet connection to HUDCLIPS</A>: (Users must register for HUDCLIPS prior to logging in.)<P>
<LI><A HREF = "telnet://telnet://bbs@hudclips.aspensys.com/">Telnet connection to HUDCLIPS-Plus</A>: Type "guest" at the login: prompt to access our free guest account.
</UL>

<HR>
For more information, contact Carol Johnson at <a href=mailto:cjohnson@aspensys.com>cjohnson@aspensys.com</a><P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>
1600 Research Boulevard<BR>
Rockville, MD 20850<P>

Phone: (301) 251-5000<BR>
<A HREF = "http://www.aspensys.com/">http://www.aspensys.com</A><P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>


