<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Distribution Services</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: David -->
<!-- Last Update: 3/19/96 10:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: servdist.htm -->


<BR><CENTER><!-- Header Tag -->
<H2>Distribution Services</H2><BR>
</CENTER>

<FONT SIZE=4>
We offer full-service order fulfillment, storage, inventory management, and mailing services in support of both government and commercial clients. We operate three state-of-the-art distribution
centers in the Baltimore-Washington corridor that combined represent more than 160,000 square feet of storage and operations space. Each year these facilities distribute more than 41 million printed and other product materials.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Order Fulfillment Services</H3> 

Aspen provides a complete range of order fulfillment services, including operation of telephone ordering lines, customer service support, mail processing, payment processing, development of order fulfillment and inventory management systems, picking and packing of orders, and shipping operations. Our experienced distribution management team will work with clients to implement an order fulfillment process that is tailored to your specific needs and provides a cost-efficient alternative to handling order processing and customer service support within your organization.<P>

Aspen's telephone support operations are supported by a state-of-the-art call management system, complete with reporting capabilities to analyze call volumes. We offer experience in
handling payment processing for orders received by phone and mail. Our fulfillment operations are supported by integrated order fulfillment/inventory management systems that can be customized and scaled to a particular organization's needs.<P>

The order fulfillment staff are experienced in handling a variety of product types, including books, pamphlets, newsletters, maps, audio and video tapes, and CD-ROM's. Work flow management procedures ensure that orders are filled in an accurate and timely manner. Packing procedures ensure that products are received by customers without damage.<P>

Our shipping operations handle both small volume shipping as well as bulk volumes and are supported by state-of-the-art metering systems that ensure the most cost-efficient shipping method. We use all major carriers including the United States Postal Service, United Parcel Service, Roadway Package Systems, and Federal Express for small package shipments, and a variety of air freight and common carriers for volume shipments. Aspen's shipping operations
will ensure that your materials are shipped in the most cost-efficient and expeditious manner available.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Storage and Records Management</H3> 

Aspen's distribution operations have more than 160,000 square feet of high-density storage space for bulk storage of printed and other information products. This space is also used for storage in support of our records management services. Aspen has developed highly sophisticated inventory management procedures supported by automated inventory management systems to track and accurately store materials in a cost-efficient environment. The inventory management processes include the use of bar coding technologies for efficient updating of inventory records.<P>

Our records management and retrieval services provide timely storage of materials, accurate maintenance of inventory records, and quick turnaround of retrieval requests. In addition to our storage of physical paper records, Aspen can provide complete imaging capability for <A HREF = "servscan.html">electronic storage of information</A>.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Mailing Services</H3>

Aspen also provides mailing support services that include materials development through our <A HREF = "servcomm.html">Communication Services</A>, insertion and collation of mailing packages, labeling, and bulk mailing support. Our labeling services are processed using a state-of-the-art computerized ink jet labeling system. In addition to labeling, this system can customize messages on mailing packets to further enhance your direct mailing. The system can convert mailing labels from most list databases and will print bar code and ZIP plus four for use in obtaining postal discounts for your mailing.<P>

In addition to performing mailing services, Aspen can help you develop and maintain your mailing list database. We have experienced staff available to assist you in developing a targeted mailing list as well as keeping that list up to date. We can assist you in receiving postal certification for your list that will enable you to generate mailing labels that will meet USPS requirements for bulk discounts. Aspen uses a number of computerized database systems to support mailing list development and maintenance requirements. These systems are supported by our experienced system professionals who have experience in converting existing files, customizing database applications, and developing reports that assist you in managing your direct mail activities.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Electronic Dissemination Support</H3>

Aspen has developed extensive capabilities to supplement traditional paper product distribution through use of electronic dissemination vehicles. These services include interactive voice response order taking, fax-on-demand, print-on-demand, and online distribution through the Internet. Each of these services provides opportunities for cost savings in distributing information.<P>

<B>Interactive Voice Response Ordering.</B> Aspen has developed an order-taking system that enables customers with a touch-tone phone to place an order for materials without talking to a customer
service representative. This service is ideal for providing 24-hour/7-day-a-week access to customers who wish to place an order for materials at their convenience. This system helps reduce the costs associated with staffing a customer service response operation.<P>

<B>Fax-on-Demand.</B> We can provide fax-on-demand services for organizations that wish to provide an alternative to traditional hard-copy distribution of a paper product. Our fax-on-demand services enable a customer to call into a user-friendly menu and to select materials to be faxed automatically to their own fax machine. This greatly increases response time for the customer. The system has payment processing options through use of credit cards, including card number validation capabilities.<P>

<B>Print-on-Demand.</B> Aspen can assist your organization in cutting storage costs for printed materials by providing print-on-demand services. Print only the copies of a paper document or pamphlet that you actually need rather than paying the costs for storing excess or used copies. The print-on-demand services provide high-quality black and white reproductions using high-speed laser printing capabilities. This service is ideal for low-demand products or for creating an archive of older materials that you would like to keep available but don't want to continue to pay storage costs for. Through our <A HREF = "servscan.html">Image Processing Center</A> we can assist you in converting your current inventory from paper to image files for long-term storage and use with our print-on-demand services.<P>

<B>Internet Distribution.</B> In today's environment, dissemination of printed material through the Internet has been an increasingly attractive alternative to traditional distribution processes. Aspen is well positioned to assist organizations in developing an Internet dissemination program that meets each organization's specific distribution requirements and expands its reach internationally through the Internet. Our <A HREF = "isdhome.html">Internet Services Division</A> provides a full range of Internet-related services, including site development, hosting services, and technical systems support for organizations interested in tapping into this new media for information dissemination, marketing,
and product distribution support.<P>

<HR>
For more information about Aspen's Distribution Services, contact Andrew Johnson at <a href=mailto:ajohnson@aspensys.com>ajohnson@aspensys.com</a><P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>
1600 Research Boulevard<BR>
Rockville, MD 20850<P>

Phone: (301) 251-5000<BR>
<A HREF = "http://www.aspensys.com/">http://www.aspensys.com</A><P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>


