<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Telecommunications</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: David -->
<!-- Last Update: 3/19/96 10:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: servtele.htm -->


<BR><CENTER><!-- Header Tag -->
<H2>Telecommunications Consulting Services</H2>
</CENTER>

<FONT SIZE=4>
 Unlike our competitors, Aspen offers a unique synergy of telecommunications support services
 and consulting capabilities that mirror your industry's paradigm -- the marriage of
 telecommunications services and information content providers. With this perspective, Aspen
 offers a proven track record in understanding the complexity of telecommunications applications
 and a unique combination of consulting services specifically designed to address the needs of the
 telecommunications industry.<P>
 
Over the past decade, Aspen has earned the reputation in the telecommunications industry for
 providing high-quality telecommunications project and support services. We understand the
 dynamic nature of the telecommunications industry and your desire to position your back office
 applications to rapidly deploy new products and services.<P>
 
 Aspen offers a variety of specialized consulting services founded on our extensive experience
 in telecommunications and information management. Our technical personnel are versed in
 implementing customized telecommunications applications that operate independently and in
 conjunction with off-the-shelf application packages and outsourced services.<P>
 <HR>
 <H3>Traffic Management Services</H3>
 
 Aspen's <B>Traffic Management Services</B> include a cadre of industry proven implementations of business event collection, monitoring, normalization, evaluation, and data warehousing applications.<P> 
 
<UL><LI> Aspen's custom developed <B>Business Event Executive Information Systems</B> provide 
sophisticated
 traffic data analysis tools to monitor call traffic for engineering management and planning
 applications, and for customer, product, and service tracking analysis.<BR>
 <BR>
<LI>Aspen's experience in <B>Normalized Event Formatting</B> provides a method to effectively integrate
 disparate CDRs and other messaging event data.<BR>
 <BR>
<LI>Aspen's expertise in <B>Real Time Event Data Collection</B> provides an extremely cost-effective
 method to quickly integrate product and service offerings operating outside of your existing
 event collection infrastructure.<BR><BR> 
 
<LI>Aspen's development of <B>Event Data Warehousing Facilities</B> offer the opportunity to develop
 easily accessible data repositories for event data.
</UL><P> 
<HR>
 <H3>Telecommunications Quality Assurance Services</H3>
 
 The success of new applications is not measured in the richness of their features but rather
 through customer acceptance. Recognizing this success factor, Aspen strongly believes that our
 <B>Telecommunications Quality Assurance Services</B> help ensure that our client's strategic
 applications can be successfully deployed.<P>
 
<UL><LI>Aspen's <B>Applications Acceptance Testing Services</B> provide an independent perspective to test
 internally developed applications or an independent third party perspective to police external
 billing service providers and custom system development firms.<BR> 
 <BR>
<LI>Aspen's <B>Customer and User Satisfaction Evaluation Services</B> offer traditional customer survey
 and data analysis capabilities to integrate customer feedback into your systems development
 process.</UL><P> 
 <HR>
 <H3>Custom Application Development Service</H3>
 
 Aspen's <B>Custom Application Development Service</B> provides extensive experience in developing
 and supporting client/server applications and traditional mainframe systems. Our success in
 telecommunications application development is based on recognizing the need to focus first on
 the telephony not the technology aspect of each effort.<P>
 <HR>
 <H3>Experience Breeds Success</H3>
 
 Working in the telecommunications industry for over a decade, Aspen has gained a wide variety
 of experience in supporting legacy systems and developing state-of-the-art information
 management applications. This diversity and expertise in telephony applications and operations
 has made Aspen a preferred vendor with many Inter Exchange Carriers (IXCs), Local Exchange
 Carriers (LECs), and other telecommunications firms -- we understand the industry and have
 proven experience in the following areas:<P>
 
<UL><LI>Voice and Data Billing Systems
 
<LI>Provisioning and Trouble Management Systems
 
<LI>Network Operation Systems
 
<LI>Network Planning Systems
 
<LI>Customer Information Systems
 
<LI>Order Entry Systems
 
<LI>Financial and Accounting Systems
 
<LI>Marketing Systems</UL>
 <HR>
 <H3>Commitment to Quality</H3>
 
 Aspen's success is founded on a guarantee that our clients are satisfied with our services. We
 are committed to offering highly qualified staff and a vast array of corporate resources required
 to support each project.<P> 
 <HR>
 
<BLOCKQUOTE>
For more information, contact Mark Lay at <a href=mailto:mlay@aspensys.com>mlay@aspensys.com</a><P>
 
