<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Corporate Communications Support</TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#3B17FF" VLINK="#FF0900">

<!-- System: Aspen Home Page -->
<!-- Author: Aspen Systems Corporation (www.aspensys.com) -->
<!-- Editor: David -->
<!-- Last Update: 3/19/96 10:00pm-->
<!-- Source File: servcomm.htm -->


<BR><CENTER><!-- Header Tag -->
<H2>Corporate Communications Support and Publishing</H2><BR>
</CENTER>

<FONT SIZE=4>
The staff of Aspen's Communications Services Department are accomplished professionals. Over nearly two decades, they have honed the skills needed to create and effectively disseminate a
wide range of information products -- from developing media kits, newsletters, brochures, technical reports, resource directories, and conference materials, to creating CD-ROM's and interactive computer products.<P>

Working within established publishing industry guidelines, 80 communications specialists provide Aspen's clients with full-service communications and publishing services. Supported by a state-of-the-art computerized desktop publishing network, the editorial and graphics staff approach publications and product development as a team experience. In support of its clients, this unit creates more than 1,500 products annually.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Editorial Services</H3> 

Our editors offer a full range of writing and editing services tailored to each client's specific needs. Matrix staffing allows correlation between project-specific demands and editorial subject-area expertise.  This staffing approach enables our editorial services staff to work in close conjunction with the substantive knowledge represented within Aspen's program divisions. We can also draw on our well-established consultant and freelance editorial pool to address specific project needs.<P>

Writing and editing capabilities include:<P>

<UL>
<LI> original writing and research<P>

<LI>substantive editing for organization, structure, sense, comprehensiveness, readability, and polish<P>

<LI>proofreading and copyediting for grammar, consistency, and compliance with U.S. Government Printing Office (GPO) and other appropriate styles
</UL><P>

Tailoring editorial output to specific product needs, the group follows established quality control routines that allow for client input as a product progresses.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Graphics Services</H3> 

Aspen's award-winning design staff provide design solutions for a broad array of information materials. In addition to traditional materials such as newsletters, journals, books, and reports, our graphics staff creates logos, videos, banners, room-size full-color exhibits, and other conference materials such as signs, overheads, tabletop displays, and name badges. We can also draw on graphics experts in our freelance and consultant pools to augment our inhouse graphics talent.<P>

Aspen's approach to design development demands the involvement of our clients at all stages. Particularly on major projects, the design group follows a sequence of steps beginning with thumbnail sketches for client review and selection and ending with full-color design comprehensives that approximate the finished published piece. Because of the range of artistic skills on staff, we can provide clients with hand-drawn illustrations as well as sophisticated computer-generated graphics. All print products are produced on an integrated desktop publishing network that supports both the editorial and graphics functions.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Special Projects</H3>

A separate creative group within Aspen's graphics staff, the Special Projects Unit, also uses multimedia software to create products integrating graphics, animation, sound, and video. The Special Projects Unit is responsible for the creation of all nontraditional products including exhibits, packaging, videos, and interactive multimedia products.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Production Services</H3>

Aspen's Communication Services is rounded out by its production group, which provides traffic control for the 1,500 products produced annually by the department. As part of our support for our clients, the production group vends over $2 million annually of printed or manufactured products from full-color brochures to silk-screened banners and exhibits.<P>

<HR>
<H3>Desktop Publishing System</H3>

Our integrated desktop publishing system offers the capabilities to produce a wide range of sharp, visually attractive information products. Working in both PC and Macintosh environments, we have the capability to send and receive files and messages via e-mail; transfer files to disks, videotape, or CD-ROM; convert software between PC and Macintosh platforms; and produce a wide variety of traditional and electronic publications using dozens of software packages.<P>

<HR>
For more information, contact Elaine Jaye at <a href=mailto:ejaye@aspensys.com>ejaye@aspensys.com</a><P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
Aspen Systems Corporation<BR>
1600 Research Boulevard<BR>
Rockville, MD 20850<P>

Phone: (301) 251-5000<BR>
<A HREF = "http://www.aspensys.com/">http://www.aspensys.com</A><P>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

<HR>
